\h Census
\toc1 Census
\toc2 Census
\toc3 Cen.
\mt1 Census
\mt3 often called
\mt2 Numbers
\is1 Introduction
\ip The English word ‘Numbers’ relates to the census of Israeli fighting men so we have chosen to rename it as \bk ‘Census’\bk*. (Actually, there are \em two\em* censuses described in this document, but the plural form of the word feels less comfortable to pronounce.) Hebrew readers call this document ‘Bemidbar’ which is the fourth word in the Hebrew text, and means ‘In the wilderness’. Some European and other translations call it ‘The fourth book of Mosheh’ (Moses).
\ip This document tells about the descendants of Yisrael (called ‘Israel’ in older translations) for the forty years after their departure from Mt. Sinai, until they arrived at the eastern edge of the land that God has promised to give them. This document is named after the census that Yahweh ordered Mosheh to take before the Israelis had left Mt. Sinai.
\ip Then the Israelis purified themselves and celebrated their second ‘pass-over’ festival after some forty years had passed.
\ip Also at that time, the second census of fighting men was taken, i.e., a generation later at Kadesh-Barnea at Kanaan's southern boundary. But from Kadesh-Barnea, none of them entered the land that Yahweh had promised to give them.
\ip When they were still camped east of the Yarden (Jordan) River, two and a half tribes requested to be given territory on that side of the river, although they sent their fighting men ahead with the other tribes to help them conquer Kanaan.
\ip This ‘Census’ document also records how people were often scared and discouraged as they faced hardship, causing them to sometimes rebel against Yahweh and his chosen servant Mosheh who led them. However, Yahweh's (mostly) patient endurance of their behaviour is told here, and his faithfulness throughout their generations. It reveals Mosheh as an obedient yet humble leader who was devoted both to Yahweh and to the people he had responsibility for.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The Israelis prepare to depart from Sinai \ior 1:1–9:23\ior*
\io2 a. The first Israeli census \ior 1:1–4:49\ior*
\io2 b. Various laws and regulations \ior 5:1–8:26\ior*
\io2 c. The second celebration of the messenger's ‘pass-over’ \ior 9:1-23\ior*
\io1 From Mt. Sinai to Moav (Moab)\ior 10:1–21:35\ior*
\io1 The events in Moav \ior 22:1–32:42\ior*
\io1 The places passed through by the Israelis \ior 33:1-49\ior*
\io1 Warnings before crossing the Yarden (Jordan) river \ior 33:50–36:13\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 The first census of the Israelis by Mosheh
\rem /s1 The First Census of Israel; The Census; Israel's First Census; Israel in the wilderness of Sinai
\p
\v 1 In April of the year¦61073 after¦61075 the Israeli people \add ≈escaped from\add* Egypt¦61077 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*, Yahweh¦61062 spoke¦61061 to Mosheh¦61065 \add (Moses¦61065)\add* in the Sinai¦61067 wilderness¦61066 in the \add ≈sacred¦61068\add* tent¦61068, saying,\x + \xo 1:1-46: \xt Num 26:1-51.\x*
\v 2 “\add ≈Count all the men who are Yisrael's descendants by their clans¦61090 and families, being sure to list all their names¦61094\add*.
\v 3 \add Only include those\add* who are twenty¦61101 or older and able \add to be recruited\add* as soldiers. You and Aharon must¦61109 enrol¦61109 them into military¦61111 divisions¦61111.
\v 4 \add ≈The leader of each tribe¦61119 will accompany\add* you.
\p
\v 5 These are the names¦61128 of the men¦61129 who will \add ≈assist\add* you:
\li1 Elitsur¦61134 (Shedeyur's son) from Reuven,
\li1
\v 6 Shelumiel¦61140 (Tsuri-Shaddai's¦61143 son) from Shimeon \add (Simeon)\add*,
\li1
\v 7 Nahshon¦61146 (Amminadav's son) from Yehudah \add (Judah)\add*,
\li1
\v 8 Netanel¦61152 (Tsuar's¦61155 son) from Yissakar \add (Issachar)\add*,
\li1
\v 9 Eliav (Helon's¦61161 son) from Zevulun,
\li1
\v 10 Elishama (Ammihud's¦61169 son) from Yosef's¦61164 son Efrayim,
\li1 Gamliel (Pedahtsur's son) from Yosef's son Menashsheh \add (Manasseh¦61170)\add*,
\li1
\v 11 Avidan (Gideoni's son) from Benyamin,
\li1
\v 12 Ahiezer¦61183 (Ammishaddai's¦61186 son) from Dan,
\li1
\v 13 Pagiel¦61189 (Okran's son) from Asher,
\li1
\v 14 Elyasaf (Reuel's¦61198 son) from Gad,
\li1
\v 15 Ahira¦61201 (Enan's¦61204 son) from Naftali.
\v 16 They¦61215 were the leaders of their tribes¦61211—chosen out of their communities¦61209, and leaders of \add units of\add* one thousand \add soldiers\add*.
\p
\v 17 Mosheh¦61219 and¦61220 Aharon¦61220 took¦61218 those men¦61222 whose names¦61226 had been \add ≈given\add*
\v 18 and¦61228 they assembled the entire¦61229 community¦61231 that April. \add ≈For each tribe,\add* they recorded¦61236 their¦61248 ancestry¦61241 by clan, counting the names¦61243 of those men who were twenty¦61245 or over,
\v 19 just as Yahweh¦61252 had commanded¦61251 Mosheh¦61255. \add ≈So\add* he¦61251 counted¦61256 them \add there\add* in¦61257 the Sinai¦61258 wilderness¦61257,
\v 20-21 individually counting those \add in each tribe below\add* by their¦61273 clan, and only including¦61261 males who were twenty¦61278 or older and able to fight in battle:
\li1 46,500 men from the tribe of Reuven,
\li1
\v 22-23 59,300 men from the tribe of Shimeon \add (Simeon¦61296)\add*,
\li1
\v 24-25 45,560 men from the tribe of Gad¦61327,
\li1
\v 26-27 74,600 men from the tribe of Yehudah¦61354 \add (Judah)\add*,
\li1
\v 28-29 54,400 men from the tribe of Yissakar \add (Issachar¦61380)\add*,
\li1
\v 30-31 57,400 men from the tribe of Zevulun¦61406,
\li1
\v 32-33 40,500 men from the tribe of Efrayim¦61434,
\li1
\v 34-35 32,200 men from the tribe of Menashsheh \add (Manasseh¦61459)\add*,
\li1
\v 36-37 35,400 men from the tribe of Benyamin¦61484,
\li1
\v 38-39 62,700 men from the tribe of Dan¦61510,
\li1
\v 40-41 41,500 men from the tribe of Asher¦61536,
\li1
\v 42-43 53,400 men from the tribe of Naftali¦61562.
\p
\v 44 Those were the ones that Mosheh¦61591 and Aharon and the twelve Israeli¦61593 leaders¦61593 (one from each tribe) listed.
\v 45 They were all the \add ≈Israelis¦61609\add* who were counted according to their¦61614 \add ≈ancestry¦61614\add*, being men who were twenty¦61616 or older, and¦61618 \add ≈capable of going off to battle\add*—
\v 46 603,550 of them in total¦61626.
\v 47 \add ≈However,\add* the Levites \add ≈weren't listed along with¦61644 the other tribes¦61640\add*
\v 48 \add ≈because\add* Yahweh¦61648 had told Mosheh¦61651,
\v 49 “Don't list the Levites \add ≈or count them with the other Israelis¦61667\add*.
\v 50 \add ≈Instead,\add* appoint¦61671 \add *them\add* to manage the tent¦61677 \add ≈where the copy of the agreement is kept\add*, along with all its¦61700 equipment. They must¦61690 serve¦61700 inside it as \add required\add*, and¦61670 they should \add ≈set their tents up around¦61701 it\add*.
\v 51 \add ≈When¦61714 it's time to leave that place\add*, the Levites¦61709 must take¦61707 \add @the tent¦61706\add* down and¦61705 when camp \add ≈is set up\add*, they must erect it \add again\add*, \add ≈but¦61705\add* any stranger¦61715 who approaches¦61716 it must be \add ≈executed\add*.
\v 52 \add When¦61721\add* the \add other\add* \add ≈Israelis¦61720\add* set up camp, each man¦61726 must¦61719 set up with his army division¦61730 by their¦61730 banner,
\v 53 \add ≈but¦61732\add* the Levites¦61747 will camp there around¦61734 the \add ≈sacred tent¦61735\add* and¦61732 look after it¦61739. \add ≈That way,\add* the Israeli¦61744 community won't¦61737 make \add Yahweh\add* angry.
\v 54 \add ≈So¦61754 the Israelis¦61756 did everything\add* that Yahweh¦61760 had instructed¦61759 Mosheh¦61763.
\c 2
\s1 Camp layout by tribe
\rem /s1 The Arrangement of the Tribal Camps; The Arrangement of the Tribes in Camp; The Order of Encampment and Marching; Organization for Israel's Camp
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦61769 told Mosheh¦61772 and Aharon:
\p
\v 2 “The \add ≈Israelis¦61787\add* must camp \add ≈with¦61782 each family joining their¦61784 tribe\add*, \add ≈which will be displaying its\add* banner¦61782. They must camp around¦61789 the \add ≈sacred¦61790 tent but\add* at¦61782 a distance¦61788.
\p
\v 3 On the eastern¦61796 side facing the sunrise¦61797 will be Yehudah's¦61800 \add (Judah's)\add* banner and¦61802 their¦61801 army divisions¦61801, led by Amminadav's son Nahshon¦61805
\v 4 with 74,600 in his division¦61810.
\v 5 The tribe¦61820 of Yissakar \add (Issachar¦61821)\add* will \add ≈set up\add* next to them, led by Tsuar's¦61828 son Netanel¦61825,
\v 6 with 54,400 in his division¦61830.
\v 7 Then the tribe¦61839 of Zevulun, led by Helon's¦61847 son Eliav,
\v 8 with 57,400 in his division¦61849.
\v 9 The total number in the divisions¦61872 in the Yehudah¦61861 camp¦61860 is 186,400, and \add ≈when travelling\add*, \add ≈they'll all go at the front\add*.
\p
\v 10 On the southern¦61880 side \add of the sacred tent\add* will be Reuven's banner, led by Shedeyur's son Elitsur
\v 11 with 46,500 in his division¦61890.
\v 12 The tribe¦61900 of Shimeon \add (Simeon¦61901)\add* will \add ≈set up\add* next to them, led by Tsuri-Shaddai's son Shelumiel¦61905
\v 13 with 59,300 in his division¦61912.
\v 14 Then¦61920 the tribe¦61920 of Gad¦61921, led by Reuel's¦61928 son Elyasaf.
\v 15 with 45,650 in his division¦61930.
\v 16 The total number in the divisions¦61953 in the Reuven camp¦61942 is 151,450, and \add ≈when travelling\add*, \add ≈they'll all go second¦61954\add*.
\p
\v 17 Then the Levites¦61963 will go next with their¦61974 own banners in the order that they were camped, \add carrying\add* the \add ≈sacred¦61959 tent¦61959\add*.
\p
\v 18 On the western side \add of the sacred tent\add* will be Efrayim's banner, led by Ammihud's¦61988 son Elishama
\v 19 with 40,500 in his division¦61990.
\v 20 The tribe¦61998 of Menashsheh \add (Manasseh¦61999)\add* will \add ≈set up\add* next to them, led by Pedahtsur's son Gamliel
\v 21 with 32,200 in his division¦62008.
\v 22 Then¦62015 the tribe¦62015 of Benyamin¦62016 led by Gideoni's son Avidan
\v 23 with 35,400 in his division¦62025.
\v 24 The total number in the divisions¦62044 in the Efrayim camp¦62036 is 108,100, and \add ≈when travelling\add*, \add ≈they'll all go third¦62045\add*.
\p
\v 25 On¦62056 the northern¦62052 side \add of the sacred tent\add* will be Dan's¦62051 banner, led by Ammishaddai's¦62060 son Ahiezer¦62057
\v 26 with 62,700 in his division¦62062.
\v 27 The tribe¦62072 of Ahser will \add ≈set up\add* next to them, led by Okran's son Pagiel¦62077
\v 28 with 41,500 in his division¦62082.
\v 29 Then¦62090 the tribe¦62090 of Naftali¦62091 led by Enan's¦62098 son Ahira¦62095
\v 30 with 53,400 in his division¦62100.
\v 31 The total number in the divisions in the Dan¦62112 camp¦62111 is 157,600, and \add ≈when travelling\add*, \add ≈they'll all go last\add* with their¦62122 banners.
\p
\v 32 Those¦62129 are the listed \add ≈Israelis¦62127 by their ancestral¦62131 tribes\add* \add ≈with a total¦62132 of 603,500 fighting men\add*.
\v 33 However, \add ≈following\add* Yahweh's instructions¦62154, the Levites weren't listed among them.
\p
\v 34 \add ≈So¦62160\add* the \add ≈Israelis¦62162\add* did everything¦62163 that Yahweh¦62167 commanded¦62166 Mosheh¦62170. They camped¦62173 under their banners, and \add ≈travelled grouped in their tribes and clans¦62178\add*.
\c 3
\s1 Aharon's sons
\rem /s1 The Levites; The Sons of Aaron; Levites Appointed for Service; Aaron's Sons
\p
\v 1 \add ≈The following\add* are the descendants¦62185 of Aharon \add (Aaron¦62186)\add* and¦62187 Mosheh as on the day¦62188 when Yahweh¦62190 spoke¦62189 with¦62194 Mosheh on Mt¦62194. Sinai¦62195:
\v 2 Aharon's sons¦62199 were: Nadav (the oldest), Avihu, Eleazar¦62206, and¦62197 Itamar¦62207.\x + \xo 3:2: \xt Num 26:60.\x*
\v 3 They¦62212 were \add all\add* anointed¦62214 as priests and \add ≈served¦62219 in that role\add*,
\v 4 \add ≈except that\add* Nadav and Avihu died¦62221 \add ≈in front¦62224\add* of Yahweh¦62225 when they offered¦62226 \add ≈unacceptable\add* fire¦62227 to \add *him\add* in the Sinai¦62232 wilderness¦62231, and \add so\add* they had no sons¦62233. \add ≈So¦62221\add* Eleazar¦62239 and Itamar¦62240 served¦62238 as priests¦62238 \add ≈alongside\add* their¦62245 father¦62245 Aharon.\x + \xo 3:4: \xt Lev 10:1-2; Num 26:61.\x*
\s1 The Levites as ransom for their sons
\rem /s1 The Duties of the Levites; The Levites Are Appointed to Serve the Priests
\p
\v 5 Then Yahweh¦62249 told Mosheh¦62252,
\v 6 “Summon the Levites to come and stand¦62260 in front¦62262 of Aharon the priest¦62264, so they¦62265 can assist¦62265 him.
\v 7 They must¦62268 perform¦62268 duties¦62271 for him¦62271 and for the entire¦62275 community¦62277 at and around the \add ≈sacred¦62285 tent¦62285\add*,
\v 8 including¦62295 looking after all of its equipment and¦62295 \add ≈fulfilling the obligations\add* of the \add ≈Israelis¦62299\add*.
\v 9 You must¦62306 assign the Levites¦62309 to Aharon—out of all the \add ≈Israelis¦62317\add* it's them who are assigned \add to serve the priests\add*.
\v 10 Appoint Aharon and his sons¦62325 as priests and to preserve the priesthood. Any other person \add ≈who tries to act as a priest\add* \add ≈must¦62326 be executed\add*.”
\p
\v 11 Then Yahweh¦62337 told Mosheh¦62340,
\v 12 “Out of all the \add ≈Israelis¦62350\add*, I've¦62345 taken¦62345 the Levites instead of the \add ≈oldest son from every¦62353 family\add*. The Levites \add ≈will be the ransom for those sons¦62358\add*, and¦62360 so they¦62360 belong to me,
\v 13 because every firstborn male person and animal is set aside as belonging¦62387 to me ever since I killed those firstborn males in¦62381 Egypt¦62375. I am Yahweh¦62389.”
\s1 The census of the Levites
\rem /s1 A Census of the Levites; The Census of the Levites
\p
\v 14 Then in¦62397 the Sinai¦62398 wilderness¦62397, Yahweh¦62393 told Mosheh¦62396,
\v 15 “List all the male¦62411 Levites that are at least one month¦62414 old. Count them by their families and clans¦62408.”
\v 16 \add ≈So¦62418\add* Mosheh¦62420 listed them exactly as Yahweh¦62424 had commanded¦62426 him to,
\v 17 and these¦62430 were Levi's¦62433 sons¦62431: Gershon¦62435, Kohat¦62436, and Merari¦62437.
\v 18 Gershon's¦62443 sons¦62441 were: Livni¦62445 and¦62446 Shimei¦62446.
\v 19 Kohat's¦62449 sons¦62448 were: Amaran, Yitshar, Hevron, and¦62448 Uzziyel.
\v 20 Merari's¦62457 sons¦62456 were Mahli¦62459 and¦62456 Mushi¦62460.
\m Those were the families of the Levites¦62464 by their clans.
\p
\v 21 Gershon's descendants were the Livnites and¦62471 the Shimites, so they¦62474 made up the Gershonites.
\v 22 They had 7,500 males that were at¦62479 least a month¦62485 old.
\v 23 The Gershonite clans¦62493 were to camp on the western side of the \add ≈sacred¦62496 tent¦62496\add*,
\v 24 and¦62500 \add *their\add* leader¦62500 was Lael's¦62508 son Elyasaf.
\v 25 Gershon's¦62513 descendants¦62511 were responsible¦62510 for the \add ≈sacred¦62516 tent¦62516\add*, including¦62517 its¦62518 covering¦62518 and¦62510 the entrance¦62520 curtain,
\v 26 the courtyard curtains, and¦62524 the courtyard entrance¦62529 curtain, that¦62531 surrounded \add *it\add*. Also the ropes¦62540 \add ≈used to hold them\add*.
\p
\v 27 Kohat's descendants were the Amramites, the Yitsharites, the Hevronites, and¦62544 the Uzziyelites, so they¦62554 made up the Kohatites.
\v 28 They had 8,600 males that were at least a month¦62564 old. They were in charge of the running of the \add ≈sacred¦62572 tent¦62572\add*.
\v 29 The Kohatite clans¦62574 were to camp of the southern¦62582 side of the \add ≈sacred¦62581 tent¦62581\add*,
\v 30 and¦62584 \add *their\add* leader¦62584 was Uzziyel's son Elitsafan.
\v 31 They were in charge of the box, the table¦62598 and the lampstand¦62599, the altars¦62600 and all the utensils used for ministry, the \add inside\add* curtain and its¦62608 gear.
\p
\v 32 The man who organised the Levites¦62612 was Aharon's son, Eleazar¦62613 the priest¦62617. He had oversight¦62618 over all those who were responsible for the \add ≈sacred¦62621 tent¦62621\add*.
\p
\v 33 Merari's descendants were the Mahlites and¦62626 the Mushites, so they¦62629 made up the Merarites.
\v 34 They had 6,200 males that were at¦62634 least a month¦62640 old,
\v 35 and¦62646 their leader¦62646 was Avihayil's son Tsuriel¦62652. They were to camp on the northern¦62660 side of the \add ≈sacred¦62658 tent¦62658\add*.
\v 36 \add *They\add* were in charge of all the frames¦62666 for the \add ≈sacred¦62667 tent¦62667\add*, its crossbars, posts, bases¦62670, all its containers and¦62662 equipment¦62673,
\v 37 as well as the pillars¦62677 \add used to make\add* the courtyard¦62678 with their bases¦62680, pegs, and¦62677 ropes¦62682.
\p
\v 38 Mosheh¦62694 and Aharon and his sons¦62697 \add ≈set up their tents\add* \add ≈in front¦62685 of\add* \add the entrance on\add* the eastern¦62687 side of the \add ≈sacred¦62700 tent\add*. They were in charge of that tent and \add ?≈the needs of\add* the \add ≈Israelis¦62702\add*. Any stranger¦62704 who approached¦62705 had to be \add ≈executed\add*.
\v 39 Mosheh¦62714 and Aharon listed 22,000 Levite¦62711 males that were at least a month¦62727 old, listing them by their¦62721 clans¦62721 as \add ≈per Yahweh's instructions\add*.
\s1 Paying the price for the firstborn sons
\rem /s1 The Redemption of the Firstborn; The Levites Take the Place of the First-Born Sons; Redeeming the Firstborn Sons
\p
\v 40 Then Yahweh¦62735 told Mosheh¦62738, “List all the \add other\add* male¦62743 \add ≈Israeli¦62745\add* that are at least one month¦62748 old and \add ≈count them\add*.
\v 41 The Levites¦62758 are for me, Yahweh¦62761, in the place of the firstborn males from every \add ≈Israeli¦62766\add* family, and¦62755 their animals are in place of the \add ≈Israelis'\add* firstborn male animals.”
\v 42 \add ≈So¦62779\add* Mosheh¦62780 listed the firstborn¦62789 Israelis¦62790 exactly as Yahweh¦62783 had commanded¦62782 him to.
\v 43 and¦62793 the total number¦62798 of firstborn¦62796 males a month¦62802 old or more whose names¦62799 were listed came to 22,273.
\p
\v 44 Then Yahweh¦62814 spoke¦62813 to Mosheh¦62817,
\v 45 “Take the Levites instead of every¦62825 firstborn¦62827 male Israeli¦62828, and the Levites' animals instead of their¦62835 animals, and the Levites will be mine—I am Yahweh¦62841.
\v 46 To redeem the 273 firstborn¦62852 Israelis¦62854 who outnumber¦62848 the Levites¦62851,
\v 47 collect¦62856 five silver coins for each one of them. (Use the same silver coins weighing eleven grams, that the priests use in¦62861 the \add ≈sacred¦62862 tent¦62862\add*.)
\v 48 Give that \add ≈money¦62869\add* to Aharon and¦62871 his sons¦62871 as payment of the ransom¦62872 for those¦62873 excess¦62873 273 males.”
\v 49 \add ≈So¦62876\add* Mosheh¦62877 collected that ransom money¦62879 to cover the ransom of the excess¦62882 \add not covered by the number of\add* Levites¦62885.
\v 50 He¦62890 collected 1,365 silver coins from the firstborn¦62888 Israeli¦62889 males (using the standard weight of silver from the sanctuary¦62901)
\v 51 and gave¦62903 \add *it\add* to Aharon and his sons¦62910 just as Yahweh¦62914 had commanded¦62916.
\c 4
\s1 Kohat's descendants' duties
\rem /s1 The Duties of the Levite Clan of Kohath; Duties of the Kohathite Clan; The Kohathites
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦62924 told Mosheh¦62927 \add (Moses¦62927)\add* and Aharon \add (Aaron¦62930)\add*,
\v 2 “\add ≈Take¦62941 a detailed census\add* of Kohat's¦62938 male descendants by their clans¦62942 and families
\v 3 \add ≈who are from twenty-five up to fifty¦62953 years old\add* and who goes into the \add ≈sacred¦62961 tent¦62961\add* to minister.
\p
\v 4 This is what the Kohatites are responsible for concerning the \add ≈sacred¦62971 tent¦62969 including the inner room\add*:
\v 5 When¦62974 \add ≈it's time to break camp¦62978\add*, Aharon¦62975 and his sons¦62976 must¦62974 enter and take¦62979 down the curtain¦62981 that veils it, and then¦62974 use that to cover¦62983 the box \add ≈containing the agreement\add*.
\v 6 Then¦62990 they must¦62990 cover it with \add ?≈fine\add* leather, followed by a blue cloth, and¦62990 then¦62990 put its¦63002 \add carrying\add* poles¦63002 \add through the rings\add*.
\p
\v 7 They must¦63008 spread¦63008 a blue cloth over the \add ≈sacred bread table¦63006\add*, then¦63004 place the dishes¦63018, pans, bowls¦63021, and¦63004 jugs for the drink¦63024 offerings¦63024 on top of that, along with the \add ≈sacred\add* bread.
\v 8 Then¦63030 they must¦63030 spread¦63030 a scarlet cloth over all that, and cover¦63035 that again with¦63037 \add ?≈fine\add* leather, and then¦63030 put its¦63043 poles¦63043 \add through the rings\add*.
\p
\v 9 They must¦63045 spread a blue cloth over the lampstand with¦63072 its \add oil\add* lamps, its tongs¦63059 and trays¦63062, and the oil containers that¦63068 are used for it.
\v 10 Then¦63074 they must¦63074 wrap the lampstand and all its equipment in \add ?≈fine\add* leather, and place it \add all\add* on its carrying¦63089 frame¦63089.
\p
\v 11 Then¦63091 the must¦63095 spread¦63095 a blue cloth over the gold¦63094 \add incense\add* altar¦63093, and cover¦63098 that again with¦63100 \add ?≈fine\add* leather, and then¦63091 put its¦63106 poles¦63106 \add through the rings\add*.
\v 12 Then¦63108 they must¦63108 get all the \add other\add* utensils that they use in¦63118 the \add ≈sacred¦63119 tent¦63119\add*, and cover¦63125 that again with¦63118 \add ?≈fine\add* leather, and place¦63119 it \add all\add* on¦63118 its carrying¦63133 frame¦63133.
\v 13 They need to remove the ashes¦63135 from the \add bronze\add* altar¦63138 and¦63139 spread¦63139 a purple¦63142 cloth¦63142 over it,
\v 14 and put all the utensils¦63150 they use on top of it: the trays, meat forks¦63160, shovel¦63163 and basins¦63166 for the altar¦63169. Then¦63144 they must¦63144 cover¦63172 it with \add ?≈fine\add* leather, and then¦63144 put its poles¦63176 \add through the rings\add*.
\v 15 Aharon and his sons¦63181 must¦63178 finish¦63178 covering¦63182 the \add ≈sacred tent\add* and all its utensils and equipment when \add ≈they're about to move camp¦63193\add*. Then¦63178 the Kohatites can come¦63197 to carry it all without touching¦63204 the \add ≈inner room¦63185\add* so they won't¦63202 die¦63208. That's the responsibility of Kohat's¦63200 descendants—\add carrying\add* the \add ≈sacred tent\add*.
\p
\v 16 Eleazar¦63218 (son of Aharon¦63222 the priest¦63223) is in¦63241 charge¦63217 of the lamp oil and the fragrant¦63227 incense¦63226, the regular¦63229 grain¦63228 offering¦63228, the anointing¦63231 oil, and the oversight¦63232 of the \add ≈sacred¦63241 tent¦63241\add* and the inner room¦63241, including¦63226 everything that's used inside them.
\p
\v 17 Then Yahweh¦63246 told Mosheh¦63249 and Aharon,
\v 18 “Don't allow the Kohatite Levites¦63264 to \add ≈get wiped out\add* \add by mishandling the most sacred items\add*,
\v 19 \add ≈but¦63266 take these precautions on¦63273 their behalf so\add* they won't¦63271 die¦63272 when they approach the \add ≈most sacred¦63276 items\add*: Get Aharon and his sons¦63279 to go¦63280 and show \add ≈each of them personally\add* the \add ≈correct and proper way to do his duties\add*.
\v 20 \add ≈However,\add* they must¦63294 never \add go¦63294 early\add* to \add ≈set their eyes on\add* the \add ≈sacred¦63299 objects¦63299\add*, \add ≈even briefly\add*, or they'll die¦63300.”
\s1 Gershon's descendants' duties
\rem /s1 The Gershonites; Duties of the Gershonite Clan; The Duties of the Levite Clan of Gershon; The Gershonites and Merarites
\p
\v 21 Then Yahweh¦63304 told Mosheh¦63307,
\v 22 “\add ≈Take a detailed census\add* of Gershon's¦63315 male descendants¦63314 by their clans¦63321 and families
\v 23 \add ≈who are from thirty¦63324 up to fifty¦63330 years old\add* and¦63326 who goes into the \add ≈sacred¦63341 tent¦63341\add* to minister.
\p
\v 24 This is what the Gershonites are responsible for working with and¦63349 carrying¦63349:
\v 25 They must¦63351 carry¦63351 the \add inner\add* curtains from the \add ≈sacred¦63355 tent¦63355\add*, the covering, the \add ?≈fine\add* leather¦63362 covering, the entrance¦63370 curtain,
\v 26 the courtyard curtains, and the courtyard gate curtain, along with the ropes¦63394 and other equipment for using them. That will be their ministry.
\v 27 Aharon and his sons¦63413 \add ≈will direct\add* the Gershonites in¦63427 their¦63424 duties and assign¦63425 all \add the items\add* to them.
\v 28 That will be the ministry of Gershon's descendants¦63436 with¦63438 the \add ≈sacred¦63438 tent¦63438\add*, and¦63440 it will all be under the supervision of Aharon's son Itamar¦63442 the priest¦63446.
\s1 Merari's descendants' duties
\rem /s1 The Duties of the Levite Clan of Merari; Duties of the Merarite Clan; The Merarites
\p
\v 29 “\add ≈Take a detailed census\add* of Merari's¦63450 descendants¦63449 by their clans¦63451 and families,
\v 30 listing the men who are from thirty¦63459 to fifty¦63465 years old and who goes into the \add ≈sacred¦63476 tent¦63476\add* to minister.
\v 31 Their duties are carrying¦63481 the frames¦63487, crossbars, posts, and¦63479 sockets for the \add ≈sacred¦63488 tent¦63488\add*,
\v 32 the courtyard¦63494 pillars¦63493 and their bases¦63496, their pegs and ropes¦63498, and all their equipment. Every man must be assigned¦63505 by name¦63504 as to what equipment he must carry¦63510.
\v 33 That will be the ministry of Merari's¦63516 descendants¦63515 with¦63520 the \add ≈sacred¦63520 tent¦63520\add*, and it will all be under the supervision of Aharon's son Itamar¦63523 the priest¦63527.
\s1 The totals from the Levite census
\rem /s1 The Numbering of the Levite Clans; Census of the Levites; The Census of the Levites
\p
\v 34 \add ≈So¦63529\add* Mosheh¦63530 and Aharon and the community¦63533 leaders¦63532 listed the Kohatites by their clans¦63538 and families,
\v 35 \add counting\add* the men from thirty¦63543 to fifty¦63549 years old who go into the \add ≈sacred¦63556 tent¦63556\add* to minister,
\v 36 and¦63559 the total for all the clans¦63561 was 2,750.
\v 37 That was from the Kohatite clans¦63569 who ministered at¦63574 the \add ≈sacred¦63574 tent¦63574\add* and were listed by Mosheh and Aharon just as Yahweh¦63583 had instructed Mosheh.
\v 38 They counted¦63589 the Gershonites by their clans¦63592 and families,
\v 39 \add counting\add* the men from thirty¦63597 to fifty¦63603 years old who go into the \add ≈sacred¦63610 tent¦63610\add* to minister,
\v 40 and¦63613 the total for all the clans¦63615 was 2,630.
\v 41 That was from the Gershonite clans¦63625 who ministered at¦63631 the \add ≈sacred¦63631 tent¦63631\add* and were listed by Mosheh and Aharon just as Yahweh¦63640 had instructed Mosheh.
\v 42 They counted¦63642 the Merarites by their clans and¦63642 families,
\v 43 \add counting\add* the men from thirty¦63651 to fifty¦63657 years old who go into the \add ≈sacred¦63664 tent¦63664\add* to minister,
\v 44 and¦63672 the total for all the clans¦63669 was 3,200.
\v 45 That was from the Merarite clans¦63676 who ministered at¦63687 the \add ≈sacred tent\add* and were listed by Mosheh and Aharon just as Yahweh¦63686 had instructed Mosheh.
\v 46 \add ≈So\add* Mosheh¦63696, Aharon, and the Israeli¦63698 leaders¦63698 counted \add all\add* the Levites¦63702 by their clans¦63703 and families,
\v 47 \add counting\add* the men from thirty¦63708 to fifty¦63714 years old who go into the \add ≈sacred¦63724 tent¦63724\add* to minister and also help with¦63724 carrying¦63723 it,
\v 48 and¦63727 the total came to 8,580.
\v 49 Those were the ones counted¦63752 by Mosheh \add ≈following Yahweh's instructions¦63755\add*. Each man's name was listed by Mosheh, along with¦63741 his duties and what was his responsibility to carry¦63751.
\c 5
\s1 Handling ceremonial ‘uncleanness’
\rem /s1 The Purity of the Camp; Purity in Israel's Camp; Unclean People; Unclean Persons
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦63763 told Mosheh¦63766 \add (Moses¦63766)\add*,
\v 2 “Order¦63773 the \add ≈Israelis¦63772\add* that anyone with a skin disease¦63780 or a discharge¦63783, and anyone who's ‘unclean¦63785’ because¦63786 they¦63774 touched a corpse¦63786, must be sent outside the camp¦63777.
\v 3 Whether they're male or female¦63791, they must¦63792 be sent outside¦63795 the camp so that¦63803 the whole camp doesn't become ‘unclean¦63799’ \add because\add* I'm living¦63805 there \add right\add* amongst¦63806 them.”
\v 4 \add ≈So¦63808 the Israelis¦63811\add* did what Yahweh¦63821 told Mosheh¦63824, and¦63808 sent those people outside¦63817 the camp¦63818.
\s1 Reparations for crimes
\rem /s1 Confession and Restitution; Restitution for Wrongs; Repayment for Wrongs Done
\p
\v 5 Then Yahweh¦63832 told Mosheh¦63835,
\v 6 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦63841\add* that when any man or a woman¦63846 \add ≈disobeys God by doing any of the things that humans¦63852 do\add* when they're unfaithful¦63853 towards Yahweh¦63855, then that person is guilty¦63856
\v 7 and¦63860 they must confess¦63860 their¦63863 \add ≈disobedience\add*. Then¦63860 that¦63864 person must make full reparation to whoever they wronged¦63869, along with¦63870 an extra twenty percent \add of the cost\add*.
\v 8 \add ≈However,\add* if reparation to \add ≈the victim isn't¦63881 possible\add* \add for some reason\add*, then¦63879 it must¦63895 be paid to Yahweh¦63889 via a priest¦63890, in addition to the ram \add that will be offered\add* for that person's¦63882 atonement¦63893.
\v 9 Any¦63908 sacred¦63905 contributions¦63902 by the \add ≈Israelis¦63906\add* that¦63909 are presented to a priest¦63912 will belong¦63914 to him.
\v 10 Each person's sacred¦63919 contributions will be their own, \add but¦63916\add* anything given to a priest¦63926 will belong to him¦63919.”
\s1 Testing for an unfaithful wife
\rem /s1 Concerning an Unfaithful Wife; Cases of Wives with Suspicious Husbands; Protecting Marital Faithfulness; The Test for an Unfaithful Wife
\p
\v 11 Then Yahweh¦63932 told Mosheh¦63935,
\v 12 “Tell¦63942 the \add ≈Israelis¦63941\add* that if any man's wife \add ≈has an affair\add* and is unfaithful¦63951 towards him,
\v 13 when another man secretly has sex with¦63969 her, then¦63955 she becomes ‘unclean¦63966’, even though there's¦63968 no witness¦63967 against her and¦63955 she wasn't caught¦63972.
\v 14 \add ≈If the husband becomes suspicious, whether or not she's actually\add* become ‘unclean’,
\v 15 then¦64000 \add *he\add* should take \add *her\add* to a priest¦64007. He must also bring¦64034 an offering on her behalf: two litres of barley¦64016 flour¦64015. It must not have any oil or \add ≈spices mixed into it\add* because it's a grain offering for suspicion—\add ≈for determining if unfaithfulness has occurred\add*.
\p
\v 16 Then¦64037 the priest¦64039 must¦64037 \add ≈lead her forward\add* and¦64037 stand¦64040 her in front¦64041 of Yahweh¦64042.
\v 17 He must¦64044 \add ≈fill\add* a pottery jar with¦64048 sacred¦64047 water, and¦64044 then¦64044 mix some dust from the floor¦64056 of \add Yahweh's\add* residence into the water.
\v 18 Then¦64065 the priest must stand¦64065 the woman \add ≈in¦64087 front¦64070\add* of Yahweh¦64071 and¦64065 \add ≈let her hair down\add*, then¦64065 he must place the suspicion grain offering on¦64087 her palm. (It's a grain offering for jealousy¦64085.) The priest must be \add ≈holding\add* the water¦64090 of bitterness¦64091 that¦64092 brings¦64092 a curse¦64092
\v 19 and tell the woman¦64100 to make this oath: “If no \add other\add* man \add ≈slept\add* with you, and if you didn't¦64103 \add ≈dirty yourself while you're married\add*, then¦64094 be free from this water¦64115 of bitterness¦64116 that¦64117 brings¦64117 a curse¦64117.
\v 20 \add ≈But¦64120\add* if you \add ≈have cheated on\add* your husband and become ‘unclean¦64126’ and slept with some other¦64133 guy, \add there'll be consequences\add*.
\v 21 Then¦64136 the priest will make the woman¦64140 take that curse as an oath, and \add *he'll\add* tell \add *her\add*, “Yahweh will \add ≈make your experience\add* a curse and your people¦64152 \add ≈will see the results of the\add* oath, when Yahweh gives \add ≈disease to your genitals\add* and makes¦64153 your belly¦64161 swell.
\v 22 This water¦64165 will \add ≈invoke\add* the curse¦64166 to make your belly¦64170 swell¦64169 and¦64164 your \add ≈genitals shrivel\add*.” Then¦64164 the woman¦64174 must¦64164 say¦64173, “Indeed, let it be so.”
\p
\v 23 Then¦64179 the priest¦64184 must¦64179 write¦64179 those curses¦64182 on¦64185 a scroll¦64185, then¦64179 wipe \add the ink\add* into the water¦64189 of bitterness¦64190.
\v 24 He must¦64201 make the woman¦64195 drink that water¦64192 of bitterness¦64199 that brings¦64200 the curse¦64200, and¦64201 \add *it\add* will enter¦64201 into her¦64202.
\v 25 Then¦64207 he'll take the grain offering of suspicion from her hand, and hold it up \add ≈in front¦64218\add* of Yahweh¦64219, and then¦64207 take it to the altar¦64224.
\v 26 \add *He'll\add* take¦64226 some of the grain¦64230 as a memorial¦64233 portion and¦64226 burn¦64234 it on the altar¦64235. Then¦64226 he'll make the woman¦64240 drink¦64237 the water¦64243.
\v 27 \add ≈After she's drunk it\add*, if she was ‘unclean¦64252’ and unfaithful¦64253 to her husband¦64255, the water will carry that¦64259 curse into her, and her belly¦64262 will swell¦64261 and her \add ≈genitals will get diseased\add*, and the woman¦64266 will become¦64265 a curse among her people¦64269.
\v 28 \add ≈However,\add* if she hadn't defiled herself¦64274 and is pure, then¦64271 she'll be free and \add be able to\add* \add ≈have children\add*.
\p
\v 29 That's the rule about jealousy¦64284 when a wife¦64287 \add ≈cheats on\add* her husband¦64289 and¦64290 defiles¦64290 herself¦64290,
\v 30 or when a \add ≈husband\add* \add ≈becomes jealous¦64298 and suspicious\add* and he stands¦64303 \add ≈his wife\add* \add ≈in front¦64307\add* of Yahweh¦64308, and the priest¦64311 applies this ruling to her.
\v 31 Then¦64318 \add ≈the husband\add* will be \add ≈innocent\add*, and¦64321 that women will \add ≈bear the consequences\add* of her¦64326 wrongdoing.
\c 6
\s1 Instructions for the Nazirite vow
\rem /s1 The Nazirites; The Nazirite; Nazirite Laws; Rules for Nazirites
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦64330 told Mosheh¦64333,
\v 2 “Tell¦64340 the \add ≈Israelis¦64339\add* that when any man or woman¦64346 wants to make a solemn vow to separate¦64352 themself to Yahweh¦64353 as a Nazirite¦64351,
\v 3 they must¦64357 keep away from wine and strong drink, and \add even\add* vinegar made from wine or strong drink, plus¦64356 they mustn't drink grape juice¦64366 or eat either grapes or raisins.\x + \xo 6:3: \xt Luk 1:15.\x*
\v 4 For the entire¦64379 time¦64377 of their separation¦64378, they mustn't eat¦64389 anything coming from a grapevine¦64382, \add ≈not even\add* the seeds¦64384 or the skins.
\p
\v 5 “For the entire time¦64406 of their vow to Yahweh¦64410 as a Nazirite¦64409, they mustn't cut their hair—they must¦64399 sacred¦64411 and grow their hair long.
\p
\v 6 “For¦64421 the entire time¦64420 of their separation¦64421 to Yahweh¦64422, they mustn't approach any dead¦64426 body,
\v 7 even if it's their father¦64430 or mother¦64431, or brother¦64432 or sister¦64433. They mustn't defile themselves with¦64438 death, because their consecration¦64440 to their god¦64441 is on¦64438 their head¦64444.
\v 8 They must remain holy to Yahweh¦64451 for the whole time¦64447.
\p
\v 9 “\add ≈However,\add* if someone right next to them suddenly¦64459 died, that would defile¦64460 their consecrated¦64462 head, and¦64453 after the \add regular\add* seven¦64468 days of purification¦64466, they would have to shave their head.
\v 10 Then¦64471 on¦64471 the eighth¦64472 day¦64471, they'd have to take two doves or young¦64478 pigeons to the priest¦64482 at¦64471 the entrance¦64485 of the \add ≈sacred¦64486 tent¦64486\add*,
\v 11 and \add *he\add* would take one for a sin¦64492 offering and the other¦64493 for a burnt¦64494 offering—making atonement¦64495 for their transgression with the corpse¦64501. Then¦64489 they would consecrate¦64502 their head¦64505 again that day¦64506
\v 12 and¦64509 \add ≈restart\add* their days of separation, as well as bringing¦64515 a one-year old male lamb as a guilt¦64520 offering¦64520. (Their¦64510 initial days of separation \add ≈won't count\add* because they were made ‘unclean¦64525’.)
\p
\v 13 “Now these are the instructions for the Nazirites¦64530: Once their days¦64533 of separation¦64534 are fulfilled, \add someone¦64535\add* must¦64535 take them to the entrance¦64539 of the \add ≈sacred¦64540 tent¦64540\add*
\v 14 and they will present¦64543 their offerings¦64566 to Yahweh¦64547—an unblemished, one-year old, male lamb as a burnt¦64554 offering, and an unblemished, one-year old, female lamb as a sin¦64561 offering, plus¦64555 an unblemished ram as a peace¦64566/fellowship¦64566 offering,
\v 15 \add ≈along with\add* a basket¦64568 of flat breads, flour¦64570 mixed¦64572 with oil, and wafers¦64574 spread with \add olive\add* oil, and their grain¦64578 and drink¦64579 offerings¦64578.
\v 16 The priest¦64582 must¦64581 present¦64581 all that to Yahweh¦64584, and \add ≈handle\add* their sin¦64588 offering and burnt¦64591 offering.
\v 17 The ram and the basket¦64601 of flat breads¦64602 will be offered as a peace¦64598 offering to Yahweh¦64599, and the priest¦64604 will offer their grain and wine offerings¦64598.
\v 18 Then¦64612 the Nazirite¦64613 must shave¦64612 their head of separation at the opening to the \add ≈sacred¦64615 tent\add*, and¦64612 taking the hair¦64624, must put it on the fire¦64630 under¦64633 their peace¦64635 offering¦64635 sacrifice¦64634.
\p
\v 19 “The priest¦64638 will then¦64637 take the boiled¦64642 shoulder¦64641 from the ram, and one flat bread roll and one wafer¦64652 from the basket¦64651, and place them on the palms¦64658 of that Nazirite¦64659 with their consecrated¦64664 head that's been shaved¦64661.
\v 20 Then the priest will raise them as a raised offering to Yahweh¦64672. Those raised breads and the shoulder \add ≈are now sacred¦64673 and belong to\add* the priest. Then the Nazirite¦64684 can drink¦64683 some wine.
\p
\v 21 Those are the instructions for the Nazirite¦64689 who makes a solemn oath to Yahweh¦64693 for their separation¦64696, \add ≈plus what they're able to give\add*. \add ≈They must¦64691 do exactly what they promised\add* as per these instructions.”
\s1 The priests' prayer for blessing
\rem /s1 The Priestly Benediction; The Priestly Blessing
\p
\v 22 Then Yahweh¦64714 told Mosheh¦64717 \add (Moses¦64717)\add*,
\v 23 “Tell Aharon \add (Aaron¦64723)\add* and his sons¦64726 that when the bless¦64729 the \add ≈Israelis¦64732\add*, this is what they must¦64729 say:
\q1
\v 24 May Yahweh¦64739 bless¦64738 you and protect you.
\q1
\v 25 May \add ≈Yahweh¦64744 give you prosperity and show grace toward\add* you.
\q1
\v 26 May¦64752 \add *he\add* \add ≈watch over\add* you and give¦64756 you peace¦64758.
\p
\v 27 “\add ≈In that way,\add* they'll put my name¦64764 on the \add ≈Israelis¦64767\add*, and I will bless¦64770 them.”
\c 7
\s1 The leaders' offerings at the altar dedication
\rem /s1 Offerings of the Leaders; The Offerings of the Leaders; Offerings of Dedication; Offerings at the Dedication of the Tabernacle
\p
\v 1 When Mosheh¦64776 \add (Moses¦64776)\add* had finished¦64775 setting¦64777 up the \add ≈sacred¦64780 tent¦64780\add*, he anointed it \add with oil\add* and consecrated it and all its furniture¦64789, as well as the altar¦64792 and all its equipment.
\v 2 Then¦64802 Yisrael's leaders presented \add <gifts\add*. They were the leaders of the tribes¦64810 who ruled over those who'd been listed \add for duties\add*.
\v 3 They brought¦64817 their¦64820 gifts to Yahweh's \add ≈presence¦64837\add* in six carts¦64825 \add pulled by\add* twelve bulls. Each cart was from two leaders¦64834, and¦64817 each of the bulls was from one leader.
\v 4 Then¦64842 Yahweh¦64844 told Mosheh¦64847:
\v 5 “\add ≈Accept their gifts because they'll be useful for the running of the sacred¦64857 tent¦64857\add*. \add ≈Distribute them appropriately to the Levites¦64863, depending on each man's duties\add*.”
\v 6 \add ≈So¦64868\add* Mosheh¦64869 took¦64868 the carts¦64872 and the cattle and distributed them to the Levites¦64880,
\v 7 giving two¦64884 carts¦64885 and¦64886 four¦64887 bulls¦64888 to the Gershonites¦64891 to help them with their¦64893 assigned duties.
\v 8 Then¦64895 he gave¦64902 four¦64897 carts¦64898 and¦64895 eight¦64900 bulls¦64901 to the Merarites to help them with¦64907 their¦64906 assigned duties under the supervision of the priest¦64912 (Aharon's son) Itamar¦64908.
\v 9 \add ≈However,\add* the Kohaties weren't given any because they¦64924 were responsible for carrying¦64924 the very holy objects, and¦64914 those had to be carried¦64924 on¦64923 their shoulders¦64923.
\p
\v 10 The day¦64931 that the altar was dedicated¦64929 and anointed¦64932, the leaders brought their¦64938 gifts and presented them at the altar,
\v 11 and¦64942 Yahweh¦64943 told Mosheh¦64946, “\add ≈Each day\add* \add for the next twelve days\add*, one leader must¦64953 present his offering¦64956 for the altar¦64958 dedication¦64957.”
\p
\v 12-83 \add ≈These were the leaders who presented their offerings:\add*
\li1 On the first¦64964 day, Amminadav's son Nahshon¦64968 \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Yehudah¦64973,
\li1 on the second day, Zuar's son Netanel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Yissakar,
\li1 on the third day, Helon's son Eliav \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Zevulun,
\li1 on the fourth day, Shedeyur's son Elitsur \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Reuven,
\li1 on the fifth day, Tsurishaddai's son Shelumiel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Shimeon,
\li1 on the sixth day, Deuel's son Elyasaf \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Gad,
\li1 on the seventh day, Ammihud's son Elishama \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Efrayim,
\li1 on the eighth day, Pedahzur's son Gamaliel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Menashsheh,
\li1 on the ninth day, Gideoni's son Avidan \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Benyamin,
\li1 on the tenth day, Ammishaddai's son Ahiezer \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Dan,
\li1 on the eleventh day, Okran's son Pagiel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Asher,
\li1 and on the twelfth day, Enam's son Ahira \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Naftali.
\p \add ≈Each of the leaders presented the following offerings:\add*
\li1 a silver dish (1.5 kg—\add ≈all weights\add* by the standard temple measurement) and a silver bowl (800g)—both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering,
\li1 a small gold dish (110g) filled with incense,
\li1 a young bull, a ram and a one-year-old male lamb for a burnt offering,
\li1 a male goat for a sin offering,
\li1 two cows, five rams, five male goats, and five one-year-old rams for the peace offering.
\p
\v 84 That was the dedication¦65962 of the altar¦65963 in the day¦65964 it was anointed¦65965, when Yisrael's leaders¦65968 \add presented\add* twelve silver dishes¦65970, twelve silver bowls¦65974, and twelve gold¦65980 pans.
\v 85 Each silver dish weighed 1.5kg (\add ≈all weights\add* by the standard temple measurement) and the silver bowls were 800g. The total¦65992 weight of the silver was around 27 kg.
\v 86 The gold pans that had been filled with¦66012 incense¦66008 weighed 110g and their total¦66014 weight came to 1.3kg.
\v 87 For the burnt¦66024 offerings there was: twelve bulls¦66027, twelve rams, and twelve male one-year-old lambs¦66032 along with their¦66038 grain¦66038 offerings. There were twelve male goats for a sin offering.
\v 88 For the peace¦66049 offering, there were 24 bulls¦66052, 60 rams, 60 male goats¦66055, 60 male one-year-old lambs¦66057. All of those were part of the dedication¦66063 offerings¦66049 for the altar¦66064 after¦66065 it was anointed¦66066.
\v 89 Then¦66069 Mosheh¦66070 entered the \add ≈sacred tent¦66073\add* to speak¦66075 with¦66069 \add @Yahweh\add*. He heard the voice¦66080 speaking¦66081 to him from between¦66090 the two¦66091 images of winged-creatures that¦66085 were on¦66069 the platform above the sacred box. That's how \add @Yahweh\add* spoke¦66093 to him.
\c 8
\s1 Lighting the seven lamps
\rem /s1 The Seven Lamps; Setting Up the Lamps; Placing the Lamps; Preparing the Lamps
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦66098 told Mosheh¦66101 \add (Moses¦66101)\add*,\x + \xo 8:1-4: \xt Exo 25:31-40; 37:17-24.\x*
\v 2 “Tell Aharon \add (Aaron¦66107)\add* that when he \add ≈places\add* the seven¦66120 lamps \add on¦66110\add* the lampstand, \add ≈they must¦66108 light¦66119 up the area in¦66110 front¦66116 of it\add*.”
\v 3 \add ≈So¦66123\add* Aharon did it just as Yahweh¦66135 had instructed¦66134, setting up the lamps on the lampstand to face¦66129 forwards.
\v 4 The lampstand from the base to its blossoms¦66150 had been made by hammering \add a single sheet\add* of gold¦66144, just as Yahweh¦66156 had shown¦66155 Mosheh¦66159.
\s1 The dedication of Levites
\rem /s1 Consecration and Service of the Levites; The Setting Apart of the Levites; The Purification and Dedication of the Levites; The Levites Dedicated
\p
\v 5 Then Yahweh¦66168 told Mosheh¦66171,
\v 6 “\add ≈Out¦66180 of all the Israelis¦66179\add*, take the Levites¦66177 and¦66181 purify¦66181 them.
\v 7 This is how to make them pure: sprinkle the sin¦66192 offering¦66192 water¦66191 on them, then¦66184 they must¦66186 shave¦66193 their \add ≈entire¦66197 bodies\add* and wash themselves¦66202 and their clothes¦66201.
\v 8 They must¦66204 take a \add ≈young\add* bull along with its grain¦66209 offering of flour¦66210 mixed¦66211 with oil, plus¦66209 a \add ≈second¦66215 young\add* bull for a sin offering.
\v 9 You¦66236 must¦66222 have the Levites¦66225 stand at the front¦66226 of the \add ≈sacred¦66227 tent¦66227\add* and¦66229 summon the rest of the \add ≈Israelis¦66235\add* \add there too\add*.
\v 10 Then¦66238 you¦66238 must present the Levites¦66241 \add ≈in front¦66242 of\add* Yahweh¦66243 and¦66244 the \add ≈Israeli¦66247 men\add* must place their¦66250 hands¦66250 on them.
\v 11 \add ≈Out of all the Israelis¦66264,\add* Aharon must¦66255 present¦66255 the Levites¦66259 as a raised offering to Yahweh \add ≈so they¦66266 can serve¦66267 Yahweh\add* \add with their assigned duties\add*.
\v 12 Then¦66273 the Levites must place their¦66277 hands¦66277 on the bulls' heads, and one must be given as a sin¦66285 offering and the other as a burnt¦66289 offering to Yahweh, to make the Levites \add ≈innocent in Yahweh's eyes\add*.
\p
\v 13 “The Levites¦66299 must¦66296 stand¦66296 in front¦66300 of Aharon and¦66296 his sons¦66303, then¦66296 they can be offered as a raised offering to Yahweh¦66307.
\v 14 That's how \add *they'll\add* be \add ≈distinguished from the other Israelis¦66314\add*, and¦66316 then¦66309 \add *they'll\add* belong to me.
\v 15 Then¦66320 the Levites¦66324 will go¦66323 to serve¦66325 at the \add ≈sacred¦66328 tent¦66328\add* after¦66320 you've purified¦66330 them and¦66320 presented¦66332 them as a raised offering,
\v 16 because they're given to me by all the Israeli¦66342 people¦66342—I've¦66353 taken¦66353 them for myself in place¦66344 of their firstborn male sons¦66351,
\v 17 because every firstborn Israeli¦66362 male person and animal belongs to me. I set them apart¦66373 for myself when I killed every \add other\add* firstborn in¦66362 Egypt¦66372,
\v 18 \add ≈so\add* I've¦66386 \add now\add* taken¦66377 the Levites¦66380 instead of the firstborn¦66384 Israeli¦66385 sons¦66385.
\v 19 Then¦66388 I've¦66388 given the Levites¦66391 out of all the Israelis, to Aharon and his sons¦66395 to serve¦66399 \add ≈the whole country\add* by serving¦66402 in the \add ≈sacred tent\add* and making \add ≈the Israelis innocent in Yahweh's eyes\add*. That way, a plague¦66417 won't¦66413 strike the Israelis when they approach the \add ≈sacred tent\add*.”
\p
\v 20 \add ≈So¦66426\add* Mosheh and Aharon and all the \add ≈Israelis¦66432\add* did to the Levites¦66435 \add just\add* what Yahweh¦66440 had instructed¦66439 Mosheh.
\v 21 The Levites¦66453 purified¦66452 themselves¦66452 and washed¦66454 their¦66455 clothes¦66455, and Aharon offered them to Yahweh as a raised offering, and Aharon offered a sacrifice to \add ≈make them innocent in Yahweh's eyes\add*.
\v 22 After that, the Levites went¦66470 to do their¦66475 \add assigned\add* duties at¦66476 the \add ≈sacred¦66476 tent¦66476\add* \add ≈working under\add* Aharon and¦66480 his sons¦66481. \add ≈The Israelis did exactly what Yahweh¦66484 told¦66483 Mosheh¦66487 to do with¦66476\add* the Levites.
\p
\v 23 Then Yahweh¦66497 told Mosheh¦66500,
\v 24 “These are the instructions for the Levites¦66505: from the age of twenty-five, Levite¦66505 men will begin serving¦66513 the work¦66513 in¦66514 the \add ≈sacred¦66515 tent¦66515\add*
\v 25 until the age of fifty¦66519 when they must¦66521 retire from that work¦66522.
\v 26 They may then¦66528 assist¦66528 their¦66542 fellow Levites¦66541 with guard¦66534 duties¦66542, but¦66528 they can no longer work¦66536 \add directly\add* with the \add ≈sacred¦66532 tent¦66532\add*.”
\c 9
\s1 The ‘pass-over’ celebration
\rem /s1 The Passover; The Passover at Sinai; The Second Passover
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦66546 spoke¦66545 to Mosheh¦66549 \add (Moses¦66549)\add* in the Sinai¦66552 wilderness¦66550, in the first¦66559 month¦66558 of the second¦66554 year¦66553 \add ≈after¦66555 they'd left\add* Egypt¦66557,
\v 2 “The \add ≈Israelis¦66565\add* must observe¦66562 ‘pass-over¦66568’ at¦66569 the appointed¦66569 time¦66569.
\v 3 You all must¦66580 \add ≈celebrate\add* it on¦66575 the evening¦66578 of the 14th of this month¦66575, \add ≈following all the instructions that you've all been given previously\add*.”
\v 4 \add ≈So¦66592\add* Mosheh¦66593 \add ≈ordered\add* the \add ≈Israelis¦66596\add* to \add ≈prepare\add* the ‘pass-over¦66599’,
\v 5 and¦66601 they \add ≈celebrated\add* it in¦66605 the Sinai¦66613 wilderness¦66612 \add ≈starting\add* on¦66605 the evening¦66611 of the 14th of that first¦66605 month¦66609, \add ≈following all the instructions¦66616 that Yahweh¦66617 had given\add* Mosheh¦66620.
\p
\v 6 \add ≈However,\add* there were some men who were ‘unclean¦66630’ (because they'd touched a dead body) and hence they weren't able to \add ≈celebrate\add* the ‘pass-over¦66638’ that day, \add ≈so\add* they \add ≈approached\add* Mosheh¦66643 and Aharon
\v 7 and¦66649 \add ≈asked\add* them, “We¦66668 were ‘unclean¦66654’ because we'd touched a dead body, \add but¦66649\add* \add ≈how come we're excluded\add* from presenting an offering¦66663 to Yahweh¦66664 \add ≈along with¦66665 the other Israelis¦66667\add*?”
\p
\v 8 “\add ≈Wait here\add*,” Mosheh¦66672 \add ≈answered\add*, “and¦66670 I'll \add ask\add* Yahweh¦66678 \add ≈what he¦66677 wants you all to do\add*.”
\p
\v 9 Then Yahweh¦66683 told Mosheh¦66686,
\v 10 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦66692 that\add* for this and future generations¦66710, if a person is ‘unclean¦66701’ or \add ≈far from home\add*, then they can \add still\add* \add ≈observe¦66711\add* Yahweh's ‘pass-over¦66712’.
\v 11 They can \add ≈start\add* it on¦66717 the evening¦66721 of the 14th of the \em second¦66716\em* month¦66715, and eat¦66728 it \add as usual\add* with¦66717 flat bread¦66726 and bitter¦66727 herbs¦66727.
\v 12 They must not break¦66739 \add ≈any of the lambs bones\add*, must not leave¦66732 any of it until¦66734 the morning¦66736, and must observe¦66746 it \add ≈following all the normal instructions\add*.\x + \xo 9:12: \xt Exo 12:46; Yhn 19:36.\x*
\v 13 \add ≈However¦66768,\add* any person¦66749 who isn't¦66755 ‘unclean’ or far away, but¦66749 yet who didn't¦66755 celebrate the ‘pass-over¦66760’ \add ≈that first month\add*, must¦66761 be \add ≈driven out of the community\add* and¦66749 will have to bear their \add own\add* sin¦66772.
\p
\v 14 If¦66784 an \add ≈outsider is living among¦66780 you\add* and¦66777 \add ≈celebrates\add* the ‘pass-over’, they must¦66779 also do it according to \add ≈all the same instructions\add*—\add ≈there's only one way to do it whether it's\add* you all, or a foreigner, or a native¦66795 of the land.
\rem /s1 The journey from Sinai to Edom; The Cloud Above the Tabernacle; The Fiery Cloud; The Cloud and the Fire
\rem /r (Exodus 40.34-38)
\p
\v 15 \add ≈When the sacred tent was dedicated\add*, the cloud¦66805 covered¦66804 the \add ≈inner room of the tent\add*, and \add ≈every evening¦66811 it would look like fire¦66818 above\add* the residence, until¦66819 morning¦66821 \add came\add*.
\v 16 \add ≈It remained like that\add* continually¦66825—the cloud¦66826 would cover¦66827 it \add during the day\add*, and then at night¦66831, it \add ≈would appear¦66828 like\add* fire¦66830.
\v 17 \add ≈Whenever\add* the cloud \add ≈would be lifted up\add* from the tent¦66837, \add ≈then¦66833 the Israelis\add* would \add ≈leave that place¦66844\add*. \add Then¦66833\add* wherever the cloud settled¦66846 down, \add ≈that's where the Israelis would set up camp\add*,
\v 18 \add so in that way,\add* the \add ≈Israelis¦66861 would leave a place whenever Yahweh¦66858 told them, and would set up camp whenever he told them\add*. As¦66865 long as the cloud¦66872 stayed above the residence, they would \add stay\add* camped \add in that place\add*.
\v 19 Whenever the cloud¦66879 remained above the residence for a \add ≈long¦66878 time¦66883\add*, then¦66878 the \add ≈Israelis¦66886\add* would \add ≈follow\add* Yahweh's \add ≈guidance\add* and¦66878 wouldn't \add ≈pack up camp\add*.
\v 20 Sometimes¦66913 the cloud¦66899 would only remain above the residence for a few days¦66900, in which case they'd \add ≈leave where they'd just camped, and¦66910 move on as Yahweh¦66908 commanded\add*.
\v 21 If the cloud was lifted up the next morning, then they'd \add ≈move on\add*—\add in¦66929 fact\add* whether day¦66932 or night¦66933 if the cloud was lifted up, then they would \add ≈move on\add*.
\v 22 Whether it was two days or a month¦66943 or \add ≈a year\add* that the cloud¦66948 stayed¦66952 above the residence, then the \add ≈Israeli¦66957\add* camp would remain in¦66947 that place, until \add eventually\add* \add ≈moving on¦66947\add* when it was lifted¦66960 up \add again\add*.
\v 23 \add In that way,\add* \add ≈when Yahweh ordered them to camp, they would, and when order to move on¦66982, they'd do that\add*—thus they \add ≈obeyed\add* Yahweh's \add ≈instructions to\add* Mosheh¦66984.
\c 10
\s1 The silver trumpets
\rem /s1 The Silver Trumpets
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦66988 told Mosheh¦66991 \add (Moses¦66991)\add*,
\v 2 “Make two¦66996 hammered¦66999 silver¦66998 trumpets¦66997 for yourself to use for \add ≈assembling the community¦67005\add* and for \add signalling when it's time\add* to leave the camp.
\v 3 \add ≈When¦67011 both are sounded, the whole community¦67017 is to assemble¦67013 in¦67012 front of\add* you¦67014 at¦67012 the entrance¦67020 to the \add ≈sacred¦67021 tent¦67021\add*.
\v 4 \add ≈If¦67033 just one is sounded,\add* then¦67024 it's \add only\add* the leaders¦67030 and¦67028 heads¦67031 of clans who must¦67027 assemble¦67028.
\v 5 A \add ≈single blast¦67035\add* means that¦67039 the camps¦67038 on the eastern¦67040 side should \add start\add* moving out.
\v 6 A \add ≈double blast\add* means that¦67047 the camps¦67046 on the southern¦67048 side should \add start\add* moving out. \add ≈So¦67042 the blasts will signal them to get going\add*.
\v 7 (To assemble¦67056 the community \add as above\add*, \add ≈use long blows, not short blasts¦67057\add*.)
\v 8 The priests¦67063 (Aharon's descendants) must¦67064 be the ones to blow the trumpets¦67065. That is a \add ≈permanent\add* regulation¦67068.
\p
\v 9 When¦67072 you \add ≈need to defend yourselves against an attacker¦67080\add*, then¦67072 you must¦67074 sound¦67082 an alarm¦67082 with¦67076 the trumpets¦67083, and you'll all be \add ≈noticed\add* by Yahweh¦67087, and you'll be saved¦67089 from your¦67076 enemies¦67090.
\p
\v 10 On festival days and at times of celebrations and at the beginning¦67095 of each new month¦67096, then¦67092 the trumpets¦67098 will be blown as the burnt¦67100 offerings and peace¦67103 offerings are made as a memorial¦67106 for you all towards your god. I am your god, Yahweh¦67110.
\s1 The Israelis leave Sinai
\rem /s1 The Israelites Leave Sinai; Departure from Sinai; The Israelites Break Camp
\p
\v 11 Then on¦67115 the 20th of the second month in¦67115 that second year¦67115 \add (after leaving Egypt)\add*, the cloud¦67122 was lifted up from above the \add ≈sacred¦67124 tent¦67124\add*
\v 12 and¦67127 the \add ≈Israelis¦67130\add* \add ≈started moving out from the Sinai¦67133 wilderness as per the pre-arranged order\add*. The cloud¦67135 moved to the Paran¦67137 wilderness.
\v 13 That was the first¦67140 time that they¦67139 had moved \add ≈as a result of Yahweh¦67144 signalling Mosheh¦67147\add* \add by means of the cloud\add*.
\p
\v 14 Yehudah¦67154 tribe¦67152 with¦67155 their¦67156 banner \add ≈was the first¦67155 to leave under the leadership of\add* Amminadav's¦67163 son Nahshon¦67160.
\v 15 Tsuar's¦67174 son Netanel¦67171 led the company from Yissakar¦67170 tribe¦67168,
\v 16 and¦67176 Helon's¦67185 son Eliav led the company from Zevulun tribe¦67179.
\p
\v 17 Then¦67187 the \add ≈sacred tent\add* was disassembled, and the men of Gershon¦67192 and Merari¦67194 set off, carrying¦67195 the tent.
\p
\v 18 Reuven tribe with their¦67203 banner \add ≈was next to leave under the leadership of\add* Shedeyur's son Elitsur.
\v 19 Tsurishaddai's son Shelumiel¦67218 led the company from Shimeon tribe¦67215.
\v 20 Deuel's¦67234 son Elyasaf¦67231 led the company from Gad¦67230 tribe¦67227.
\p
\v 21 Then¦67236 the \add ≈sacred utensils\add* were carried¦67238 out by the Kohatite¦67237 \add men\add*, who \add ≈then¦67236 helped set up the sacred tent¦67243 when they arrived¦67246\add*.
\p
\v 22 Efrayim tribe¦67252 with their¦67255 banner \add ≈was next to leave under the leadership of\add* Ammihud's¦67262 son Elishama.
\v 23 Pedahtsur's son Gamaliel¦67270 led the company from Menashsheh tribe¦67267.
\v 24 Gideoni's son Avidan led the company from Benyamin¦67282 tribe¦67280.
\p
\v 25 Dan¦67294 tribe with their¦67299 banner \add ≈was last to leave as the rear guard under the leadership of\add* Ammishaddai's¦67306 son Ahiezer¦67303.
\v 26 Okran's¦67318 son Pagiel¦67315 led the company from Asher¦67314 tribe¦67312.
\v 27 Eynan's¦67329 son Ahira¦67326 led the company from Naftali¦67325 tribe¦67323.
\v 28 That¦67335 was \add ≈the order of the departures of the companies of the Israeli¦67333 tribes when they¦67337\add* set off.
\p
\v 29 Then Mosheh told Hovav (son of the Midianite Reuel¦67345 who was Mosheh's father-in-law), “We're heading towards the place¦67354 that¦67355 Yahweh said he'd give¦67359 us. Come \add ≈and join us, and we'll look after you, because Yahweh has promised to look after\add* Yisrael¦67373.”
\p
\v 30 “\add Thank you but¦67375\add* \add ≈no\add*,” Hovav \add ≈replied\add*, “I'll¦67378 \add ≈return\add* to my land and¦67375 to my relatives¦67387.”
\p
\v 31 “Please don't¦67391 leave¦67394 us,” Mosheh \add ≈insisted\add*, “because you're \add the one who\add* knows about camping in¦67403 the wilderness¦67403, and¦67390 you \add ≈could be our guide\add*.
\v 32 When¦67408 you come with us, Yahweh¦67419 \add ≈will be blessing us so we'll also bless\add* you.”
\rem /s1 The People Set Out
\p
\v 33 Then¦67424 they \add ≈left¦67424\add* Yahweh's mountain \add ≈and¦67424 travelled for\add* three days, with the box \add ≈containing\add* Yahweh's agreement \add ≈being carried at the front¦67435\add* to find a resting¦67441 place¦67441 for them,
\v 34 and¦67443 Yahweh's¦67444 cloud¦67443 was over them \add each\add* day¦67446 as they set out from their¦67447 stop.
\p
\v 35 \add ≈As the box started moving\add*, Mosheh¦67459 would say, “Yahweh¦67462, take action and then your enemies¦67464 will scatter¦67463, and the ones hating you will flee away from your \add ≈presence¦67467\add*.”\x + \xo 10:35: \xt Psa 68:1.\x*
\v 36 Then¦67469 \add at¦67469 the end of the day\add* when it came to rest, he would say, “Yahweh¦67472, return¦67471 \add to\add* the \add ≈tens of thousands¦67473 of Israelis¦67474\add*.”
\c 11
\s1 Complaints and fire from Yahweh
\rem /s1 The People Complain to Moses; The Place Named Taberah; Fire From the Lord; Complaining in the Desert
\p
\v 1 \add ≈One day,\add* the people¦67481 were complaining¦67482 \add about their situation\add* and \add ≈when Yahweh¦67485 heard them, it made him angry\add* \add ≈so he sent a fire¦67493 that burnt¦67490 up the edges of their camp¦67497\add*.
\v 2 The people¦67500 cried¦67499 out to Mosheh \add for help\add*, and \add *he\add* prayed¦67504 to Yahweh¦67508, and the fire¦67510 stopped,
\v 3 and¦67512 they named that place¦67515 Taverah \add (which means ‘burning¦67522’)\add* because Yahweh's fire¦67522 had burnt¦67520 among¦67521 them.
\s1 The choosing of seventy elders
\rem /s1 Quail From the Lord; Moses Chooses Seventy Leaders
\p
\v 4 \add ≈However\add*, there was a \add ≈group of stirrers among the people¦67533\add* that¦67526 \add ≈badly wanted to have meat and other foods to eat\add*. \add ?≈That spread to all the Israelis¦67533 who wept and asked\add*, “Who'll give us meat to eat?
\v 5 We remember¦67540 the fish¦67543 that¦67544 we¦67546 ate¦67546 in¦67547 Egypt¦67547 for free, \add as well as\add* the cucumbers¦67550, melons¦67552, leeks¦67555, onions¦67558, and garlic¦67561,
\v 6 \add ≈but¦67563\add* now our¦67564 appetite¦67564 \add ≈has shrivelled up because we don't¦67566 see anything¦67567 to eat except¦67568 this ‘stuff’\add*.”
\p
\v 7 (The ‘stuff’ \add they ate every day\add* was \add a bit\add* like coriander¦67577 seed \add except kind of clear\add*.\x + \xo 11:7-8: \xt Exo 16:31.\x*
\v 8 \add Each morning\add* the people¦67584 went¦67583 around gathering¦67585 it, then ground¦67586 it with a \add stone\add* mill or pounded¦67589 it in¦67587 a mortar¦67590, then they boiled¦67591 it and made \add ≈something like bread¦67595 rolls with\add* it. They tasted¦67597 like fresh \add olive\add* oil¦67600.
\v 9 The ‘stuff’ actually descended on¦67602 the camp¦67606 during the night¦67607 with¦67602 the dew.)\x + \xo 11:9: \xt Exo 16:13-15.\x*
\p
\v 10 Mosheh heard the people¦67616 weeping¦67617 in¦67627 their tents¦67621 (set up by tribe and clan). \add *He\add* thought it was wrong, and \add it made\add* Yahweh¦67625 \add ≈very angry\add*.
\v 11 \add ≈So¦67631\add* Mosheh¦67632 \add ≈asked\add* Yahweh¦67635, “Why \add ≈have you caused me, your servant¦67638, to be in¦67644 trouble\add* \add like this\add*? \add ≈Don't you approve of me?\add*. \add ≈Why\add* has the burden¦67648 of all this people¦67651 group \add landed\add* on¦67644 me?
\v 12 \add ≈Was it me who\add* conceived¦67656 \add *it\add*? \add ≈Did I carry¦67670 it to the land promised to their ancestors¦67682, like I was a wet-nurse\add*?
\v 13 All these people¦67690 come to me to ask me to give them meat to eat. Where would I get \add enough\add* meat \add to feed all\add* them?
\v 14 I can't bear \add the load of\add* this entire¦67711 people¦67713 group by myself¦67707—it's too heavy¦67716 for me.
\v 15 If that's what you're¦67723 doing¦67725 to me, please¦67728 kill me now if I've¦67732 found¦67732 favour¦67733 in¦67734 your eyes¦67734. \add ≈Then¦67719 I wouldn't have to suffer like this\add*.”
\rem /s1 Moses Chooses Seventy Leaders; The Seventy Elders
\p
\v 16 Then Yahweh¦67742 told Mosheh¦67745, “Bring me seventy¦67749 of Yisrael's elders who you know¦67754 \add ≈are good leaders\add*, and take them to the \add ≈sacred¦67765 tent¦67765\add*, and \add ≈let them take their positions\add* there¦67768 with you.
\v 17 I'll come¦67771 down and talk with you there¦67774, and I'll take¦67775 some of the spirit¦67778 that's on you and put \add <it\add* on them, and then¦67771 they'll carry the burden¦67785 of the people¦67786 along with you. Then¦67771 you won't¦67787 \add have to\add* carry \add <it\add* by yourself¦67791.
\v 18 \add ≈Also,\add* tell the people¦67795 that because they wept in my hearing¦67803 about not having meat to eat like you all did in Egypt¦67813, they must¦67796 \add ≈purify\add* themselves for tomorrow¦67798, because I'll provide meat for you all to eat.
\v 19 You won't¦67824 \add just\add* have meat for a day or two, or for five, ten, or twenty¦67834 days,
\v 20 you have it for a \add whole\add* month¦67839 until¦67841 it comes out your nostrils¦67845. \add Yes,\add* it'll make you all nauseous because¦67849 you rejected¦67852 Yahweh¦67855 who's among you, and you all wept \add ≈in¦67857 front of him, complaining\add*, ‘Why did we ever leave Egypt¦67864?’ ”
\p
\v 21 Mosheh¦67867 \add ≈queried\add*, “There's 600,000 \add ≈able to serve in¦67876 the army\add* \add plus¦67877 women and¦67866 children\add*, yet you say that¦67874 you'll give them \add all\add* enough meat to eat \add every\add* day for month¦67883!
\v 22 \add ≈Even if we killed all the cattle and sheep, or caught all the fish in the sea¦67898, that wouldn't be enough meat\add* for \add all\add* them.”
\p
\v 23 “\add Do you think that\add* Yahweh's \add ≈powerless¦67910\add*?” Yahweh \add ≈replied\add*. “\add ≈Soon\add* you'll see¦67914 whether¦67915 or not my statement will \add ≈come¦67915 true\add*.”
\p
\v 24 \add ≈So¦67921\add* Mosheh¦67922 went out and \add ≈passed on\add* Yahweh's message¦67928 to the people. Then¦67921 he gathered¦67930 seventy¦67931 men from the \add ≈Israeli\add* elders¦67933 and stood them around¦67937 the tent.
\v 25 Then¦67940 Yahweh¦67941 came down in¦67943 the cloud¦67943 and spoke¦67944 to \add @Mosheh\add*, and he took \add ≈some of\add* the spirit away from him and put it on those seventy¦67955 elders¦67957. As the spirit rested¦67959 on them, they prophesied¦67962 \add ≈(but¦67940 they never did that¦67950 again)\add*.
\p
\v 26 Two of the men¦67969 who were listed (named Eldad¦67975 and Meydad), had remained¦67966 in the \add main\add* camp (not going to the \add sacred\add* tent), and the spirit¦67981 had \add also\add* rested¦67979 on¦67971 them and they prophesied¦67987 in the camp.
\v 27 A young¦67991 man¦67991 ran¦67990 to Mosheh¦67993 and told him that Eldad¦67995 and Meydad were prophesying¦67997 \add there\add* in¦67998 the camp¦67998.
\p
\v 28 Then¦68000 Nun's¦68004 son Yehoshua (who had helped Mosheh since his youth¦68007) \add ≈responded¦68000\add*, “My master¦68009 Mosheh, stop them \add from that\add*.”
\p
\v 29 \add ≈But¦68013\add* Mosheh¦68015 replied, “Are you¦68017 being jealous¦68016 \add ≈on my behalf\add*? \add ≈I'd be happy if\add* Yahweh¦68024 would put his spirit on \em all\em* the people¦68023 and¦68019 \add ≈make them into\add* prophets¦68025.”
\v 30 Then¦68035 Mosheh¦68036 and¦68041 the elders¦68041 \add ≈went back to their tents\add*.
\s1 Yahweh sends quails for meat
\rem /s1 The Lord Sends Quails; The Quails; The Lord Sends Quail
\p
\v 31 Then¦68044 Yahweh¦68048 sent a wind that blew quails¦68050 from the ocean, and¦68044 \add ≈they dropped\add* on the ground a day's walk in every direction around¦68064 the camp \add until they were piled\add* a metre high.
\v 32 \add ≈So¦68072\add* the people¦68073 went out and collected the quail¦68088—\add ≈each family getting at least¦68089 the equivalent of ten¦68091 large barrels full\add*, and they spread the meat around¦68096 the camp¦68097 \add to sun dry\add*.
\v 33 Then¦68110 when they started to \add cook and\add* eat \add some of the fresh\add* meat, Yahweh¦68106 \add ≈got very angry\add* and struck¦68109 the people with¦68108 a terrible plague¦68112 before they could even chew it.
\v 34 \add ≈So¦68116\add* that place¦68121 was named Kivrot-Hattaavah¦68124 \add (which means ‘Graves of the cravers’)\add*, because that was where they¦68128 buried¦68128 the people¦68131 who had craved \add <meat\add*.
\v 35 From Kivrot-Hattaavah, the people¦68137 \add ≈moved on¦68140\add* to Hatserot and¦68139 \add ≈stayed\add* \add *there\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Miryam's punishment
\rem /s1 Aaron and Miriam Jealous of Moses; The Complaints of Miriam and Aaron; Miriam Is Punished; Miriam and Aaron Oppose Moses
\p
\v 1 \add ≈One day,\add* Miryam and Aharon spoke¦68143 out against¦68146 Mosheh¦68146 because he'd taken an \add Ethiopian\add* woman (Kushitess) as a wife,
\v 2 and¦68160 they \add ≈challenged\add*, “Did Yahweh really only speak through Mosheh¦68164? Doesn't he also speak through us?” Yahweh heard \add what they said¦68160\add*.
\v 3 (Now Mosheh¦68176 was \add actually\add* a very humble man¦68175—more humble than anyone else \add ≈alive\add*.)
\p
\v 4 Then Yahweh¦68190 suddenly¦68191 told Mosheh¦68194, Aharon, and Miryam, “Go out, the three of you, to the \add ≈sacred¦68205\add* tent¦68205.” \add ≈So\add* the three of them went¦68207 there.
\v 5 and Yahweh¦68211 descended¦68210 in¦68212 a pillar¦68212 of cloud¦68213 and stood¦68214 at¦68212 the tent¦68216 opening and called¦68217 Aharon and Miryam, and the two of them \add ≈stepped forward\add*,
\v 6 and he¦68230 said¦68223, “\add ≈Listen to me\add*. When¦68223 there's a prophet¦68231 of Yahweh¦68232, I make myself¦68235 known¦68235 to him in a vision¦68233 and speak¦68237 to him in a dream¦68236,
\v 7 \add but\add* \add ≈I don't do that to\add* my servant¦68244 Mosheh¦68245. He's the \add most\add* faithful¦68249 \add ≈of all my people\add*\x + \xo 12:7 \xt Heb 3:5.\x*
\v 8 \add and\add* I speak to him \add ≈directly\add*—\add ≈face-to-face, and not in¦68261 parables, and he's able to see my\add* form. \add ≈So\add* why weren't you afraid¦68267 to speak against my servant¦68269 Mosheh¦68270?”
\p
\v 9 \add ≈So¦68272\add* Yahweh¦68275 \add ≈was angry\add* at¦68276 \add @Miryam and¦68277 Aharon\add*. Then¦68272 he departed¦68277
\v 10 and¦68279 the cloud¦68279 \add ≈moved\add* from the tent¦68282. Then¦68279 wow, Miryam had leprosy—her skin had gone as white as snow. As Aharon turned¦68287 to her, he saw, wow, she was leprous,
\v 11 and \add *he\add* \add ≈begged\add* Mosheh¦68299, “Please¦68296, my master¦68301, please¦68304 don't¦68302 \add ≈make us suffer for our foolish¦68309 disrespect and disobedience\add*.
\v 12 \add ≈Don't let her be like a still-born baby that's already starting to decompose when its mother¦68321 gives birth to it¦68322\add*.
\p
\v 13 \add ≈So¦68326\add* Mosheh¦68327 \add ≈pleaded with\add* Yahweh¦68330, “God¦68332, please, please heal¦68334 her!”
\p
\v 14 “\add ≈If\add* her father¦68344 had spit in her face, wouldn't she \add ≈stay inside in disgrace\add* for seven days?” Yahweh¦68340 \add ≈replied\add*. “\add So\add* she must¦68349 be put outside¦68355 the camp¦68356 for seven days, then after¦68357 that, she \add ≈can enter again\add*.”\x + \xo 12:14: \xt Num 5:2-3.\x*
\v 15 \add ≈So¦68360\add* Miryam was sent outside¦68362 the camp¦68363 for seven¦68364 days¦68365, and¦68366 the people¦68366 didn't¦68367 \add ≈move on\add* until¦68369 after she¦68360 \add was allowed\add* \add ≈to return\add*.
\v 16 After that, the people¦68376 left¦68375 Hatserot and¦68378 set up camp in¦68379 the Paran¦68380 wilderness¦68379.
\c 13
