\p
\v 16 Mosheh called¦68532 (Nun's¦68537 son) Hoshea¦68534, ‘Yehoshua’ \add (Joshua)\add*. Those were the names¦68522 of the men¦68523 that Mosheh sent¦68526 out to explore \add @Kanaan\add*.
\p
\v 17 \add ≈So¦68540\add* Mosheh¦68542 sent¦68540 them to explore Kanaan, telling them, “Go through the Negev¦68552 and¦68540 then¦68540 up into the hill country¦68556.
\v 18 \add ≈Find out\add* what the land's like, and whether¦68572 the people¦68567 living there are \add militarily\add* strong¦68570 or weak, and if they're many or few.
\v 19 \add ≈Find out\add* whether¦68586 the land is good¦68586 or bad¦68590, what cities¦68592 they live in¦68585, and¦68579 \add ≈how fortified¦68600 they are\add*.
\v 20 \add Find out\add* whether the soil is fertile¦68604 or not, whether or not there's trees there. \add ≈Be courageous\add* and¦68602 bring¦68617 back some of the produce¦68618 from that land.” (He said that because it was the time¦68620 \add of the year\add* when \add ≈grapes¦68623 were starting to ripen\add*.)
\p
\v 21 \add ≈So¦68625\add* \add @the twelve men\add* went¦68625 and¦68625 explored the region from the Tsin¦68632 wilderness¦68630 \add in the south, all the way\add* up to Rehob¦68635 at Levo¦68636-Hamat¦68637 \add in the north\add*.
\v 22 \add They started\add* in the Negev¦68640, and¦68639 went¦68639 as far as Hevron where some of Anak's¦68650 descendents lived: Ahiman¦68646, Sheshay, Talmai¦68648. Hevron had been built¦68654 seven¦68652 years¦68653 \add ≈before\add* Tsoan¦68656 in Egypt¦68657 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 23 When¦68659 they got to the Eshkol¦68663 riverbed, they cut off a branch¦68666 \add ≈with\add* a cluster¦68667 of grapes¦68668, and carried¦68670 it¦68670 on¦68671 a pole between two¦68672 of them, \add ≈along with some\add* pomegranates¦68675 and figs¦68678.
\v 24 (That place¦68680 was then called¦68682 Eshkol, \add meaning ‘cluster’\add*, because of the cluster \add of grapes¦68687\add* they'd taken from there¦68691.)
\s2 The reports from the scouts
\rem /s1 The Report of the Spies; The Scouting Report
\p
\v 25 Forty days \add ≈later\add*, they¦68695 returned¦68695 from exploring that land
