\v 26 and went¦68703 to Kadesh¦68722 in the Paran¦68721 wilderness¦68720. There they¦68703 reported back to Mosheh¦68706 and Aharon and all the assembled people¦68715, and showed¦68731 them the fruit¦68734 from the land,
\v 27 and told \add #them\add*, “We went¦68741 to the land where you sent¦68746 us, and it is indeed flowing¦68748 with milk and honey¦68750, and this is its fruit¦68754.
\v 28 However, the people living in that¦68761 land are powerful, and the cities¦68763 are very well fortified¦68764. Also, some of the Anak¦68770 people group live there¦68772.
\v 29 The Amalekite people live in the Negev¦68777, and the Hittites¦68778, Yebusites, and Amorites¦68780 live in the hill country¦68782, and the Kanaanites live along the coast and \add ≈along\add* the Yarden¦68790 \add (Jordan) river\add*.”
\p
\v 30 Then¦68792 Kalev \add (Caleb¦68793)\add* \add raised an arm\add* to quieten¦68792 the people¦68796 in front of Mosheh¦68799 \add ≈and stated\add*, “We'll certainly go in there and take it over, because we're capable of \add going\add* against \add #them\add*.”
\p
\v 31 \add ≈But¦68811\add* the men¦68811 who'd gone in with him \add ≈argued\add*, “\add No,\add*, we're not able to \add battle\add* against¦68820 them because \add #they're\add* stronger¦68825 than us.”
\v 32 Then¦68829 \add they went on¦68843 to\add* bring out a bad report¦68830 to the \add ≈Israelis¦68837\add* about the land that they'd explored, saying, “The land that we passed¦68842 to explore is a land that devours¦68847 those who live in it. \add ≈In addition,\add* all the people we saw in there were \add ≈tall\add* \add and¦68829 powerful\add*,
\v 33 plus¦68870 we saw the Nefilim¦68869 (descendants¦68865 of Anak¦68866), and we felt \add as small as\add* grasshoppers¦68872 \add ≈compared to them\add*, and \add ≈that's how they saw us as well\add*.”\x + \xo 13:33: \xt Gen 6:4.\x*
\c 14
\s1 The people rebel
\rem /s1 The People Complain; The People Rebel
\p
\v 1 The assembled \add people¦68886\add* \add ≈cried loudly that entire¦68878\add* night¦68887,
\v 2 and then¦68890 they \add started\add* to protest against¦68894 Mosheh¦68893 and Aharon. They \add ≈were all saying\add*, “If only we'd died in Egypt¦68909 or \add back there\add* in this wilderness¦68911.
\v 3 Why did Yahweh¦68918 bring¦68919 us to this \add ≈place only to be slaughtered in¦68926 battle with¦68926 our wives¦68927 and¦68917 children being taken as\add* plunder¦68930? Wouldn't it be better for us to return¦68934 to Egypt¦68935?”
\v 4 \add ≈So¦68937 they¦68937 said¦68937 to each other\add*, “Let's \add ≈choose a new leader¦68943\add* to take us back to Egypt¦68945.”
\p
\v 5 Then¦68947 Mosheh¦68948 and¦68947 Aharon fell \add ≈to their knees with their faces¦68952 bowed in front¦68953 of all the assembled¦68956 Israelis¦68958\add*.
\v 6 Then¦68961 Nun's¦68964 son Yehoshua and¦68961 Yefunneh's¦68968 son Kalev, two of those¦68971 who'd explored that land, tore their¦68976 clothes¦68976 \add in grief\add*
\v 7 and spoke to all \add ≈those Israelis¦68984 gathered there\add*, “The¦68986 land that¦68989 we¦68990 passed¦68990 throughout and explored¦68992 is a very, very good¦68994 \add ≈place\add*.
\v 8 If Yahweh¦69003 \add ≈is pleased with\add* us, then he'll take us into \add *it\add* and give¦69010 it to us—that¦69013 land flowing¦69016 with milk and honey¦69018.
\v 9 However, you all mustn't rebel¦69024 against¦69021 Yahweh, and you mustn't be scared of the people¦69031 in¦69021 that \add ≈area\add* because they'll \add be like\add* bread¦69034 for us. \add ≈There's nothing left to protect¦69037 them as\add* Yahweh is with¦69021 us, \add so\add* don't¦69022 be afraid.”
\v 10 Then¦69045 the \add ≈mass of people¦69061 talked about killing them by throwing rocks¦69051 at¦69051 them, but¦69045\add* Yahweh's \add ≈brilliant light\add* \add suddenly\add* appeared¦69054 to all the \add ≈Israelis¦69061 from the sacred¦69055\add* tent¦69055.
\s1 Mosheh asks Yahweh to forgive
\rem /s1 Moses Prays for the People
\p
\v 11 Yahweh¦69066 said¦69065 to Mosheh¦69069, “How long will this people¦69074 group spurn¦69073 me for? \add ≈How long will they¦69081 refuse to believe¦69081 in¦69082 me for\add*, \add ≈despite¦69073 all the miracles that¦69085 I've done among them\add*?
\v 12 I'll¦69089 strike¦69089 \add #them\add* with¦69090 a plague and destroy¦69091 them. I'm make you¦69093 into a nation¦69094 that's greater¦69096 and more powerful than them.”
\rem /s1 Moses Intercedes for the People
\p
\v 13 \add ≈But¦69100\add* Mosheh¦69101 \add ≈disagreed with¦69110\add* Yahweh¦69104, “Then¦69100 Egypt¦69106 will hear¦69105 about how you¦69109 \add ≈used\add* your¦69110 power¦69110 to bring \add #these\add* people¦69113 out from among¦69115 them,
\v 14 and they'll \add ≈report\add* to the inhabitants of \add @Kanaan\add*, because those \add ≡inhabitants\add* have heard¦69123 that \add you\add*, Yahweh¦69127, are \add right here\add* in¦69128 the middle of \add ≈us Israeli people¦69129\add*, and how your cloud rests on¦69128 us, and how you lead \add ≈us\add* with¦69128 that pillar of cloud that becomes a pillar of fire¦69149 at¦69128 night¦69150.
\v 15 If you \add ≈exterminate all the Israelis\add*, those nations¦69160 who've heard¦69163 about your fame will say,
\v 16 ‘\add That\add* Yahweh¦69171 couldn't take those people¦69175 into the land that¦69180 he promised them, so he slaughtered¦69184 them in¦69185 the wilderness¦69185.’
\v 17 \add ≈So¦69187\add* may the power¦69191 of my master¦69192 be great¦69188, just as you've¦69194 \add previously\add* said,
\v 18 ‘Yahweh¦69197 is \add ≈slow to anger¦69199\add* and \add ≈quick to show\add* loyal¦69202 commitment, \add ≈forgiving¦69203 disobedience and rebellion¦69205\add*. \add ≈Yet he doesn't leave the guilty\add* unpunished, \add ≈bringing the consequences\add* of the father's disobedience onto \add ≈the next three generations\add*.’
\v 19 Please forgive¦69231 \add #this\add* people for their \add ≈disobedience\add*, \add ≈applying\add* your \add ≈incredible\add* loyal¦69229 commitment like how you did when you brought these people from Egypt¦69234 all the way to here.”
\p
\v 20 “I've¦69241 forgiven¦69241 \add ≈as per your¦69242 request\add*,” Yahweh¦69240 \add ≈replied\add*,
\v 21 “\add ≈however,\add* as surely¦69244 as I live and¦69244 as all the land is filled¦69248 with Yahweh's \add ?≈light\add*,
\v 22 \add ≈and despite\add* \add *them\add* all seeing my \add ≈power\add* and the \add ≈miracles\add* that¦69269 I did \add both\add* in Egypt¦69272 and in the wilderness¦69273, they've \add now\add* tested¦69274 me \add ≈many\add* times¦69278 and \add ≈haven't done what I told them\add*,
\v 23 \add ≈so there's no way\add* that they'll \add ≈enter\add* the land that I promised to their¦69291 ancestors¦69291. All those¦69294 who despised¦69294 me won't¦69295 \add get to\add* \add ≈enter\add* it¦69296.
\v 24 \add ≈However,\add* my servant¦69298 Kalev \add (Caleb¦69299)\add* has a different spirit¦69302 with him, and he wholeheartedly¦69305 followed¦69306 me, \add ≈so\add* I'll¦69307 take¦69316 him into the land \add ≈that he explored\add*, and his descendants¦69315 will inherit¦69316 it.\x + \xo 14:24: \xt Josh 14:9-12.\x*
\v 25 The Amalekites and Kanaanites live in¦69321 the valleys¦69321. Tomorrow, you all must turn¦69323 and set off towards the wilderness¦69326 via the \add ≈route to\add* the Red Sea.
\s1 Punishment for the protestors
\rem /s1 An Attempted Invasion is Repulsed; The Lord Punishes the Israelites; The Lord Punishes the People for Complaining
\p
\v 26 Then Yahweh¦69334 said to Mosheh¦69337 and Aharon,
\v 27 “\add ≈How much longer\add* \add do I have to put up with\add* this evil¦69347 gathering that grumble¦69355 against me? I've¦69362 heard¦69362 the \add ≈complaints that the Israelis¦69356 are making\add* against me.
\v 28 Tell them \add this\add*, ‘Yahweh¦69371 declares that as I live, \add ≈your own words that I heard are exactly what\add* I'll¦69379 do to you all.
\v 29 \add Indeed\add* you'll \add ≈die there\add* in the wilderness¦69382—all those men who were listed as being twenty¦69393 years old and older that complained against¦69398 me.
\v 30 You all won't enter that land that I \add would have\add* \add ≈used my¦69411 power\add* to settle¦69412 you into. \add The only exceptions are\add* Yefunneh's¦69421 son Kalev \add (Caleb¦69418)\add* and Nun's¦69425 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*.
\v 31 The children¦69427 of you all that you said¦69429 would \add be taken\add* as plunder¦69430, I take \em them\em* in¦69440 and¦69427 they'll \add ≈experience\add* the land that you all have rejected¦69439,
\v 32 \add ≈but¦69442 your bodies will remain\add* in¦69445 this wilderness¦69445.
\v 33 Your sons will become shepherds¦69450 in the wilderness for forty¦69452 years, and¦69448 they will suffer¦69454 for your unfaithfulness¦69457 until¦69458 you \add yourselves\add* all \add ≈become\add* corpses¦69461 in the wilderness.
\v 34 \add ≈For each day\add* that¦69466 you explored the land, you'll all \add ≈bear your disobedience for one year\add*, so forty days¦69465 will be forty years \add ≈of experiencing\add* my displeasure¦69487.
\v 35 I, Yahweh¦69490, have spoken¦69491 that I'll¦69497 certainly do that to this evil¦69501 community¦69500 that joined together¦69503 against¦69504 me. They'll meet their¦69507 end¦69507 and¦69508 die¦69509 there¦69508 in¦69505 the wilderness¦69505.’ ”
\p
\v 36 \add ≈Now\add* those \add ten\add* men¦69511 who Mosheh¦69515 had sent¦69514 in to explore the land, and who'd returned¦69520 and the made the whole assembly grumble¦69521 against him because of their evil report¦69530 about the land,
\v 37 they¦69535 died¦69535 of a plague¦69542 \add ≈in¦69542 front¦69543\add* of Yahweh¦69544 after producing that evil¦69541 report¦69538.
\v 38 \add ≈However,\add* Yehoshua (\add Joshua\add*—Nun's¦69549 son) and¦69546 Kalev (\add Caleb¦69550\add*—Yefunneh's¦69553 son) who had also explored that land, continue to live on.
\s1 The wrong-minded attempt to invade
\rem /s1 The First Attempt to Invade the Land
\r (Deu. 1:41-46)
\p
\v 39 \add ≈So¦69565\add* Mosheh¦69566 \add ≈passed on to the Israelis¦69575 what Yahweh¦69576 had said\add*, and¦69565 the people \add ≈were extremely sad\add*.
\v 40 Early the \add next\add* morning¦69582, they went¦69583 up towards the hilltops, saying, “Look at¦69582 us all here! \add ≈Yes,\add* we sinned¦69600 \add yesterday, but¦69581 today\add* we'll go¦69591 up to the place¦69594 that¦69595 Yahweh¦69598 said¦69597.”
\p
\v 41 “What's that?” Mosheh¦69603 \add ≈responded¦69602\add*. “\add ≈Don't go against Yahweh's instructions because\add* \add @your plan\add* won't¦69613 succeed¦69614.
\v 42 Don't \add ≈continue onwards\add* because Yahweh¦69621 \add ≈isn't¦69616 with¦69622 you\add* and¦69623 \add for sure\add* you'll all be defeated¦69624 by your enemies¦69626
\v 43 because \add ≈you'll all be facing\add* the Amalekites and the Kanaanites and you'll die by the sword¦69634. Yes, you've turned¦69640 away from following¦69641 Yahweh¦69642 so \add *he\add* won't¦69643 be with¦69634 you all.”
\p
\v 44 \add Nevertheless,\add* they¦69662 dared¦69649 to \add ≈continue\add* up to the tops of the hills, \add ≈but¦69649\add* \add neither\add* Mosheh¦69659 nor the box \add ≈containing\add* the agreement with Yahweh¦69658, left the camp¦69664.
\v 45 Then¦69666 the Amalekites and Kanaanites that lived¦69669 in¦69670 that \add part of the\add* hill country¦69670 attacked¦69672 them and \add ≈killed\add* them as far down as Hormah¦69676.
\c 15
\s1 Instructions about sacrifices and offerings
\rem /s1 Supplementary Offerings; Laws about Sacrifice; Laws concerning Offerings; Various Offerings
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦69680 told Mosheh¦69683 \add (Moses¦69683)\add*,
\v 2 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦69689\add* that when they \add ≈enter the region¦69697 that I'll give¦69701 them to live in\add*, \add they must¦69691 do this:\add*
\v 3 \add When¦69704\add* you all make a gift to Yahweh—a burnt¦69707 offering or a sacrifice¦69710, to fulfill¦69711 a vow, or as a freewill¦69715 offering, or at¦69715 your appointed¦69717 times, to make a scent of pleasing¦69720 for Yahweh from the cattle or from the flock¦69728—
\v 4 then¦69730 the \add ≈donor\add* must¦69730 present¦69730 their offering to Yahweh¦69733, \add along with\add* a grain¦69734 offering of a kilogram of fine flour¦69735 mixed¦69737 with 0.9 litres of \add olive\add* oil¦69740.
\v 5 \add ≈Also\add* about a quarter of a litre of wine for the drink¦69743 offering \add must¦69746 be offered\add* with the burnt¦69749 offering and¦69742/or with \add each\add* male lamb¦69752.
\v 6 For a ram, there must¦69757 also be a grain¦69758 offering¦69757 of two¦69760 kilograms of fine flour¦69759 mixed with mixed with 1.2 litres of oil¦69763
\v 7 plus 1.2 litres of wine, all to be presented as a pleasing¦69774 aroma¦69772 to Yahweh¦69775.
\v 8 When¦69793 you¦69779 offer a young¦69780 bull as a burnt¦69783 offering or as a sacrifice¦69786 such as fulfilling¦69787 a vow or as a peace¦69792 offering,
\v 9 the \add ≈donor\add* must¦69795 present¦69795 a grain¦69801 offering¦69801 of 3.5kg of fine flour¦69802 mixed¦69805 with¦69806 two litres of oil¦69806,
\v 10 plus a drink¦69812 offering of two litres of wine, all to be presented as a pleasing¦69818 aroma¦69816 to Yahweh¦69819.
\p
\v 11 That's what must¦69822 be done for each bull¦69823 or ram or lamb or young goat.
\v 12 Whatever number \add of animals\add* that¦69836 you offer, \add ≈there must¦69837 be the appropriate\add* \add grain and wine offerings\add*.
\v 13 Every¦69843 \add ≈native-born\add* \add Israeli\add* must¦69846 do that when presenting a gift, all to be presented as a pleasing¦69856 aroma¦69854 to Yahweh¦69857.
\p
\v 14 If a \add ≈foreigner is staying with you all\add* or living among¦69867 you for \add multiple\add* generations¦69868, and¦69869 they make an offering¦69869 to Yahweh¦69874 with a pleasing¦69873 aroma¦69871, then¦69859 they must¦69861 \add ≈follow the same instructions\add* as all of you.
\v 15 \add Yes,\add* \add ≈the same regulations apply to both you and¦69884 the foreigners living among you all\add*. \add ≈That will always apply—foreigners in front¦69892 of Yahweh¦69893 must¦69891 do the same\add* as all of you.
\v 16 One \add set of\add* instructions and regulations for \add both\add* you and the foreigner that lives among you all.
\p
\v 17 Then Yahweh¦69907 told Mosheh¦69910,
\v 18 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦69916 that\add* when you get to the land that I'm taking you to,
\v 19 and \add you all settle there and\add* start eating \add ≈food that you've grown there\add*, you all must¦69934 \add ≈dedicate\add* a \add special\add* contribution¦69935 to Yahweh¦69936.
\v 20 You must¦69941 present the first¦69938 portion of your dough¦69939 and hold it up \add just\add* like a presentation from the threshing¦69944 floor¦69944.
\v 21 You¦69952 all must¦69951 do that \add each year\add* with your first¦69949 dough¦69950, even through¦69954 \add future\add* generations¦69954.
\s1 Handling unintentional non-compliance
\rem /s1 Offerings for Unintentional Sins
\p
\v 22 “\add ≈However,\add* if you \add ≈do something wrong\add* and don't¦69959 follow all these¦69965 instructions that¦69966 Yahweh¦69969 told Mosheh¦69972,
\v 23 i.e., \add ≡don't follow\add* everything that Yahweh¦69979 has commanded through Mosheh¦69983 from when the commands were given \add right\add* through to \add ≈future\add* generations¦69991,
\v 24 then¦69993 \add ≈assuming that it was an accident\add*, the community¦70002 must¦69999 offer a young bull¦70003 for a burnt¦70008 offering to make a pleasing¦70010 aroma¦70009 for Yahweh¦70011, along with its grain¦70012 offering and¦69993 drink¦70013 offering as per the instructions, plus¦69999 a male¦70015 goat¦70015 as a sin¦70019 offering.
\v 25 \add That way\add* the priest¦70022 will make atonement¦70021 for the \add ≈Israeli¦70028 community\add* and they'll be forgiven¦70030 because it was a mistake and they'd brought¦70037 their gift as an offering to Yahweh¦70042 plus¦70030 their sin¦70043 offering because of their mistake.
\v 26 The¦70055 \add ≈Israeli¦70054 community\add* will be forgiven¦70050 along with¦70058 \add ≈any foreigner living among¦70058 them\add* because it¦70050 accidentally affected the entire community.
\p
\v 27 “\add ≈Now\add* if a single person disobeys by mistake, then that person must¦70070 present¦70072 a one-year-old female¦70073 goat¦70073 as a sin offering¦70077,
\v 28 and¦70091 the priest¦70080 will make atonement for that person. \add In that way,\add* the one making a mistake in¦70085 front¦70087 of Yahweh¦70088 will be forgiven¦70091.
\v 29 \add Both¦70096\add* \add ≈native-born Israelis¦70095\add* and¦70097 foreigners living among them must¦70102 \add all\add* \add ≈follow the same instructions after\add* making a mistake.
\v 30 \add ≈However,\add* any person who \add ≈disobeys defiantly\add*, whether native-born or foreigner, they are slandering Yahweh¦70122 and¦70107 that person must¦70110 be \add ≈driven out of the community\add*
\v 31 because they've despised¦70135 Yahweh's message¦70132 and disobeyed his instructions. That person must¦70142 be \add ≈completely\add* cut off and their guilt¦70145 \add remains\add* on¦70146 them.
\s1 Violating the rest day
\rem /s1 Penalty for Violating the Sabbath; Penalty for Breaking the Sabbath; The Man Who Broke the Sabbath; The Sabbath-Breaker Put to Death
\p
\v 32 \add One day\add* when the \add ≈Israelis¦70152\add* were in¦70153 the wilderness¦70153, they \add ≈noticed\add* a man gathering¦70156 firewood on¦70153 the rest day,
\v 33 and those¦70163 who \add ≈caught\add* him took him to Mosheh¦70169 and Aharon¦70172 and the rest of the community.
\v 34 They put him into custody¦70180, because it hadn't been decided¦70183 what to do with¦70180 him,
\v 35 and Yahweh¦70191 told Mosheh¦70194, “That man¦70197 must definitely be put to death¦70196—the community must do it outside¦70204 the camp¦70205 by throwing rocks¦70200 at¦70200 him.”
\v 36 \add ≈So¦70207\add* the community took him outside¦70214 the camp¦70215, and¦70207 they executed him by throwing rocks¦70218 at¦70218 him just as Yahweh¦70222 had commanded¦70221 Mosheh¦70225.
\s1 Tassels on clothes
\rem /s1 Fringes on Garments; Rules about Tassels; Tassels on Clothing; Tassels on Garments
\p
\v 37 Then Yahweh¦70229 told Mosheh¦70232,
\v 38 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦70238 that\add* they must make tassels on the corners¦70247 of their \add outer\add* \add ≈robes\add*. Each tassel must have a blue cord, and they must do this \add ≈for all future\add* generations¦70249.
\v 39 Then¦70258 when you see¦70261 a tassel¦70260, it'll remind you of Yahweh's¦70269 instructions, and \add so\add* you'll \add ≈follow\add* them \add ≈rather than your own desires and lusts that¦70279 lead you all into unfaithfulness\add*.
\v 40 \add Instead,\add* you'll remember¦70286 and follow my instructions, and \add ≈stay pure¦70294\add* for your god¦70295.
\v 41 I am your god Yahweh—the one who brought¦70301 you all out of Egypt¦70304 (Heb. Mitsrayim) to be your god. I am Yahweh your god.”
\c 16
\s1 Korah's rebellion
\rem /s1 Revolt of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram; Korah's Rebellion; Korah, Dathan and Abiram; The Rebellion of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram
\p
\v 1 \add ≈Now\add* Korah¦70314 (son of Yitshar, son of Kehat, son of Levi¦70323) \add along with\add* Datan¦70324 and Aviram (sons of Eliav) and On¦70328 (son of Pelet¦70331)\x + \xo 16:1-35: \xt Jude 11.\x*
\v 2 \add ≈rebelled\add* against Mosheh¦70337 along with 250 \add ≈respected, Israeli¦70341\add* community leaders¦70344.
\v 3 They \add ≈got together and challenged\add* Mosheh¦70355 and Aharon, “\add ≈You think you're great but¦70352 the entire¦70365 community is sacred¦70369 and has Yahweh among¦70370 us, so why do you consider yourselves¦70373 more important than Yahweh's community?\add*”
\p
\v 4 \add ≈When¦70379\add* Mosheh¦70380 heard \add <that\add*, he¦70381 fell \add ≈to his knees with his face to the ground\add*
\v 5 and \add ≈responded\add* to Korah¦70389 and his \add ≈supporters\add*, “\add Tomorrow\add* morning¦70396 Yahweh will show who's sacred¦70406 and who belongs to him. \add ?≈Yahweh will present his chosen leader\add*. make known¦70397 who is to him and the holy one, and he will present to him, and whom he chooses¦70411 he will present to him.
\v 6 \add ≈So\add* Korah¦70423 and¦70424 \add ≈supporters\add*, bring incense burners
\v 7 and put \add ≈burning¦70431 coals\add* and incense¦70434 in¦70429 them, and bring them to \add ≈Yahweh's presence\add* tomorrow¦70437. Then¦70428 the man¦70439 that Yahweh chooses¦70442 will be the sacred¦70445 one. \add ≈It's you Levites who think you're\add* great.”
\p
\v 8 Then¦70452 Mosheh¦70453 told Korah¦70456, “\add ≈You Levites\add*, please¦70459 listen¦70457.
\v 9 Isn't it enough¦70463 for you all that Yisrael's god¦70468 separated you from the \add rest of\add* the Israeli¦70468 community to present you to him to serve¦70485 in Yahweh's residence and to stand¦70482 in front¦70483 of the gatherings to minister to them?
\v 10 \add @Yahweh\add* has presented you and¦70487 your brothers¦70493, the \add other\add* \add ≈Levites\add* to approach \add <him\add*. Are you all wanting the priesthood¦70501 \add now\add* also?
\v 11 \add ≈So\add* it's Yahweh¦70511 that you and your¦70507 group are opposing, not \add really\add* Aharon that you're all grumbling¦70517 about.”
\p
\v 12 Then¦70521 Mosheh¦70522 \add ≈summoned\add* Eliav's sons¦70526 Datan¦70524 and¦70521 Aviram \add ≈but¦70521 they¦70528 refused\add*, “We won't¦70529 come¦70530.
\v 13 \add ≈Isn't it enough¦70532\add* that you brought¦70534 us \em out\em* of a land flowing¦70536 with¦70540 milk and honey¦70538, to kill us \add here\add* in¦70540 the wilderness¦70540, without also making yourself the ruler over us?
\v 14 \add ≈What's more\add*, you didn't¦70550 bring us into a land flowing¦70554 with milk and honey¦70556 or give us an inheritance¦70561 of land and vineyards¦70563. Will you gouge¦70567 out the eyes¦70564 of those¦70566 \add @Kanaanites\add* \add so that we can defeat them\add*? \add No,\add* we won't¦70550 come¦70569.”
\p
\v 15 \add That made\add* Mosheh¦70572 very angry and¦70571 he told Yahweh¦70577, “Don't \add ≈accept\add* their¦70583 grain offering¦70583. I've¦70588 \add never\add* taken¦70588 \add even\add* one donkey¦70585 from them \add ≈or done anything bad to any of\add* them.”
\p
\v 16 Then¦70596 Mosheh¦70597 told Korah¦70600, “You and¦70596 all your¦70604 group, \add ≈must appear in front¦70606\add* of Yahweh¦70607 tomorrow¦70611, \add ≈as will\add* Aharon.
\v 17 \add Each\add* man must¦70617 bring¦70620 his pan with incense¦70619 \add ≈burning in it\add* and¦70613 present¦70620 it to Yahweh¦70622—\add ≈all 250 of you as well as\add* Aharon.
\v 18 \add ≈So¦70633\add* \add the next day,\add* they all brought their pans with \add ≈burning¦70638 coals\add* and incense¦70641 in them, and they stood¦70642 at the entrance¦70643 of the \add ≈sacred¦70644\add* tent¦70644, as did Mosheh¦70646 and Aharon¦70647.
\v 19 plus¦70662 Korah¦70651 had \add also\add* assembled¦70649 the entire¦70654 community \add ≈to oppose\add* \add @Mosheh and¦70662 Aharon\add* at the entrance¦70659 to the \add ≈sacred¦70660\add* tent¦70660. Then¦70649 Yahweh's \add ≈brilliance\add* appeared¦70662 to all the community
\v 20 and Yahweh¦70674 warned Mosheh¦70677 and Aharon¦70680,
\v 21 “Get away from \add ≈all those people\add*, then I can destroy them in an instant.”
\p
\v 22 \add ≈However,\add* \add @Mosheh and Aharon\add* fell \add ≈to their knees with their faces¦70695 to the ground and interceded\add*, “God¦70697, \add you are\add* the god \add ≈who gives life to everything\add*. Will you be angry¦70710 at the entire¦70707 community \add because of\add* the sin of one man?”
\v 23 \add ≈So\add* Yahweh¦70714 told Mosheh¦70717,
\v 24 “Tell the \add ≈people to keep back from the homes\add* of Korah¦70729, Datan¦70730, and¦70731 Aviram.”
\p
\v 25 Then¦70733 Mosheh¦70734 \add ≈walked to\add* \add the homes of\add* Datan¦70738 and Aviram, and the \add ≈Israeli¦70742\add* elders¦70742 followed¦70740 behind him¦70741,
\v 26 and he told the \add ≈people\add*, “Please \add ≈keep back\add* from the tents¦70753 of these¦70756 wicked¦70755 men¦70754, and don't¦70757 touch¦70759 anything of theirs, in case you get caught up in their \add ≈disobedience\add*.”
\v 27 \add ≈So¦70771\add* \add @the rest of the Israelis\add* \add ≈kept back\add* from the residences of Korah¦70775, Datan, and Aviram. \add ≈Meanwhile,\add* Datan and Aviram had come out of their tents¦70785, and were standing¦70783 at the entrances¦70784 with their wives¦70786 and children¦70787.
\p
\v 28 Then¦70790 Mosheh¦70791 said¦70790, “This is how \add you'll all\add* known that \add it was\add* Yahweh¦70796 \add ≈who selected me for this role\add*—it's \add never\add* \add ≈been something that I aspired to\add*:
\v 29 If all these¦70816 men \add ≈die¦70815 a natural death¦70811 like most people\add*, then Yahweh¦70824 didn't¦70823 \add ≈choose\add* me,
\v 30 \add ≈but¦70827\add* if Yahweh \add ≈does something new\add* and the ground opens¦70832 its mouth¦70836 and swallows¦70837 them and their homes and tents and \add ≈all their possessions\add*, and if they¦70850 then go¦70845 down alive¦70846 into \add ≈their grave\add*, then you'll all know¦70848 that it was because these¦70852 men¦70851 rejected Yahweh.”
\p
\v 31 \add ≈As soon as Mosheh had finished¦70858 speaking¦70859\add*, the ground below \add @those men\add* split¦70865 open
\v 32 and the earth¦70871 opened¦70870 its mouth¦70874 and swallowed¦70875 them and their homes and every¦70881 man who \add ≈backed\add* Korah¦70885 along with all \add &their\add* property¦70889.
\v 33 They¦70898 went¦70891 down alive¦70897 to \add ≈their grave\add*, along with everything they owned, and then¦70891 the ground covered¦70899 over them and they \add ≈vanished\add* from the \add ≈community\add*.
\v 34 All¦70908 the people who were around¦70910 them fled \add away\add* \add ≈screaming because they were afraid of getting swallowed¦70917 by the earth¦70918 as well\add*.
\p
\v 35 Then¦70920 Yahweh¦70923 \add ≈sent\add* fire¦70920 that consumed the 250 men who were presenting incense¦70930.
\s1 The incense burners
\rem /s1 The Fire Pans
\p
\v 36 Then Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 37 “Tell the priest Eleazar (Aharon's son) to \add ≈collect the incense pans\add* from \add ≈those who were burnt\add*, and scatter the \add ≈coals far away\add* because they're sacred.
\v 38 The pans of those who \add ≈rebelled at the expense of their own lives\add* must be hammered into thin plates \add ≈to be attached\add* to the altar, because they presented them \add ≈in front\add* of Yahweh and \add now\add* they're sacred, and they'll become a \add ≈reminder\add* for the \add ≈Israelis\add*.
\v 39 \add ≈So\add* the priest Eleazar took the bronze incense burners that had been presented by those men who'd been burnt up, and they were hammered into a plating for the altar
\v 40 for a memorial for the \add ≈Israelis\add* just as Yahweh had told him via Mosheh. That's a reminder that no one who's not a descendant of Aharon is allowed to approach Yahweh with incense burners, so they don't end up like Korah and his \add ≈supporters\add*.
\s1 The people complain and cause a plague
\rem /s1 Aaron Saves the People
\p
\v 41 \add ≈However,\add* the next day the \add ≈Israelis\add* complained about Mosheh and Aharon, “\add ≈It was you who\add* killed Yahweh's people.”
\v 42 \add ≈But\add* as the community gathered \add there\add* against Mosheh and Aharon, they \add ≈looked across\add* to the \add ≈sacred\add* tent, and wow, the cloud covered over it and Yahweh's \add ≈brilliance\add* appeared.
\v 43 Mosheh and Aharon went \add over\add* to the front of the \add ≈sacred\add* tent,
\v 44 and Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 45 “Get away from this \add ≈gathering\add* and then I'll finish them \add ≈in an instant\add*.”
\p \add ≈But\add* \add @Mosheh and Aharon\add* fell \add ≈to their knees with their faces to the ground\add*,
\v 46 and Mosheh told Aharon, “Take the incense burner, and put fire in it from the altar and incense, and take it quickly to the \add ≈people\add* and make atonement for them, because Yahweh's rage is \add already\add* \add ≈burning\add*—the plague has begun.”
\v 47 \add ≈So\add* Aharon took it as Mosheh had told \add <him\add* and ran into the middle of the \add ≈people\add*. Wow, the plague had already begun, \add ≈so he burnt\add* incense and made atonement for \add *them\add*.
\v 48 He stood between those who were dying and those still alive, and the plague was restrained.
\v 49 There were 14,700 \add >people\add* who died from the plague, in addition to those who'd died due to Korah's \add ≈rebellion\add*.
\v 50 Then Aharon returned to Mosheh at the \add ≈sacred\add* tent entrance, \add ≈as\add* the plague had been \add ≈stopped\add*.
\c 17
\s1 The budding of Aharon's rod
\rem /s1 Aaron's Walking Stick; The Budding of Aaron's Staff; The Budding of Aaron's Rod
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦70935 told Mosheh¦70938,
\v 2 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis\add* to bring you twelve staffs—one from each ancestral \add tribe\add* with the leader's name inscribed on it,
\v 3 and inscribe Aharon's name on¦70970 the staff for the \add ≈Levites\add* so there's one for each tribe.
\v 4 Put them \add all\add* in the \add ≈sacred\add* tent in front of the \add ≈sacred box\add* where I meet with you,
\v 5 and then the staff of the man¦71012 that I choose \add to be the priest\add* will sprout. Then the \add ≈people¦71005\add* can stop complaining to me about you.”
\p
\v 6 \add ≈So Mosheh¦71047 passed the message on to the Israeli¦71041\add* leaders and they¦71037 gave him one staff for each leader—\add ≈a total¦71038 of twelve including¦71037 Aharon's one\add*,
\v 7 and Mosheh¦71065 \add ≈laid\add* them \add ≈in front\add* of Yahweh¦71079 in the \add ≈sacred¦71072\add* tent¦71072.
\p
\v 8 Then the next day when Mosheh¦71083 went¦71082 to the \add ≈sacred¦71088\add* tent¦71088, wow, he saw that Aharon's staff (\add ≈representing\add* Levi tribe) had sprouted, plus¦71082 it had blossomed and produced a flower and ripened almonds!\x + \xo 17:8-10: \xt Heb 9:4.\x*
\v 9 Mosheh¦71097 took all the staffs \add ≈out of the tent\add* to the people \add ≈to look at\add* and¦71093 \add ≈each of the leaders\add* took back his own staff,
\v 10 then Yahweh told Mosheh, “Put Aharon's staff \add back\add* \add ≈in front of the sacred chest\add*. \add ≈Keep it there as a reminder to\add* \add any\add* \add ≈rebels to stop complaining against me so they¦71108 won't\add* die.”
\v 11 \add ≈So¦71118\add* Moses¦71115 did what Yahweh¦71143 had commanded.
\p
\v 12 Then the \add ≈Israelis\add* \add ≈complained\add* to Mosheh¦71153, “Wow, \add ≈we're done for—it's clear that we're all going to die\add*!
\v 13 Everyone who goes close to Yahweh's residence \add ≈gets killed\add*. \add ≈Won't we all die\add*?”
\c 18
\s1 The work of priests and Levites
\rem /s1 Duties of Priests and Levites; Responsibility of Priests and Levites
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦71452 told Aharon \add (Aaron¦71455)\add*, “You and your \add ≈Levite brothers and cousins\add* and \add all\add* your descendants must bear the \add ≈imperfections\add* of the \add ≈sacred¦71466 tent¦71466\add*, and you and your sons must bear the \add ≈imperfections\add* of your priesthood¦71474.
\v 2 Bring your \add ≈Levite\add* brothers¦71479 (your father's tribe) to \add ≈work closely with\add* you and to assist¦71488 you \add as\add* you and your sons¦71490 \add ≈perform your duties at\add* the \add ≈sacred\add* tent¦71493.
\v 3 They must¦71496 look after the tent¦71501, however, they mustn't approach the \add ≈furnishings or utensils\add*, or the altar¦71509, so that both you¦71497 and¦71496 they won't¦71510 die¦71514.
\v 4 Then¦71522 must¦71522 \add ≈work¦71531 closely with\add* you¦71523 and¦71522 \add ≈take care\add* of \add ≈all the duties to do with\add* the \add ≈sacred¦71528\add* tent, \add ≈but¦71522\add* no \add ≈outsider¦71533\add* \add ≈is allowed to approach\add*.
\v 5 You¦71554 \add priests\add* will \add ≈take care\add* of the sacred¦71542 place¦71542 and the altar¦71545, and then¦71539 there won't¦71546 be anymore fury against¦71549 the \add ≈Israeli¦71553 people¦71553\add*.
\v 6 \add ≈Now listen\add*, I've¦71558 taken¦71558 your brothers¦71561 the Levites¦71562 \add ≈out from the rest of the Israelis¦71564\add* as a gift¦71567 for you—they're given to \add ≈do the duties\add* at the \add ≈sacred¦71574\add* tent¦71574.
\v 7 \add ≈However,\add* it's you¦71579 and your¦71578 sons¦71578 who \add ≈are the priests\add* who must serve¦71590 for things to do with the altar¦71587 and inside¦71588 the curtain¦71589. Your priesthood is a gift¦71592 of service¦71591, and any \add ≈outsider¦71597\add* who approaches¦71598 must be executed.”
\rem /s1 Offerings for Priests and Levites; Support for the Priests and Levites; The Priests' Portion; The Share of the Priests
\p
\v 8 Then Yahweh¦71603 told Aharon, “\add ≈Also listen\add*, I've put you in charge¦71613 of \add ≈looking after\add* the sacred¦71617 offerings¦71614 \add ≈to me\add*. I've given¦71623 them to you and your sons¦71625 as your \add ≈permanent income\add*.
\v 9 Every offering apart from the burnt offerings, will belong¦71632 to you. That includes their grain¦71644 offerings, their sin¦71647 offerings, and their guilt¦71650 offerings. \add ≈Once they're given, they become sacred¦71635,\add* and they're for you and your¦71658 sons¦71658.
\v 10 You and \add ≈the males in your families\add* may eat that sacred offering \add ≈but do remember that it's sacred\add*.
\p
\v 11 “\add ≈In¦71682 addition,\add* the \add people's¦71681\add* raised offerings belong¦71675 to you, and¦71673 they are \add ≈permanently given¦71684 to your entire families\add* to eat—everyone¦71691 who's ‘clean¦71693’ may eat them.
\p
\v 12 “All the best of the fresh¦71700 oil¦71700, and the new wine and grain¦71705 that¦71707 they give to Yahweh¦71710, I give to you.
\v 13 The first¦71714 \add ≈portions of all their¦71718 harvests\add* that¦71719 they¦71721 bring¦71721 to Yahweh¦71722, belong¦71724 to you—everyone¦71725 in¦71718 your¦71728 \add ≈families\add* who's ‘clean¦71727’ may eat¦71729 them.
\p
\v 14 “Everything¦71731 throughout Yisrael¦71734 that's dedicated \add to Yahweh\add* will belong¦71736 to you.\x + \xo 18:14: \xt Lev 27:28.\x*
\p
\v 15 “Every¦71738 firstborn \add male\add* \add ≈baby\add*, as well as animals, will belong¦71751 to Yahweh¦71748, \add however\add* you must¦71747 buy back the \add ≈human¦71749 babies\add* as well as the firstborns from the ‘unclean¦71765’ livestock.
\v 16 \add ≈The babies\add* must¦71772 be bought back when they're one month¦71771 old, paying five¦71775 silver¦71774 coins \add ≈of the proper weight according to the scales at¦71773 the sacred¦71778 tent¦71778\add*.
\v 17 \add ≈However,\add* the firstborn cows or sheep or goats can't¦71795 be bought back. They are sacred¦71797—you must¦71796 sprinkle¦71802 their blood¦71801 on the altar¦71805 and burn their fat as an offering¦71810 that's a soothing¦71812 aroma¦71811 for Yahweh¦71813.
\v 18 Their meat will belong to you¦71818, just like the breast¦71819 or the right¦71822 thigh¦71821 of the wave offerings¦71820 are yours¦71823.
\v 19 All sacred¦71829 donations by the \add ≈Israelis¦71832\add*, I've \add ≈permanently\add* given to you and your \add ≈children\add* to eat—it's an \add ≈irrevocable agreement with\add* Yahweh¦71835 for you and your \add future\add* ancestors.”
\s1 The Levites' share
\p
\v 20 Yahweh¦71855 \add also\add* told Aharon, “You \add priests\add* won't¦71860 inherit \add ≈any land or property\add*—I am your share and¦71854 your inheritance \add ≈among¦71867 the Israelis¦71872\add*.
\rem /s1 The Share of the Levites
\p
\v 21 For an inheritance¦71884 for the \add ≈Levites\add*, I've given them all the tenths \add ≈given by the Israelis\add* as their inheritance in¦71883 exchange for their service¦71890 at¦71883 the \add ≈sacred¦71894\add* tent¦71894.
\v 22 The¦71902 \add ≈other Israelis¦71901\add* mustn't approach that tent¦71905 \add or\add* they'll \add ≈incur guilt\add* and¦71897 die¦71909,
\v 23 \add ≈but¦71911\add* the Levites¦71912 must serve¦71911 at¦71925 the \add ≈sacred¦71917\add* tent¦71917 and¦71911 they must bear their¦71921 \add ≈inadequacies\add*. That¦71927 order \add ≈applies for all future generations¦71924\add*, \add ≈including¦71919\add* the not inheriting¦71929 any land \add ≈like the other Israelis¦71926\add*.
\v 24 \add That's\add* because I've¦71949 given the Levites¦71944 that tenth that the \add ≈other Israelis¦71936\add* offer¦71940 to Yahweh¦71941 as a donation. That's why I said¦71949 that they won't¦71954 receive \add ≈any other inheritance¦71955\add*.”
\s1 The Levites' contribution
\rem /s1 The Levites' Tithe
\p
\v 25 Then Yahweh¦71960 told Mosheh¦71963,
\v 26 “Tell the Levites¦71968: ‘When¦71966 you all receive the tenth from the \add ≈Israelis¦71976\add* that I've given to you as you inheritance¦71986, then¦71966 you must¦71969 offer¦71987 a tenth of that tenth as a donation to Yahweh¦71990.
\v 27 That will be considered as your contribution¦71998 \add just\add* as if it¦71996 was grain¦71999 from the threshing¦72002 floor¦72002, or \add ≈juice\add* from the winepress¦72006.
\v 28 \add ≈So\add* when you all offer¦72009 that donation from all the tenths that you receive from the \add ≈Israelis¦72020\add*, it must¦72009 then be given as Yahweh's contribution to the priest¦72029 Aharon. DOUBLE-CHECK
\v 29 When an offering¦72033 is presented to Yahweh¦72038, it¦72045 must¦72033 be \add ≈the best parts of whatever is given\add*.’
\v 30 Also¦72055 tell them, ‘When¦72047 you all present \add ≈the best of what was given\add*, it'll be as \add ≈it's come straight\add* from the threshing¦72057 floor¦72057 or the winepress¦72059.
\v 31 \add The rest\add* is for your wages for the service¦72074 you all do at¦72075 the \add ≈sacred¦72075\add* tent¦72075, and¦72061 you all can eat¦72061 it \add ≈wherever you want to\add*.
\v 32 \add ≈After¦72093 donating the best tenth from it\add*, you won't¦72078 incur guilt for what you all do with¦72083 the rest of it, \add ≈however\add* you all mustn't defile any sacred¦72090 things or you'll die¦72097.’ ”
\c 19
\s1 The red cow's ashes
\rem /s1 The Water of Purification; Ashes of the Red Cow; Ceremony of the Red Heifer; The Water of Cleansing
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦72101 told Mosheh¦72104 and Aharon,
\v 2 “This is \add ≈a new\add* law that Yahweh¦72116 has commanded¦72115, ‘Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦72122\add* that¦72113 they¦72124 must bring¦72124 you¦72125 an unblemished¦72128 red heifer¦72126 \add ≈with¦72132 no¦72128 defects¦72128\add* \add ≈and¦72124 that has never had a yoke on¦72132 its neck\add*.
\v 3 Give it to the priest¦72146 Eleazar¦72145, and he must¦72141 take¦72147 it outside¦72151 the camp¦72152 and have \add someone¦72153\add* slaughter¦72153 it \add ≈in front of him\add*.
\v 4 Then¦72157 Eleazar¦72158 must¦72157 get some of its¦72170 blood with¦72161 his finger¦72161 seven¦72171 times¦72172 and¦72157 \add ≈flick\add* it onto the ground \add ≈directly in¦72161 front¦72165\add* of the \add ≈sacred¦72167\add* tent.
\v 5 Then¦72174 \add ≈while he watches\add*, they must¦72174 \add completely\add* burn¦72191 the heifer¦72177—its skin and flesh¦72184, and \add including¦72182\add* its blood¦72187 and dung.
\v 6 \add ≈Meanwhile,\add* the priest¦72194 must¦72193 take¦72193 some cedar¦72196 wood, hyssop¦72197, and scarlet¦72199 wool, and throw¦72200 them into \add the fire\add* where the cow is burning¦72204.
\v 7 Then¦72207 the priest must¦72207 wash his clothes¦72208 and¦72207 bathe¦72210. After that, he can return to the camp¦72217, \add ≈but¦72207\add* \add *he'll\add* be ‘unclean¦72218’ until¦72220 that evening¦72222.
\v 8 The \add man\add* who burnt \add @the cow\add* must¦72226 \add also\add* wash his clothes¦72227 and bathe¦72229, and he will \add also\add* be ‘unclean¦72232’ until¦72233 that evening¦72235.
\v 9 A¦72253 ‘clean’ man¦72239 must¦72237 collect the cow's ashes and¦72237 place them in¦72247 a \add ≈sacred\add* place outside¦72245 the camp¦72246 where they can be used for water¦72255 for purification for the \add ≈Israelis¦72251\add* to purify from \add ≈disobedience\add*.
\v 10 Then¦72260 that man who collected the ashes must¦72260 \add also\add* wash his clothes¦72268 and be ‘unclean¦72269’ until¦72270 that evening¦72272. Those¦72275 regulations¦72279 will permanently apply both to \add ≈Israelis¦72274\add* and to foreigners living among¦72278 them.
\s1 Contact with a corpse
\rem /s1 Contact with a Corpse
\p
\v 11 “ ‘\add #All those\add* who touch¦72282 a dead¦72283, human body¦72283 will be ‘unclean¦72288’ for seven¦72289 days¦72290.
\v 12 On the third day, they must¦72293 purify themselves, and then they'll be ‘clean’ on the seventh day. (If they don't¦72303 purify themselves, they'll won't¦72303 become ‘clean’ on that seventh day—
\v 13 if they've touched¦72314 a dead¦72315, human¦72317 body¦72316 and don't¦72321 purify¦72322 themselves, that would defile Yahweh's residence, and \add so\add* they must¦72320 be \add ?≈permanently removed from the camp\add*. If the purifying water¦72333 wasn't sprinkled¦72337 on them, that ‘uncleanness¦72342’ will remain on them.)
\p
\v 14 “ ‘This is the regulation if a person dies in a tent: Everyone¦72354 who was in the tent, and¦72358 everyone¦72352 that enters \add afterwards\add*, will all be ‘unclean¦72362’ for seven¦72363 days¦72364,
\v 15 and¦72366 every container that¦72369 doesn't have its lid on becomes ‘unclean¦72375’.
\v 16 \add ≈Out in\add* the countryside¦72385, who touches¦72381 the corpse of someone killed¦72386 in a fight, or any dead¦72390 human¦72394 body¦72390 or bone or grave¦72396, will be ‘unclean¦72397’ for seven¦72398 days¦72399.
\v 17 \add ≈Someone\add* must¦72401 take¦72401 some of the ashes¦72403 from that burnt cow, and¦72401 put them into a jar with some fresh, running water¦72408, then¦72401 \add pour some of it over them\add*.
\v 18 Then¦72414 a man who's ‘clean¦72419’ must¦72414 dip some hyssop¦72415 in that water¦72417 and sprinkle¦72420 it onto the tent¦72423 and all the containers \add in it\add* and everyone¦72431 who lives in it or who touched¦72438 the body¦72443 or the bone or grave¦72445.
\v 19 On the third¦72453 day, that ‘clean¦72448’ man must sprinkle¦72447 \add ≡that water¦72462\add* on the ‘unclean’ ones, and then¦72447 must purify¦72456 them on the seventh day. Then¦72447 he \add himself\add* must wash his clothes¦72460 and bathe¦72461, and will be ‘unclean’ until that evening¦72464.
\p
\v 20 “ ‘Anyone¦72481 who's ‘unclean’ and¦72466 doesn't purify¦72471 themself, that person¦72466 will be \add ?≈permanently removed from the camp\add* because they've made Yahweh's sanctuary¦72480 ‘unclean’. They didn't¦72470 sprinkle¦72487 that purifying water¦72483 on themself, so they \add remain\add* ‘unclean’.
\v 21 That will be a \add ≈permanent\add* regulation¦72495. The person who's had the purifying water sprinkled on¦72504 them must¦72492 wash their clothes¦72502, and¦72492 any person who \add ≈sprinkles\add* the water will be ‘unclean¦72506’ until¦72507 that evening¦72509.
\v 22 Anything touched by an ‘unclean’ person becomes ‘unclean’, and¦72519 anyone¦72519 who touches¦72520 an ‘unclean’ person will become ‘unclean’ until¦72522 that evening¦72524.
\c 20
\s1 Water from the Kadesh rock
\rem /s1 The Waters of Meribah; Events at Kadesh; Moses Strikes the Rock; Water From the Rock
\r (Exo. 17:1-7)
\p
\v 1 Then in¦72537 the first¦72538 month¦72537 \add of the next year\add*, all the \add ≈Israelis¦72530\add* entered the Tsin¦72536 \add (‘Thorny’ or ‘Thirsty’)\add* wilderness¦72534 and the people \add ≈camped\add* at¦72537 Kadesh¦72541. \add While they were\add* there, Miryam died, and was buried¦72545 there.
\p
\v 2 \add ≈However,\add* there was no water¦72551 \add ≈to drink,\add* \add ≈so the people\add* came against¦72557 Mosheh¦72556 and¦72548 Aharon\x + \xo 20:2-13: \xt Exo 17:1-7.\x*
\v 3 and¦72561 complained, “\add ≈It¦72565 would have been better if we'd died¦72569 in¦72570 front¦72572 of Yahweh¦72573 along with¦72570 our¦72571 relatives\add* \add back there\add*.
\v 4 Why did you two bring¦72576 Yahweh's people here to die¦72585 in this wilderness¦72583, along with our¦72588 livestock¦72588?
\v 5 Why did you bring us out of Egypt¦72592 to bring us to this miserable place? There's no \add ≈grain\add* or figs¦72604, and¦72590 no grapes or pomegranates¦72606. There's \add not even\add* water¦72607 to drink¦72609!”
\v 6 Then¦72611 Mosheh¦72612 and Aharon went¦72611 from \add there\add* in front¦72614 of the people to the entrance¦72618 to the \add ≈sacred\add* tent¦72619, where they¦72621 fell \add ≈to their knees with their faces¦72624 to the ground\add*, and Yahweh's brilliance appeared¦72625 to them.
\p
\v 7 Then Yahweh¦72633 told Mosheh¦72636,
\v 8 “Take \add &Aharon's\add* staff¦72642, then the two of you must¦72650 command \add that\add* rock to \add ≈pour out\add* water. Then water will come out of it, and both the people and the animals will \add have plenty to\add* drink¦72664.”
\p
\v 9 \add ≈So¦72672\add* Mosheh¦72673 took¦72672 the staff¦72676 from \add ≈Yahweh's¦72678 residence\add* like he was told¦72680 to.
\v 10 Then¦72682 \add *the two of them\add* gathered¦72682 the people in front¦72690 of the rock and¦72682 told them, “Listen now \add ≈you bunch of rebels¦72697\add*—do we have to bring¦72702 water¦72704 out of this rock for you?”
\v 11 Then¦72706 Mosheh¦72707 raised¦72706 \add ≈the staff¦72715\add* and hit the rock¦72714 twice, and water¦72718 \add ≈gushed\add* out, and so the people and their¦72722 animals were able to drink.
\p
\v 12 Then Yahweh¦72726 \add ≈scolded\add* Mosheh¦72729 and Aharon, “Because you two \add ≈publicly demonstrated that\add* you didn't¦72734 believe¦72736 \add ≈that what I say is absolute truth\add*, therefore you two won't¦72734 lead this community into the land that I've¦72754 given¦72754 them.”
\p
\v 13 \add ≈That spring was named\add* ‘Merivah’ \add (meaning ‘Quarrelling’)\add* because that was where the \add ≈Israelis¦72763\add* argued with¦72770 Yahweh¦72768, and \add ≈where he demonstrated his absolute truthfulness to\add* them.
\s1 Edom's king refuses the Israelis' passage
\rem /s1 The King of Edom Refuses to Let Israel Pass; Passage through Edom Refused; The approach to the promised land; Edom Denies Israel Passage; Edom Refuses Israel Passage
\p
\v 14 Then from there in Kadesh¦72776, Mosheh¦72774 sent¦72773 messengers¦72775 to Edom's¦72780 king¦72779 to \add ≈ask\add* him, “This \add message is from\add* your \add ≈Israeli relatives\add*. You \add ≈are already aware\add* of all the hardship¦72790 \add ≈that¦72791 we've been through\add*—
\v 15 \add how\add* our ancestors¦72795 went¦72794 down to Egypt¦72796 and¦72794 \add ≈lived¦72797 there for many years\add*, \add ≈but¦72794 then¦72794\add* the Egyptians \add ≈mistreated¦72801\add* \add *them\add*.
\v 16 \add ≈However,\add* \add when\add* we cried¦72806 out to Yahweh¦72809 and he heard \add ≈us\add* and sent¦72812 a messenger¦72813 and brought¦72814 us out of Egypt¦72815, and now we're in¦72818 Kadesh¦72818 town¦72819 at¦72818 the \add southern\add* border of your territory¦72821.
\v 17 \add Now\add* please¦72825 let us pass through your \add ≈country\add*. We won't go¦72837 through the countryside¦72829 or the vineyards¦72830, and we won't drink¦72832 water¦72833 from any well. We'll stay on¦72826 the king's highway without turning to the right¦72840 or the left, until¦72842 after we've \add ≈exited\add* at¦72826 your \add northern\add* border.
\p
\v 18 \add ≈But¦72848\add* Edom's¦72850 \add king\add* \add ≈replied\add*, “You can't¦72851 pass¦72852 through my country. \add ≈If you do try to enter\add*, \add ≈I'll send my swordsmen¦72856 out against¦72858 you\add*.”
\p
\v 19 The \add ≈Israelis¦72862 reiterated\add*, “We'll \add ≈stay\add* on¦72866 the highway¦72866, and¦72860 if we or our¦72880 livestock¦72873 drink¦72871 \add any of\add* your water¦72870, then¦72860 we'll \add ≈pay what it's worth so that's no big deal\add*. \add ≈Just let us walk\add* through¦72881.”
\p
\v 20 \add ≈Again\add* \add @the king\add* \add ≈responded¦72883\add*, “You may not pass¦72885 through¦72885.”
\p Then¦72883 Edom¦72887 \add ≈sent a large, heavily-armed contingent to intimidate them\add*,
\v 21 and because they'd been refused¦72894 passage through their territory¦72902, the \add ≈Israelis\add* turned¦72903 around \add and went via a longer, less direct route\add*.
\s1 Aharon's death
\rem /s1 The Death of Aaron
\p
\v 22 \add ≈So\add* the \add ≈Israelis¦72913\add* left¦72908 Kadesh¦72909 and went¦72910 to Mt¦72918. Hor¦72917.
\v 23 \add *There\add* near the Edom¦72935 border¦72932, Yahweh¦72921 told Aharon and¦72920 Mosheh¦72924,
\v 24 “Aharon will be \add ≈taken to join his ancestors\add* because he won't¦72944 not enter the land that I have given¦72950 to the \add ≈Israelis¦72951\add*, because you two rebelled¦72956 against¦72956 \add ≈what I said at\add* the Meribah¦72961 \add ≈rock that gave¦72950 water¦72960\add*.
\v 25 Take Aharon and his son Eleazar¦72969 and \add ≈climb\add* up Mt¦72974. Hor¦72973 \add together\add*,
\v 26 then¦72976 remove \add ≈his high priest's uniform\add* and put it on his son Eleazar¦72986. \add ≈After that,\add* Aharon will die¦72990 there¦72991 and go to join his ancestors.”
\p
\v 27 \add ≈So¦72993\add* Mosheh¦72994 \add ≈followed Yahweh's¦72997 instructions¦72996\add* and¦72998 \add @the three of them\add* \add ≈climbed\add* Mt¦73002. Hor¦73001 as the \add ≈people\add* watched.
\v 28 Then¦73008 Mosheh removed Aharon's \add ≈uniform\add* and put it on¦73025 his son Eleazar. Aharon died¦73022 there¦73024 at¦73025 the top of the mountain, and then¦73008 Mosheh and Eleazar went \add back\add* down.\x + \xo 20:28: \xt Exo 29:29; Num 33:38; Deu 10:6.\x*
\v 29 When¦73034 the \add ≈assembled people realised¦73034\add* that Aharon had died¦73039, all the \add ≈Israelis¦73048\add* mourned¦73041 for thirty¦73045 days for him.
\c 21
\s1 The defeat of Canaanites
\rem /s1 Victory over the Canaanites; The Bronze Serpent; Arad Destroyed
\p
\v 1 \add ≈When\add* Kanaanite king¦73054 of Arad¦73056 who lived by the wilderness, heard that Yisrael¦73061 was coming on¦73065 the Atarim¦73063 road, he \add ≈attacked them\add* and captured¦73066 \add ≈some prisoners\add*.\x + \xo 21:1: \xt Num 33:40.\x*
\v 2 Then¦73071 the \add ≈Israelis promised\add* Yahweh¦73074, “If you help us defeat \add *them\add*, then¦73071 we'll \add ≈completely destroy¦73085 their¦73088 towns (instead of looting them) as a way of offering them to you\add*.”
\v 3 Yahweh listened¦73090 to \add ≈what they said\add* and \add ≈enabled them to defeat\add* those Kanaanites, then¦73090 they dedicated the towns \add to Yahweh\add* and destroyed¦73098 them, and they named that area ‘Hormah¦73107’ \add (which means ‘Destruction’)\add*.
\rem /s1 The Snake Made of Bronze; The Bronze Snake
\p
\v 4 Then they¦73110 \add all\add* left¦73110 Mt¦73112. Hor¦73111 by the road \add ≈going towards the Red\add* Sea to go¦73117 around¦73117 Edom¦73121, \add ≈but¦73110\add* the people¦73125 became¦73122 impatient¦73122 on¦73126 the way¦73126\x + \xo 21:4: \xt Deu 2:1.\x*
\v 5 and they started to grumble against God¦73130 and against Mosheh¦73131, “Why did you two bring us \add ≈out of\add* Egypt¦73134 \add just\add* to die¦73135 in¦73130 the wilderness¦73136, because there's¦73138 no bread and no water¦73141, and our¦73142 \add ≈insides detest that tasteless\add* ‘stuff’?”\x + \xo 21:5-6: \xt 1Cor 10:9.\x*
\v 6 \add ≈So¦73147\add* Yahweh¦73148 sent \add ≈poisonous¦73151\add* snakes¦73151 into the people, and many \add ≈Israelis¦73161\add* were bitten and died.
\p
\v 7 The people came to Mosheh and \add ≈begged\add*, “We've \add ≈done wrong\add* by speaking out against Yahweh and against you. Pray to Yahweh \add for us\add* to get him to take the snakes¦73183 away.” \add ≈So¦73163\add* Mosheh prayed¦73184 on¦73173 the peoples' behalf,
\v 8 and Yahweh¦73190 told \add *him\add*, “Make¦73193 \add a model of\add* a snake and put it \add up\add* on a pole, and \add ≈so that anyone¦73205 who gets\add* bitten¦73205, can see¦73206 it and live¦73208.”
\v 9 \add ≈So¦73210\add* Mosheh¦73211 made a snake out of bronze and \add ≈attached it\add* \add to the top\add* of a pole, and \add ≈anyone¦73225 who was bitten¦73221 by a snake\add* would \add ≈recover when\add* they looked¦73226 towards the bronze snake.\x + \xo 21:9: \xt 2Ki 18:4; Yhn 3:14.\x*
\s1 Going around Edom via Moav
\rem /s1 From Mount Hor to the Valley of the Moabites; The Journey to Moab; Israel's Journey to Moab
\p
\v 10 Then¦73233 the \add ≈Israelis¦73235\add* set off and¦73236 camped¦73236 at¦73237 Ovot¦73237.
\v 11 \add ≈When¦73239\add* they left¦73239 Ovot, they camped¦73241 at¦73242 Iyey-Haavarim in¦73242 the wilderness¦73244 \add ≈near\add* Moav's eastern border.
\v 12 From there¦73253 they¦73254 set off and¦73255 camped¦73255 by the Zared riverbed,
\v 13 \add ≈before moving on¦73265\add* and camping at¦73265 \add the north side of\add* the Arnon \add river\add*, in¦73265 the wilderness¦73265 that¦73264 extends¦73266 from the Amorite¦73269 border. (The Arnon is the border between Moav and the Amorites¦73269.
\v 14 That's why it¦73282 says in the book about Yahweh's battles:
\q1 “Vahev in Sufah¦73289, and the riverbeds there, and the Arnon¦73293 River
\q1
\v 15 and¦73301 the sloping valleys there,
\q1 that¦73297 extend¦73298 to Ar¦73300 \add ≈village\add* along¦73302 Moav's¦73303 border¦73302.”)
\p
\v 16 From there¦73305 they went to the well at Be'er \add (which¦73309 means ‘Well’)\add*, where Yahweh¦73311 told Mosheh¦73312, “Gather the people¦73316, and¦73317 I'll give¦73317 them water¦73319.”
\v 17 \add ≈That's where the Israelis\add* sang this song:
\q1 “\add ≈Come on\add*, well,
\q1 sing for \add @this well\add*.
\q1
\v 18 the well dug by the leaders¦73337,
\q1 ≈the \add ≈top citizens\add* dug it out.
\q1 with¦73341 their sceptres¦73341 and their staffs¦73342.”
\p From that¦73336 wilderness¦73343, \add the people¦73340 went on¦73341\add* to Mattanah¦73344,
\v 19 then¦73346 through Nahaliel¦73347 and¦73348 on to Bamot¦73349
\v 20 and¦73351 from \add *there\add* to the valley¦73352 in¦73354 the Moav countryside \add ≈where Mt. Pisgh rises above\add* the desert.
\s1 Kings Sihon and Og defeated
\rem /s1 Victory over King Sihon and King Og; King Sihon Defeated; Defeat of Sihon and Og; Victory over Sihon and Og
\r (Deu. 2:26–3:11)
\p
\v 21 Then Yisrael¦73366 sent¦73365 messengers¦73367 to the Amorite¦73373 King¦73371 Sihon¦73370,
\v 22 “Let us pass through¦73392 your \add ≈country\add*. We won't turn off into any field¦73380 or vineyard¦73381. We won't \add ≈take\add* water¦73384 from any well. We'll \add ≈stay on¦73377\add* the king's \add ≈highway¦73386\add* until¦73389 we've \add ≈exited at¦73377\add* your \add northern\add* border.”
\v 23 \add ≈However\add* \add King\add* Sihon¦73398 \add ≈refused them permission¦73397\add*, then¦73395 \add *he\add* \add ≈took his whole army\add* into the wilderness¦73414 to meet Yisrael¦73401, and¦73395 they attacked \add *them\add* at¦73403 Yahats \add village\add*.
\v 24 \add ≈Nevertheless,\add* Yisrael¦73421 defeated¦73420 them \add ≈in battle\add* and¦73420 took¦73425 possession¦73425 of his land from the Arnon¦73429 \add river\add* up as far as Yabok \add ≈where the Ammonites' border¦73439 was well fortified\add*.
\v 25 \add ≈So¦73443\add* Yisrael¦73444 took those Amorite¦73455 cities \add ≈including¦73450\add* Heshbon¦73456 and \add ≈the surrounding villages¦73459\add*, and \add started\add* living in¦73456 them.
\v 26 (Heshbon¦73462 was where the Amorite¦73466 King¦73465 Sihon¦73464 lived, as he'd \add previously\add* fought against¦73470 the former¦73472 king of Moav¦73471 and \add ≈captured\add* all his land down as far as the Arnon¦73482 \add river\add*.
\v 27 That was why the \add ≈poets¦73488\add* say¦73487,
\q1 “Come to Heshbon¦73490—let it be rebuilt¦73491.
\q1 ≈Let \add King\add* Sihon's¦73494 city¦73493 be established¦73492
\q1
\v 28 because fire¦73498 went¦73499 out from Heshbon¦73500,
\q1 ≈flame¦73501 from Sihon's¦73503 city¦73502.
\q1 It consumed¦73504 Ar¦73505 in Moav,
\q1 \add and\add* the citizens¦73507 on Arnon's¦73509 hilltops.\x + \xo 21:28-29: \xt Jer 48:45-46.\x*
\q1
\v 29 Moav, you¦73515 \add ≈won't end well\add*.
\q1 ≈Kemosh's people¦73516 have perished¦73515.
\q1 He's made his sons¦73520 into fugitives¦73521,
\q1 ≈and¦73522 given his daughters¦73522 over to captivity¦73523
\q1 by the Amorite King¦73524 Sihon¦73526.
\q1
\v 30 We've \add ?≈overpowered\add* them.
\q1 Heshbon¦73530 has perished¦73529 as far as Divon¦73533
\q1 ≈and¦73534 shattered Nofah¦73537 as far as Medeva.)
\p
\v 31 \add ≈So¦73544 the Israelis¦73545\add* lived in the Amorite¦73547 \add ≈region¦73546\add*
\v 32 and Mosheh¦73550 sent¦73549 \add some men\add* to spy out Yazer¦73554, and the captured¦73555 \add ≈its¦73556 villages¦73556\add* and \add ≈drove\add* the Amorites¦73561 out from there¦73564.
\rem /s1 King Og Defeated
\p
\v 33 Then¦73566 they turned¦73566 and went up the road \add towards\add* Bashan, \add ≈but¦73566\add* Bashan's¦73569 King¦73572 Og¦73571 came out with his army to meet them, and \add ≈attacked them at\add* Edrei¦73581.
\v 34 Yahweh¦73584 said¦73583 to Mosheh¦73587, “Don't be afraid of him because I've¦73594 given¦73594 him and all his people¦73600 and his land to you, and you'll \add be able to\add* do to him what you did to the Amorite¦73610 King¦73609 Sihon¦73608 who lived at¦73593 Heshbon¦73613.”
\v 35 \add ≈So¦73615\add* they \add ≈overcame\add* \add @King Og\add* and his sons¦73619 and all his people¦73624 until¦73625 there were no remaining survivors¦73631, then¦73615 they took¦73632 possession¦73632 of \add #their\add* land.
\c 22
\s1 King Balak sends for Bileam
\rem /s1 Israel in the plains of Moab; Balak Summons Balaam to Curse Israel; The King of Moab Sends for Balaam; Balak Sends for Balaam; Balak Summons Balaam
\p
\v 1 Then¦73637 the \add ≈Israelis¦73639\add* set off for the Moav plains¦73641, and¦73640 they camped¦73640 there across the river from Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 2 The \add Moabite King\add* Balak¦73649 (Tsipor's son), saw¦73648 everything that Yisrael¦73659 had done to the \add #Amorites\add*,
\v 3 and¦73662 when he \add ≈realised\add* that the \add ≈Israelis¦73674\add* were very numerous¦73668, the Moabite \add people\add* became sick with fear.
\v 4 and¦73696 \add *they\add* told the elders¦73681 at Midyan, “Now \add ≈all that lot\add* will \add ≈devour\add* everything that's around¦73690 us, \add just\add* like a cow¦73692 \add ≈completely cleans out\add* a green¦73694 field¦73695.”
\p \add ≈Now\add* Tsipor's son Balak¦73696 was Moav's king¦73700 at that time¦73702,
\v 5 and he sent¦73705 messengers¦73706 to Beor's¦73712 son Bileam \add (Balaam¦73709)\add* at Petor¦73713 (which¦73714 was their tribal land near the \add Euphrates\add* river¦73717). He \add ≈requested help\add*, saying, “Listen, \add ≈there's a population here\add* that¦73714 came out from Egypt¦73729. Wow, they've covered¦73731 the \add ≈entire surface in this region¦73718\add* and they're living¦73737 \add ≈opposite\add* me.\x + \xo 22:5: \xt Num 31:8; 2Pe 2:15-16; Jude 11.\x*
\v 6 \add ≈So¦73740\add* now please¦73743 \add ≈come¦73741 and\add* curse this people¦73749 group for me because they are more numerous than us, \add then¦73740\add* perhaps¦73756 I'll¦73757 be able to \add ≈attack\add* them and drive¦73761 them out of the \add ≈area\add*, because I know¦73766 that¦73772 anyone you bless will be blessed, and those who you curse will be cursed.”
\p
\v 7 \add ≈So¦73776\add* the elders from Moav and from Midyan departed¦73776 \add ≈carrying the fees for divination¦73781 with¦73782 them\add*, and they¦73783 went¦73783 to Bileam and \add ≈passed\add* Balak's¦73790 words¦73789 on¦73782 to him.
\v 8 \add @Bileam\add* told them, “Stay here tonight, and \add in the morning\add*, I'll¦73797 bring¦73797 you back \add ≈answer, depending on what\add* Yahweh¦73802 tells me,” and \add so\add* the Moav leaders¦73805 stayed \add there\add* with Bileam.
\p
\v 9 \add That night,\add* God¦73813 came¦73812 to Bileam and¦73817 \add ≈asked\add*, “Who are those men¦73819 with you¦73821?”
\p
\v 10 “Tsipor's son, King¦73832 Balak¦73828 from Moav sent¦73834 me \add <a message\add*,” Bileam \add ≈replied\add*.
\v 11 “\add He said that\add* \add ≈shockingly\add* a people¦73838 group has come out of Egypt¦73840 and has covered¦73841 \add ≈his region\add*. \add He wants me to\add* go \add and\add* curse¦73848 them for \add ≈him, so that he'll be able to attack them and drive¦73856 them out of that area\add*.”
\p
\v 12 Then¦73858 God¦73859 told Bileam, “Don't go¦73864 with them—you mustn't curse¦73867 \add &those\add* people¦73870, because they're blessed¦73872.”
\v 13 The next morning¦73877, Bileam \add ≈went over\add* and¦73875 told Balak's¦73882 \add ≈messengers\add*, “Go \add back\add* to your \add ≈place\add*, because Yahweh¦73889 has refused¦73888 to \add ≈let\add* me go with¦73877 you.”
\v 14 \add ≈So¦73894\add* the Moav leaders¦73895 \add ≈stood up\add* and went¦73897 back to \add King\add* Balak¦73900, and told \add <him\add*, “Bileam¦73903 refused¦73902 to come¦73904 with us.”
\p
\v 15 \add ≈However¦73909,\add* Balak sent \add back\add* a \add ≈larger group of leaders¦73911 who were even more senior than the first ones\add*,
\v 16 and they went¦73916 and told Bileam, “Tsipor's son \add King\add* Balak¦73924 says¦73923, ‘Please don't¦73928 \add ≈refuse to come here\add*,
\v 17 because I'll¦73945 honour you highly and do anything that you tell me to. \add ≈Just¦73938\add* please¦73948 come¦73946 and curse¦73949 this population for me.’ ”
\p
\v 18 “\add Even\add* if Balak gave me a houseful¦73970 of gold¦73972 and¦73956 sliver,” Bileam told Balak's¦73962 servant¦73961, “I \add still\add* couldn't go¦73975 \add ≈against Yahweh's instructions, even if it was just to do something\add* small¦73982.
\v 19 \add ≈However,\add* please¦73988 do stay here tonight, and¦73994 \add ≈I'll find out if Yahweh¦73998 might have anything else\add* to say to me.”
\p
\v 20 \add ≈That\add* night¦74008, God¦74003 came¦74002 to Bileam and told him, “If those men¦74016 have come¦74015 to summon you, \add ≈get ready\add* and¦74002 go¦74018 with them, \add ≈except that you must¦74026 only give the message¦74023 that I'll¦74026 tell\add* you.”
