\v 21 \add ≈So¦74031\add* in¦74033 the morning¦74033, Bileam \add ≈got ready\add* and saddled¦74034 his donkey¦74037, and went¦74038 with¦74033 the Moav leaders¦74041.
\s1 The donkey talks
\rem /s1 Balaam and His Donkey; Balaam, the Donkey, and the Angel
\p
\v 22 \add ≈However,\add* God¦74047 \add ≈got angry\add* because he'd gone, and¦74044 Yahweh's messenger¦74053 \add ≈stood¦74052 in¦74055 the middle of the road¦74055 to block them\add*. \add ≈As\add* \add @Bileam\add* rode on¦74055 his donkey¦74062, accompanied by his two¦74063 servants¦74064,
\v 23 the donkey saw Yahweh's messenger¦74071 \add ≈standing¦74073 there holding a sword¦74075 in¦74074 the middle of the road\add* and turned¦74078 off the road and went into a field¦74084. \add ≈So¦74067\add* Bileam whacked the donkey and forced it back onto the road.
\v 24 Then¦74093 Yahweh's¦74095 messenger¦74094 moved to a place where the road was very narrow¦74096, with¦74096 vineyard¦74097 walls on¦74096 each side of the road.
\v 25 \add ≈When¦74103\add* the donkey¦74104 saw¦74103 Yahweh's messenger¦74107, it \add ≈squeezed\add* close by the wall, and¦74103 \add in doing so\add*, \add ≈squashed\add* Bileam's foot¦74116 against the wall, \add ≈so\add* he whacked it again.
\v 26 Then¦74124 Yahweh's¦74127 messenger¦74125 went past again and¦74124 stood¦74129 in¦74130 a narrow¦74131 place¦74130 on the road where¦74132 there¦74133 was no \add room¦74130\add* to \add ≈get past on either side\add*.
\v 27 \add This time, when\add* the donkey saw the messenger¦74144, it lay down on the ground with Bileam sitting on top of it. Bileam \add ≈got very angry\add* and¦74140 whacked the donkey again with his staff¦74157.
\v 28 Then¦74159 Yahweh¦74160 \add ≈enabled the donkey¦74164 to speak, and¦74165 it asked\add* Bileam, “What did I do to you that you beat me these three¦74174 times?”
\p
\v 29 “Because \add ≈you've¦74181 been messing me around\add*!” Bileam \add ≈shouted\add*. “If only \add ≈I'd been carrying a sword¦74186, then¦74177 I would have killed¦74190\add* you!”
\p
\v 30 “Aren't I your donkey that you've¦74202 ridden¦74202 \add ≈all your life\add*?” the donkey \add ≈asked\add* Bileam. “Have I ever \add ≈done anything like that to you before\add*?”
\p And he said, “No.”
\p
\v 31 Then¦74217 Yahweh uncovered¦74217 Bileam's eyes¦74221 and he saw¦74223 Yahweh's messenger¦74226 standing¦74228 \add in the middle of\add* the road¦74229 with¦74229 his sword¦74230 in his hand¦74232, and \add @Bileam\add* \add ≈fell to his knees and kept bowing his face¦74235 to the ground\add*.
\v 32 Yahweh's angel \add ≈asked\add* him, “\add ≈Why did you strike¦74244 you donkey¦74247 those three¦74249 times? Listen, I came¦74253 personally to oppose you\add* because \add ≈you're choosing a very dangerous path¦74258 as far as I'm concerned¦74241\add*.
\v 33 Your donkey saw me and¦74261 \add ≈avoided me\add* those three¦74266 times—if it hadn't I certainly would have killed¦74276 you already, \add ≈but¦74261 I would have let the donkey live\add*.”
\p
\v 34 “\add Yes,\add* I've¦74286 \add ≈done wrong\add*,” Bileam said¦74280 to Yahweh's messenger¦74284, “because I didn't¦74288 know that you were \add ≈waiting\add* for me \add there\add* on¦74294 the road¦74294. \add ≈But¦74280\add* now, if \add ≈you don't¦74288 want me to continue\add*, I'll¦74300 return \add ≈home again\add*.”
\p
\v 35 “\add ≈Continue on\add* with those men¦74312,” Yahweh's angel told Bileam, “\add ≈but¦74303 make sure that you only pass on the message¦74316 that I give\add* you.” \add ≈So¦74303\add* Bileam \add ≈carried on\add* with Balak's¦74328 leaders¦74327.
\s1 Balak welcomes Bileam
