\p
\v 36 \add ≈When¦74330\add* \add King\add* Balak¦74331 heard that Bileam was coming, he went¦74335 out to meeting him at¦74347 a city¦74339 in¦74347 Moav that was on¦74347 his border¦74344 beside the Arnon¦74345 \add river\add*.
\v 37 \add *He\add* \add ≈asked\add* Bileam, “Didn't I send \add ≈an urgent¦74356 message\add* to summon you? Why didn't¦74355 you come¦74365 \add then¦74350\add*? \add ≈Did you think I couldn't pay you enough\add*?”
\p
\v 38 “Look, I've¦74379 come¦74379 \add now\add*,” Bileam \add ≈answered\add* Balak¦74376, “\add ≈but¦74372 can I say whatever I want\add*? \add No,\add* \add ≈I have to deliver\add* whatever message¦74386 God¦74389 \add ≈gives me\add*.”
\v 39 \add So¦74394\add* then¦74394 Bileam went¦74394 to Kiryat-Hutsot with Balak¦74398,
\v 40 \add ≈where\add* Balak¦74404 sacrificed¦74403 sheep¦74406 and cattle¦74405, and \add ≈gave\add* \add some of the meat\add* to Bileam¦74408 and to the leaders¦74409 who were with \add #them\add*.
