\p
\v 1 Then¦74428 Bileam said¦74428 to \add King\add* Balak¦74432, “\add Get them to\add* build¦74433 seven altars¦74438 for me \add ≈here\add*, and prepare¦74439 me seven bulls¦74443 and seven rams.”
\p
\v 2 \add ≈So¦74447\add* Balak¦74448 did what Bileam had \add ≈instructed\add*, then¦74447 \add ≈the two of them\add* offered up a bull¦74455 and¦74447 a ram on¦74457 \add each\add* altar¦74457.
\v 3 Then Bileam told Balak¦74461, “\add ≈You stand¦74462 here beside\add* your burnt¦74465 offering¦74465, and I'll \add ≈move away\add*. Perhaps Yahweh¦74469 will \add ≈want\add* to meet me, and then¦74459 I'll \add ≈tell you whatever¦74472\add* he shows¦74474 me.” Then he went¦74477 to a bare hilltop
\v 4 \add ≈where\add* God¦74481 met \add *him\add*, and \add @Bileam\add* told him, “I \add ≈organised\add* seven¦74489 altars and offered¦74492 up a bull¦74493 and a ram on¦74495 \add each\add* altar¦74495.”
\p
\v 5 Then¦74497 Yahweh¦74498 \add ≈gave Bileam a message¦74499\add* and told \add <him\add*, “Go back to Balak¦74506 and tell \add <him\add* that.”
\v 6 \add ≈So¦74510\add* he went back to \add @Balak\add* \add ≈who\add* was \add ≈still\add* standing¦74513 by his burnt¦74516 offering¦74516 \add ≈along with\add* all of Moav's¦74521 officials.
\p
\v 7 \add ≈So¦74523\add* \add @Bileam\add* \add ≈gave his pronouncement\add*,
\q1 “\add It's\add* Balak¦74530 has brought¦74529 me \add here\add* from Aram¦74528.
\q1 ≈Moav's king¦74531 \add ≡summoned me\add* from the eastern¦74536 mountains¦74534.
\q1 ‘Go curse¦74538 Yakov \add (Jacob)\add* for me,
\q1 ≈and¦74523 go denounce¦74543 Yisrael¦74544.’
