\v 13 Then¦74617 \add King\add* Balak¦74619 told \add @Bileam\add*, “Please come with me to another¦74628 place¦74627 \add ≈that you'll be able to see them from\add*. You won't¦74636 \add be able to\add* see all of \add #them\add*, only the edge \add of that large group\add*, \add ≈but¦74617\add* you'll will curse¦74638 \add @Yisrael\add* for me from there.”
\v 14 \add ≈So¦74643\add* he took¦74643 \add @Bileam\add* to a field¦74644 at¦74656 the top of \add Mt.\add* Pisgah¦74649, and he built¦74650 seven¦74651 altars and offered up a bull¦74654 and a ram on¦74656 \add each\add* altar¦74656.
\p
\v 15 Bileam said¦74658 to \add ≈the king\add*, “You stand¦74662 here beside your burnt¦74666 offering¦74666, while I \add ≈go over there so\add* \add Yahweh\add* \add ≈can meet me\add*.”
\p
\v 16 Then¦74671 Yahweh¦74672 met with¦74678 Bileam and \add ≈gave him a message\add* and told \add >him\add*, “Go back to Balak¦74683, and \add ≈give him that message\add*.”
\v 17 \add ≈So¦74687\add* he \add ≈returned\add* to him where he was standing¦74690 with the leaders¦74694 from Moav¦74695 beside the altar, and¦74687 Balak¦74699 \add ≈asked\add* him, “What did Yahweh¦74703 say?”
\p
\v 18 Then¦74705 \add @Bileam\add* \add ≈gave his speech\add*,
\q1 “\add ≈Look here\add*, Balak¦74709, and¦74705 listen¦74711.
\q1 ≈\add ≈Pay attention\add* to me, son of Tsipor.
\q1
\v 19 God¦74718 doesn't lie because he's not a human¦74717 being,
\q1 ≈and he's not a mortal who might change¦74723 his mind.
\q1 Whatever he's said¦74725, he'll do it.
\q1 ≈Anything he \add ≈promised\add*, he'll make it \add ≈happen\add*.
\q1
\v 20 Listen, I've¦74734 received¦74734 \add a command\add* to bless.
