\v 24 That population stands up like a lioness¦74784,
\q1 ≈and like a lion¦74786, it lifts¦74787 itself¦74787 up.
\q1 It won't¦74788 lie down until¦74790 it's devour¦74792 its prey
\q1 and drunk the blood¦74794 of those¦74796 it killed.”
\p
\v 25 Then¦74799 \add King\add* Balak¦74800 \add ≈scolded\add* Bileam, “Even \add ≈if you won't¦74807\add* curse them, definitely don't¦74807 \em bless\em* them!”
\p
\v 26 “Didn't I \add already\add* tell you¦74823,” Bileam¦74816 answered¦74815 Balak¦74820, “\add ≈that I can only pronounce what Yahweh¦74829 tells me to\add*.”
\s1 Bileam's third prophecy
