\p
\v 1 \add ≈By now,\add* Bileam \add ≈had realised¦74896\add* that Yahweh¦74901 wanted to bless¦74902 \add ≈the Israelis\add*, \add ≈so\add* he didn't¦74906 \add ≈use his usual divinations\add* \add ≈but¦74896 instead, he just looked towards\add* the wilderness¦74917.
\v 2 He \add ≈looked up\add* and¦74920 saw¦74925 Yisrael¦74928 \add ≈in their tents laid out by tribe¦74930\add*. Then¦74920 God's spirit¦74933 came onto him,
\v 3 and¦74936 he \add ≈made his pronouncement\add*,
\q1 “\add This is\add* the declaration of Bileam, son of Beor¦74942—
\q1 ≈the utterance¦74936 of a man¦74944 whose eyes are open.
