\q1 Those who bless, you will be blessed,
\q1 ^\add ≈but\add* those who curse you, will be cursed.\x + \xo 24:9: a \xt Gen 49:9; \xo b \xt Gen 12:3.\x*
\p
\v 10 Then¦75020 \add King\add* Balak¦75023 \add ≈got very angry\add* with Bileam, and he banged his hands¦75030 together¦75027 and said¦75031 \add angrily\add*, “I called you to \em curse¦75036\em* my enemies¦75037, and \add ≈blast you\add*, you've¦75040 actually¦75041 blessed¦75040 \add <them\add* three¦75043 times¦75044 \add now\add*!
\v 11 \add ≈Now get back to where you came from\add*! I said that I'd honour you \add ≈very well\add*, but¦75046 man, Yahweh¦75058 has kept you from any honour!”
\p
\v 12 \add ≈But¦75061\add* Bileam \add ≈replied\add*, “Didn't I also tell the messengers¦75070 that you¦75073 sent¦75073 to me that
\v 13 even if you gave me a house¦75085 full of gold¦75087 and¦75087 silver¦75086, I wouldn't be able \add ≈to say anything other than what Yahweh tells me\add*—whether good¦75096 or evil? Whatever Yahweh tells me, that's what I have to say.
