\v 23 Then¦75226 \add finally,\add* \add @Bileam\add* \add ≈made this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 “Oh dear, who can \add ≈survive\add* when God¦75233 does \add all\add* that?
\q1
\v 24 Ships will come from the Kittim¦75237 coast¦75236 \add (Cyprus)\add*,
\q1 and they'll \add ≈damage\add* Asshur¦75239 and Ever,
\q1 \add ≈but¦75235 they themselves\add* will be destroyed¦75247 as well.”
\p
\v 25 Then¦75249 Bileam \add ≈packed up\add* and went home, and \add King\add* Balak¦75256 also went on his way¦75258.
\c 25
\s1 Yisrael worships Baal at Peor
\rem /s1 Moab Seduces Israel; The People of Israel at Peor; Worship of Baal of Peor
\p
\v 1 \add ≈Meanwhile,\add* \add ≈the Israelis settled down\add* at¦75263 Shittim¦75263, and \add ≈their men started sleeping with¦75263 women from Moav\add*
\v 2 \add ≈who then¦75272\add* invited¦75272 them to sacrifices¦75274 to their \add ≈idols\add*. \add ≈So¦75272\add* \add @the Israelis\add* bowed¦75278 down \add to the idols\add* and¦75272 ate¦75276 \add at the feasts\add*,
\v 3 and¦75286 \add when\add* Yisrael¦75283 consecrated themselves to Baal¦75284-Peor¦75285, Yahweh's anger¦75288 burned towards \add *them\add*.
\v 4 Then¦75292 Yahweh told Mosheh¦75296, “\add ≈Execute\add* all the people's¦75303 leaders and \add ≈display their bodies in broad daylight\add*, and then¦75292 Yahweh's \add ≈anger¦75311\add* might turn¦75309 back away from Yisrael¦75314.”
\p
\v 5 \add ≈So¦75316\add* Mosheh¦75317 to Yisrael's judges¦75320, “\add ≈Each of you must execute your men¦75324 who have joined¦75325 others to serve\add* Baal¦75326-Peor¦75327.”
\p
\v 6 \add ≈Just then¦75329, unbelievably,\add* an \add ≈Israeli¦75332\add* man¦75330 \add ≈came past\add* Mosheh¦75342 and \add ≈all the people¦75347\add* who were \add there outside\add* the \add ≈sacred¦75353\add* tent¦75353 weeping¦75351, and he was bringing a Midyanite woman \add ≈with him\add*.
\v 7 \add ≈When¦75356\add* Pinehas (son of Eleazar¦75360, son of Aharon) saw¦75356 \add <that\add*, he \add ≈came out\add* from among¦75366 the \add ≈gathered people\add*, grabbed a spear¦75369,
\v 8 and followed the \add ≈Israeli¦75374\add* man into \add &his\add* tent. He \add ≈plunged\add* the spear through the two of them—right through the man and the woman's¦75389 belly¦75392, and \add thus\add*, stopped¦75393 the plague¦75394 \add that had started\add* against the \add ≈Israelis¦75374\add*.
\v 9 \add ≈However,\add*, twenty-four thousand¦75404 people had \add already\add* died¦75400 from the plague¦75401.
\p
\v 10 Then Yahweh¦75408 spoke¦75407 to Mosheh¦75411,
\v 11 “Aharon's grandson Pinehas has \add ≈deflected my anger¦75425\add* from the \add ≈Israelis¦75427\add* by \add ≈demonstrating my seriousness about their¦75434 behaviour\add*, \add ≈so now\add* in¦75430 my zeal, I won't¦75435 \add ≈eliminate the Israelis\add*.
\v 12 \add ≈So\add* tell him that I'm \add ≈making\add* a peace¦75453 agreement with him.
\v 13 It's¦75470 an agreement that gives him and his \add ≈descendants¦75457\add* \add ≈the rights to be priests¦75460\add* because¦75462 he was zealous¦75464 \add ≈on his god's behalf\add* and he \add ≈worked towards removing the guilt\add* of the \add ≈people¦75469\add*.”
\p
\v 14 The \add ≈Israeli¦75473\add* man¦75473 \add ≈who was killed\add* with the Midyanite woman was Salu's¦75484 son Zimri¦75481, a \add ≈clan leader¦75485\add* from the Shimeon tribe.
\v 15 The Midyanite woman¦75492 \add ≈who was killed\add* was Kozbi, the daughter¦75496 of Tsur¦75498, a Midyanite clan leader.
\p
\v 16 Then Yahweh¦75509 told Mosheh¦75512,
\v 17 “\add ≈Attack\add* the Midyanites and¦75519 \add ≈destroy\add* them
\v 18 because they were \add ≈treacherously deceiving¦75526\add* you all over the matter of Peor and Kozbi, the daughter¦75540 of one of their leaders¦75542 who was killed¦75545 on¦75526 the day¦75546 of the plague¦75548 at¦75526 \add Mt.\add* Peor.”
\c 26
\s1 The second census
\rem /s1 The Second Census; A Census of the New Generation; Israel's Second Census
\p
\v 1 After \add the incident of\add* the plague, Yahweh¦75562 told Mosheh¦75565 and Aharon's son Eleazar¦75567 the priest¦75571,\x + \xo 26:1-51: \xt Num 1:1-46.\x*
\v 2 “\add ≈Count¦75595 all the Israeli¦75582 people¦75582\add* \add again\add* \add ≈listing all those by their¦75590 clans\add* who're twenty¦75586 and over, and \add ≈capable of going out to battle\add* for Yisrael¦75584.”
\v 3 \add ≈So¦75597\add* there in¦75602 the Moav plains¦75602, across the Yarden¦75606 river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*, Mosheh¦75598 and¦75599 the priest¦75600 Eleazar¦75599 \add ≈gave these instructions\add* to \add @the people\add*,
\v 4 “Yahweh¦75616 has ordered¦75615 \add *us\add* \add ≈to list\add* the names of the \add men\add* who came¦75622 out from Egypt¦75624 who're twenty¦75611 years old or older.
\s1 Reuven's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Reuben
\v 5 Reuven was Yisrael's eldest son, and his descendants¦75629 came via his sons Hanok, Pallu¦75634,
\v 6 Hetsron, and Karmi.
\v 7 Those¦75647 clans¦75646 added up to 43,730 men.
\v 8 Pallu's¦75659 son was Eliav¦75660,
\v 9 and Eliav's son were Nemuel¦75664, Datan, and Aviram. (That was the Datan and Aviram who were the leaders that rebelled\x + \xo 26:9 \xt 16:1-33.\x* against Mosheh¦75678 and Aharon when they joined Korah's¦75684 rebellion against Yahweh¦75688.
\v 10 Then¦75690 the earth¦75691 \add ≈split open\add* and swallowed¦75695 them and Korah¦75699. Yahweh had also sent a fire¦75703 that consumed¦75702 250 men, and they¦75708 became a warning¦75709 sign¦75709.
\v 11 \add ≈However,\add* Korah's¦75713 descendants hadn't died¦75716 \add then¦75711\add*.)
\s1 Shimeon's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Simeon
\p
\v 12 Shimeon's descendants¦75719 came via his sons Nemuel¦75722, Yamin¦75725, Yakin¦75728,
\v 13 Zerah¦75734, and Shaul¦75735.
\v 14 Those¦75741 clans¦75740 added up to 22,200 men.
\s1 Gad's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Gad
\p
\v 15 Gad's¦75749 descendants¦75748 came via his sons Tsefon, Haggit¦75754, Shuni¦75757,
\v 16 Ozni¦75763, Eir,
\v 17 Arod, and Areli¦75771.
\v 18 Those¦75779 clans¦75776 added up to 40,500 men.
\s1 Yehudah's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Judah
\p
\v 19 Yehudah¦75788 \add (Judah)\add* had two sons¦75787 Er¦75789 and Onan¦75790 who died¦75791 \add childless\add* in Kenaan.
\v 20 \add *His\add* descendants¦75798 came via his \add other\add* sons Shelah¦75802, Perets, and¦75797 Zerah¦75808.
\v 21 Perets's descendants¦75813 \add came via his sons\add* Hetsron and¦75812 Hamul¦75819.
\v 22 Those¦75825 clans¦75824 added up to 76,500 men.
\s1 Yissakar's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Issachar
\p
\v 23 Yissakar's \add (Issachar's¦75835)\add* descendants¦75834 came via his sons Tola¦75837, Puah¦75840,
\v 24 Yashuv, and Shimron¦75847.
\v 25 Those¦75853 clans¦75852 added up to 64,300 men.
\s1 Zevulun's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Zebulun
\p
\v 26 Zevulun's descendants¦75862 came via his sons Sered¦75865, Eylon, and Yahle'el.
\v 27 Those¦75877 clans¦75876 added up to 60,500 men.
\s1 Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Manasseh
\p
\v 28 Yosef's¦75886 \add (Joseph's)\add* descendants came via his sons¦75885 Menashsheh \add (Manasseh¦75888)\add* and¦75889 Efrayim.
\v 29 Menashsheh's descendants¦75891 came from his son Makir¦75893 and¦75896 then his son Gilead¦75900.
\v 30 Gilead's¦75907 descendants¦75906 came via his sons Iezer¦75908, Helek¦75911,
\v 31 Asriel, Shekem,
\v 32 Shemida, and¦75925 Hefer¦75925.
\v 33 Hefer's¦75932 son Tselofehad had no sons—only daughters named Mahlah¦75945, Noah¦75946, Hoglah¦75947, Milkah¦75948, and¦75929 Tirtsah.
\v 34 Those¦75953 clans¦75952 added up to 52,700 men.
\s1 Efrayim's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Ephraim
\p
\v 35 Efrayim's descendants¦75963 came via his sons Shutelah¦75967, Beker¦75970, and Tahan¦75973,
\v 36 Shutelah's¦75979 descendants¦75978 came via his son Eran¦75980.
\v 37 Those clans added up to 32,500 men. These¦75984 last two¦75990 totals were \add all\add* Yosef's¦75998 \add (Joseph's)\add* descendants.
\s1 Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Benjamin
\p
\v 38 Benyamin's¦76003 descendants¦76002 came via his sons Bela¦76005, Ashbel¦76008, Ahiram,
\v 39 Shefufam, and Hufam¦76018.
\v 40 Bela's¦76025 descendants¦76023 came via his sons Ard¦76026 and¦76027 Naaman¦76027.
\v 41 Those¦76037 clans¦76038 added up to 45,600 men.
\s1 Dan's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Dan
\p
\v 42 Dan's¦76050 descendants¦76048 came via his son Shuham¦76052.
\v 43 That¦76063 clan had 64,400 men.
\s1 Asher's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Asher
\p
\v 44 Asher's¦76073 descendants¦76072 came via his sons Yimnah, Yishvi¦76078, and Beriah¦76081.
\v 45 Beriah's¦76086 descendants¦76085 came via his sons Hever and Malkiel¦76090.
\v 46 Asher's¦76097 daughter¦76095 was named Serah¦76098.
\v 47 Those¦76104 clans¦76101 added up to 53,400 men.
\s1 Naftali's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Naphtali
\p
\v 48 Naftali's¦76114 descendants¦76113 came via his sons Yahtse'el, Guni¦76119,
\v 49 Yetser, and Shillem¦76126.
\v 50 Those¦76132 clans added up to 45,400 men.
\s1 The census total and the division of land
\rem /s1 The Census Results
\p
\v 51 The¦76144 total of all those tribes counted came to 601,730 men.\f + \fr 26:51 \ft Slightly smaller than the total of 603,550 from the first census, see \xt 1:46.\f*
\p
\v 52 Then Yahweh¦76156 told Mosheh¦76159,\x + \xo 26:52-56: \xt Num 34:13; Josh 14:1-2.\x*
\v 53 “The land should be allocated to those \add clans\add* according to the number¦76166 of their names¦76167, to become their inheritance¦76165.
\v 54 Those with larger¦76169 numbers should receive more, and¦76172 the smaller¦76172 groups receive less, \add i.e.,\add* each inheritance \add ≈depends on the number of family members\add*.
\v 55 \add ≈You must throw\add* lots to determine \add ≈which clan gets which piece of land\add*. \add ≈The lands of the clans must be within their¦76191 tribal lands\add*.
\v 56 \add ≈Then the size of the area that will become\add* their inheritance¦76199 must¦76198 be apportioned according to the \add ≈census numbers\add*.
\s1 Levi's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Levi
\p
\v 57 The listed Levites¦76207 included the clans¦76208 \add from Levi's sons\add* Gershon¦76209, Kohat¦76212, and¦76205 Merari¦76215,
\v 58 which were the Livnites, the Hevronites, the Mahlites, the Mushites, and¦76233 the Korahites. \add ≈Also,\add* Korah fathered¦76234 Amram¦76237
\v 59 \add *whose\add* wife¦76241 was Levi's¦76246 daughter¦76244 Yokeved who'd been born in¦76251 Egypt¦76251. \add #They\add* had two sons Aharon \add (Aaron¦76256)\add* and Mosheh¦76259 \add (Moses¦76259)\add*, and their¦76262 \add older\add* sister¦76262 Miryam \add (Miriam¦76261)\add*.
\v 60 Aharon's \add ≈sons were\add* Nadav, Avihu, Eleazar¦76274, and¦76264 Itamar¦76277,\x + \xo 26:60: \xt Num 3:2.\x*
\v 61 \add ≈but¦76279\add* Nadav and¦76281 Avihu had died¦76279 when they'd offered¦76282 Yahweh¦76287 \add ≈fire¦76283 in¦76282 a disobedient manner\add*.\x + \xo 26:61: \xt Lev 10:1-2; Num 3:4.\x*
\v 62 The male¦76296 \add Levites\add* who were a month¦76299 old or older came to 23,000, but¦76289 they weren't \add ≈included in the above nation-wide count\add* because they \add ≈didn't¦76303 inherit¦76313 land in the same way as other tribes\add*.
\s1 Census summary
\p
\v 63 Those were the \add ≈census results from when\add* Mosheh¦76320 and¦76321 the priest¦76322 Eleazar¦76321 counted the \add ≈Israelis¦76327\add* on the Moav plains¦76329 \add ≈on the east side of\add* the Yarden river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 64 \add ≈None of the men on those lists were on the previous lists done\add* by Mosheh¦76341 and¦76342 the priest¦76343 Aharon when they'd counted¦76340 the \add ≈Israelis¦76348\add* in¦76335 the Sinai¦76351 wilderness¦76350,
\v 65 because Yahweh¦76356 had told them that they'd certainly die \add there\add* in¦76360 the wilderness¦76360 until none of \add @those alive\add* were left other than Yefunneh's¦76372 son Kalev \add (Caleb¦76369)\add* and Nun's¦76376 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*.
\c 27
\s1 Inheritances without sons
\rem /s1 The Daughters of Zelophehad; Zelophehad's Daughters
\p
\v 1 Then the daughters of Tselofehad (son of Hefer¦76384, son of Gilead¦76387, son of Makir¦76390, son of Menashsheh) approached¦76379. \add *Their\add* names¦76400 were Mahlah¦76402, Noah¦76403, Hoglah¦76404, Milkah, and Tirtsah.
\v 2 They stood¦76408 \add ≈in front¦76409 of\add* Mosheh¦76410 and the priest¦76413 Eleazar¦76412 and all the leaders¦76415 and the people \add there\add* at the entrance¦76419 to the \add ≈sacred¦76420\add* tent¦76420, \add and\add* \add ≈asked\add*,
\v 3 “Our father¦76425 died in¦76427 the wilderness¦76427, \add ≈although\add* he wasn't \add ≈part of the group who joined Korah¦76440 to rebel\add* against Yahweh¦76437—it was \add ≈for his own personal disobedience\add* that¦76434 he died. He didn't¦76429 have any sons¦76445
\v 4 \add but\add* why should his family name¦76453 disappear from our clan \add just\add* because he had no sons? \add So\add* give¦76462 us \add ≈some land like\add* our father's¦76455 relatives will be getting.”
\p
\v 5 \add ≈So¦76470\add* Mosheh¦76471 took their case to Yahweh¦76477
\v 6 and¦76480 \add *he\add* \add ≈responded¦76480\add*,
\v 7 “It's right what Tselofehad's daughters¦76488 are saying. You must¦76492 give them \add ≈some land like their father's relatives will be getting\add*. \add ≈Give them whatever would have been given to their father as his\add* inheritance.
\v 8 \add ≈Also¦76509,\add* tell the \add ≈people¦76508\add* that if a man¦76512 dies \add ≈without sons\add*, then¦76506 his inheritance¦76522 should go to his daughter(s).
\v 9 If he had no \add ≈children\add*, then¦76525 \add ≈it should go\add* to his brothers¦76534,
\v 10 and if he has no brothers, then \add ≈it should go\add* to his father's¦76547 brothers.
\v 11 \add ≈However,\add* if his father¦76553 had no brothers¦76552, then¦76549 the inheritance¦76557 \add ≈should go to his nearest¦76559 blood-relative to become his possession¦76562\add*. That will \add ≈become a permanent regulation¦76567\add* for Yisrael¦76566, just as Yahweh¦76571 has commanded¦76570.”
\s1 Yehoshua succeeds Mosheh
\rem /s1 Joshua to Succeed Moses; Joshua Chosen to Lead Israel; Joshua Is Chosen as Successor to Moses; Joshua Appointed Moses' Successor
\r (Deu. 31:1-8)
\p
\v 12 Then Yahweh¦76578 told Mosheh¦76581 \add (Moses¦76581)\add*, “Go up Mt¦76585. Avarim and look at the land that¦76592 I've¦76593 given¦76593 to the \add ≈Israelis¦76594\add*,\x + \xo 27:12-14: \xt Deu 3:23-27; 32:48-52.\x*
\v 13 and then¦76597 you'll \add ≈die and join your ancestors\add* just like your brother¦76609 Aharon¦76608 \add ≈did\add*.
\v 14 \add ≈That's because back\add* in the Tsin wilderness when the \add ≈people complained about water\add*, you two rebelled¦76612 against¦76612 my \add ≈command¦76613 and failed to respect my holiness¦76619\add* in front of them. That was \add when you struck the rock\add* at¦76614 Meribah¦76625 \add near\add* Kadesh¦76626 in the Tsin wilderness.”
\p
\v 15 Then Mosheh¦76633 \add ≈requested\add* Yahweh¦76636,
\v 16 “Yahweh¦76640, \add you\add* \add ≈are the god¦76641 who directs the spirits¦76642 of all humankind\add*, \add so please\add* appoint¦76639 a \add ≈new leader for the Israeli people\add*
\v 17 who will \add ≈stand in front of\add* them and lead them out and bring¦76661 them in \add ≈so\add* \add *they\add* won't¦76662 be like sheep¦76666 without a shepherd¦76671.\x + \xo 27:17: \xt 1Ki 22:17; Eze 34:5; Mat 9:36; Mrk 6:34.\x*
\p
\v 18 Then¦76673 Yahweh¦76674 told Mosheh¦76677, “Get Nun's¦76686 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*, a man¦76687 who has \add &my\add* spirit¦76690 in him, and¦76673 place your¦76695 hands on him \add to indicate the transfer of leadership\add*.\x + \xo 27:18: \xt Exo 24:13.\x*
\v 19 Stand him in front¦76700 of the priest¦76702 Eleazar¦76701 and all the assembly, and \add ≈commission¦76707 him as they watch\add*.
\v 20 Give¦76720 him some of your¦76712 authority¦76712 so that all the \add ≈Israeli¦76719\add* people¦76719 can hear¦76715 \add <it\add*.
\v 21 \add ≈When¦76722\add* \add he needs guidance\add*, he must¦76725 stand¦76725 \add ≈in front¦76730\add* of the priest¦76724 Eleazar¦76723 and ask for Yahweh's decision¦76728 \add to be given via\add* the Urim. Then¦76722 \add @Yehoshua\add* and all the \add ≈people¦76743\add* will go¦76735 in or come¦76739 out as per \add @Yahweh's\add* \add ≈instructions\add*.”\x + \xo 27:21: \xt Exo 28:30; 1Sam 14:41; 28:6.\x*
\v 22 \add ≈So¦76751\add* Mosheh¦76752 did what Yahweh¦76755 had ordered¦76754 him to, and he \add ≈presented\add* Yehoshua¦76760 to the priest¦76764 Eleazar¦76763 and to the entire¦76766 community.
\v 23 \add @Mosheh\add* placed¦76770 his hands¦76773 on¦76779 \add @Yehoshua\add* and¦76770 \add ≈commissioned¦76775\add* him¦76775, just has Yahweh¦76778 had said \add *he\add* should.
\c 28
\s1 The daily offerings
\rem /s1 The Regular Offerings; The Daily Offerings; Daily Offerings
\r (Exo. 29:38-46)
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦76785 told Mosheh¦76788 \add (Moses¦76788)\add*,
\v 2 “Give the \add ≈Israelis¦76794\add* \add <these instructions\add*: Ensure that you¦76796 present¦76806 to me the offerings \add and\add* food for offerings to be burnt at¦76808 the \add ≈proper\add* time¦76808.
\v 3 For¦76816 the \add ≈daily\add* burnt¦76824 offering, present two¦76822 one-year-old, male lambs¦76817 that¦76814 have no¦76821 defects¦76821.
\v 4 One of those lambs must¦76831 be offered in the morning¦76832, and¦76833 the other in \add ≈late afternoon\add*,
\v 5 \add each offered¦76843\add* along with a kilogram of fine flour¦76842 mixed¦76844 with a litre of \add olive\add* oil¦76845.
\v 6 That's the regular burnt¦76850 offering done like the first one at¦76853 Mt¦76853. Sinai¦76854—the soothing¦76856 aroma¦76855 from the fire¦76857 will be pleasing¦76856 to Yahweh¦76858.
\v 7 The drink offering must \add also\add* be one litre for each lamb¦76863. That strong¦76868 drink must be poured out in¦76865 the sacred area as an offering to Yahweh¦76869.
\v 8 \add ≈At the end of the afternoon,\add* offer the second¦76873 lamb¦76872 with the same-sized offerings of flour and¦76879 wine as in the morning¦76878. \add ≈When¦76871 they're burnt,\add* the aroma¦76882 will be pleasing¦76883 to Yahweh¦76884.
\s1 The Rest Day offerings
\rem /s1 The Sabbath Offerings; The Sabbath Offering; Sabbath Offerings
\p
\v 9 “On the Rest Day, \add it must be\add* two one-year-old, male lambs¦76891 with no¦76895 defects¦76895, along with 2 kilograms of fine flour¦76898 mixed¦76900 with oil¦76901, as well as the drink¦76902 offering.
\v 10 That will be burnt every Rest Day, in¦76906 addition to the regular¦76910 \add daily\add* burnt offering and its drink¦76911 offering.
\s1 The new month offerings
\rem /s1 Monthly Offerings; The Monthly Offerings; The Offering on the First Day of the Month
\p
\v 11 “\add ≈On the first day of each month¦76915\add*, you all must¦76916 bring¦76916 Yahweh¦76918 a burnt¦76917 offering¦76917 of two¦76923 young bulls¦76919, one ram, and seven¦76930 one-year-old, male lambs¦76926 with¦76914 no¦76931 defects¦76931.
\v 12 Each bull¦76939 must be offered with three¦76933 kilograms of fine flour mixed with oil, each ram with two¦76941 kilograms,
\v 13 and¦76950 each lamb¦76956 with one kilogram. \add All of that\add* will be a burnt¦76958 offering with an aroma¦76959 that will be pleasing¦76960 to Yahweh¦76962.
\v 14 Their \add respective\add* drink¦76964 offerings¦76964 will be two litres of wine with the bull¦76968, 1.3 litres with the ram, and¦76964 one litre with each lamb¦76974. That will be the burnt¦76977 offering¦76977 \add ≈for the start of each new\add* month¦76980 throughout¦76980 the year¦76981.
\v 15 In addition to those burnt¦76990 offerings and¦76993 drink¦76993 offerings, a male¦76983 goat¦76983 must¦76992 \add also\add* be presented to Yahweh¦76987 as a sin¦76986 offering.
\s1 The ‘pass-over’ offerings
\rem /s1 The Passover; Offerings for the Passover; The Offerings at the Festival of Unleavened Bread; Offerings at Passover
\r (Lev. 23:5-14)
\p
\v 16 “Yahweh's ‘passover¦77002’ \add ceremony will start\add* on¦76996 the 14th of the first¦76997 month \add (Nisan = March/April) each year\add*.\x + \xo 28:16: \xt Exo 12:1-13; Deu 16:1-2.\x*
\v 17 The 15th will be \add the start of\add* the celebration—\add ≈all your bread¦77013 must¦77005 be made without any rising agent\add*.\x + \xo 28:17-25: \xt Exo 12:14-20; 23:15; 34:18; Deu 16:3-8.\x*
\v 18 That first¦77017 day, there's to be a sacred¦77020 assembly¦77018. No \add ≈regular\add* work may be done that day.
\v 19 You¦77031 all must¦77028 offer two¦77036 \add ≈young\add* bulls¦77032, one ram, and¦77028 seven¦77039 one-year-old lambs¦77040 with no¦77043 defects¦77043 to be burnt¦77030 on the fire¦77029.
\v 20 Their \add associated\add* grain¦77047 offerings¦77047 must¦77057 be three¦77051 kilograms of fine flour¦77048 mixed¦77049 with¦77050 \add olive\add* for the bull¦77053, two¦77054 kilograms for the ram,
\v 21 \add and\add* one kilogram for each of the seven¦77064 lambs¦77065.
\v 22 \add ≈Also,\add* bring one male¦77067 goat¦77067 as a sin¦77068 offering¦77068 to make \add ≈yourselves right with God\add*.
\v 23 Those offerings must¦77079 be \em in addition¦77073\em* to the regular¦77078 morning¦77075 offerings
\v 24 \add and\add* must¦77085 be offered for each of the seven¦77087 days¦77088. The aroma¦77091 of those burnt offerings will be pleasing¦77093 to Yahweh¦77094, along with the regular¦77098 burnt offering and its drink¦77100 offering.
\v 25 On the seventh¦77103 day, there's to be \add another\add* sacred¦77106 assembly¦77104. No \add ≈regular\add* work may be done that day.
\s1 Harvest festival offerings
