\p
\v 1 Then Mosheh \add (Moses¦77690)\add* \add ≈gave\add* the \add ≈Israeli¦77693 leaders\add* \add ≈these further instructions¦77698 from\add* Yahweh¦77699,
\v 2 “If a man makes a solemn promise to Yahweh¦77719, or makes a binding vow on his own life, he mustn't dishonour \add ≈what he said\add*—he must follow whatever came out of his mouth.\x + \xo 30:2: \xt Deu 23:21-23; Mat 5:33.\x*
\p
\v 3 If a \add ≈young\add* woman who is \add ≈still living with her parents\add* solemnly promises to Yahweh¦77727 \add <to do something\add*,
\v 4 and \add ≡if\add* her father¦77756 hears her make the binding vow on¦77757 her life and he remains silent, then her vow and \add ≈all her obligations¦77754\add* will stand.
\v 5 \add ≈However,\add* if her father forbids her \add ≈when\add* he hears¦77760 her, then that¦77766 vow and \add ≈its obligations¦77780\add* won't stand, and Yahweh will forgive her, because her father \add ≈stepped in\add*.
\p
\v 6 If¦77809 she¦77803 \add ≈gets engaged or married while a vow or thoughtless promise still holds\add*,
\v 7 and her \add (future)\add* husband¦77824 hears about it and remains silent that¦77830 day, then her vow and or thoughtless promise will stand.
\v 8 \add ≈However,\add* if her \add (future)\add* husband¦77838 forbids her \add ≈when\add* he hears¦77840 her, then that¦77846 vow and \add ≈its obligations¦77845\add* won't stand, and Yahweh will forgive her.
\p
\v 9 \add ≈If¦77875\add* a widow or a woman who has been divorced \add ≈makes a promise, she must¦77859 do what she promised\add*.
\p
\v 10 \add ≈If a married woman\add* makes a solemn promise, or makes a binding vow on her¦77890 own life,
\v 11 and her husband¦77898 hears about it \add ≈but¦77895\add* says nothing and doesn't forbid her, then her vow and \add ≈all her obligations¦77903\add* will stand.
\v 12 \add ≈However,\add* if he actually nullifies it when he hears about it, any promise that¦77924 she pronounced or binding vow on her life, won't¦77914 stand. Her¦77920 husband¦77911 has nullified them and Yahweh will forgive her,
\v 13 \add so\add* every vow and its obligations¦77947 can either be nullified¦77952 or confirmed by her¦77946 husband.
\v 14 If her¦77970 husband¦77970 has stayed silent for \add ≈several days\add*, that will confirm¦77969 all her vows and/or obligations¦77965 because he \add ≈said nothing\add*.
\v 15 \add ≈However,\add* if he \add ≈cancels\add* them \add sometime\add* after he'd heard¦78005 about them, then he will bear her¦77989 guilt.
\p
\v 16 Those are the instructions that Yahweh \add ≈gave\add* Mosheh \add about promises\add* between a man and his wife, \add and\add* between a father and his \add ≈unmarried\add* daughter \add ≈living at home\add*.
\c 31
\s1 Avenging the Midyanites
\rem /s1 Vengeance on the Midianites; Conquest of the Midianites; The Holy War against Midian; War against Midian
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦78042 told Mosheh¦78045 \add (Moses¦78045)\add*,
\v 2 “Avenge¦78048 the Midyanites for what they did to \add you\add* \add ≈Israelis¦78050\add*. After that, you'll \add ≈go to join your¦78058 ancestors\add*.”
\p
\v 3 \add ≈So¦78060\add* Mosheh¦78061 told the people¦78064, “Equip some of your men¦78068 to battle¦78069 against Midyan to \add ≈execute¦78074\add* Yahweh's vengeance¦78075 on¦78078 \add *them\add*—
\v 4 one thousand men from each tribe¦78085 to go to war.”
\p
\v 5 \add ≈So¦78092\add* a thousand men were conscripted¦78090 from each tribe¦78094—twelve thousand equipped¦78099 for battle¦78100
\v 6 and¦78102 Mosheh¦78104 sent¦78102 them off to war. The priest¦78115 Pinehas (Eleazar's¦78114 son) went with them, taking some sacred¦78118 objects as well as the signal trumpets¦78119.
\v 7 Then¦78123 they fought¦78123 Midyan¦78126 just as Yahweh¦78129 had commanded¦78128 Mosheh¦78132, and¦78133 they killed¦78133 every¦78134 male¦78136.
\v 8 \add Among them,\add* they killed five Midyan kings: Evi, Rekem¦78151, Tsur¦78154, Hur¦78157, and¦78138 Reva, in¦78170 addition to Beor's¦78168 son Bileam \add (Balaam¦78165)\add*.
\p
\v 9 The \add ≈Israelis¦78175\add* took the Midyan women¦78178 and children captive¦78172, and took all their cattle¦78186, \add ≈sheep and goats\add*, and all their \add ≈possessions as plunder¦78197\add*,
\v 10 then¦78199 they¦78208 burnt¦78208 down all their cities¦78202 and houses and camps¦78207.
\v 11 They took¦78211 all the spoil¦78216 and plunder¦78220 including¦78217 the people¦78221 and animals back,
\v 12 and brought¦78224 it to Mosheh¦78227 and the priest¦78231 Eleazar¦78230, and to the \add ≈assembled Israelis¦78235\add* who were \add all still\add* camped on the Moav plains¦78252 beside the Yarden river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\s1 Purifying the returning warriors
\rem /s1 The Army Returns; Return from the War
\p
\v 13 Mosheh¦78262 and the priest¦78264 Eleazar¦78263 and all the \add ≈Israeli\add* leaders¦78267 left the camp¦78273 to meet them,
\v 14 \add ≈but¦78275\add* Mosheh¦78276 was angry¦78275 at the top army leaders who were coming back from the battle¦78286.
\v 15 “Why¦78290 did you allow all the women to live¦78291?” \add *he\add* asked them.
\v 16 “They're the \add ≈very ones who did what\add* Bileam \add (Balaam¦78302)\add* \add ≈suggested to urge the people to be unfaithful¦78305\add* to Yahweh at¦78301 Peor¦78311, \add ≈leading to\add* the plague¦78313 \add that struck\add* Yahweh's \add ≈people\add*.\x + \xo 31:16: \xt Num 25:1-9.\x*
\v 17 \add ≈So¦78317 now,\add* kill all the \add ≈boys\add* plus¦78323 every¦78319 woman¦78325 who's \add ≈slept with¦78322 a man\add*—
\v 18 \add ≈spare only the young¦78333, unmarried girls\add* for yourselves¦78342.
\p
\v 19 “Then¦78344 everyone¦78351 who's killed¦78351 someone or touched¦78355 a dead body must stay outside¦78346 the camp for seven days¦78349. On the third¦78359 day, you all must purify¦78357 yourselves¦78357, and¦78344 \add again\add* on¦78356 the seventh day \add but¦78344 this time¦78349\add* including¦78353 your captives¦78363.
\v 20 \add Also,\add* you¦78382 all must¦78382 purify¦78382 all your clothes, plus¦78368 anything \add else\add* made of leather or goats' hair¦78376 or wood.”
\p
\v 21 Then the priest¦78387 Eleazar¦78386 told¦78399 the \add ≈warriors¦78390\add* who'd gone to battle¦78393, “This is what Yahweh¦78400 has instructed¦78399 Mosheh¦78403:
\v 22 Only the gold¦78408, silver¦78411, bronze¦78414, iron, tin, and lead,
\v 23 must pass through fire to make it ‘clean¦78434’. Nevertheless¦78435, it must still be purified¦78438 with the \add special\add* purifying water, along with anything that¦78428 wouldn't \add ≈handle\add* the fire.
\v 24 On the seventh¦78451 day¦78450, you all must¦78448 wash your clothes¦78449 and then¦78448 you'll be ‘clean¦78452’ and \add ≈be allowed to reenter\add* the camp¦78457.
\s1 Dividing the plunder
\rem /s1 Division of the Spoils; Division of the Loot; Disposition of Captives and Booty; Dividing the Spoils
\p
\v 25 Then Yahweh¦78461 told Mosheh¦78464 \add (Moses¦78464)\add*,
\v 26 “You and the priest¦78476 Eleazar¦78475 and the \add ≈tribal leaders\add* must \add ≈list all\add* the plunder \add ≈including¦78473 both\add* human¦78472 and animals that were taken captive¦78471.
\v 27 Then¦78481 you¦78481 must¦78481 divide¦78481 \add *it all\add* out \add equally between the two groups\add*: those¦78486 who went¦78488 out to battle¦78489, and¦78490 all \add the rest of\add* the community¦78493.
\v 28 \add ≈Set aside¦78495\add* a tribute¦78496 for Yahweh¦78497 from \add the plunder of\add* the \add ≈warriors¦78499\add* who fought in the battle¦78502: one from every five-hundred \add captive\add* people, and \add ≡the same\add* from the cattle¦78512 and donkeys¦78515, and from the \add ≈sheep¦78518 and goats\add*.
\v 29 Half of that must¦78521 be given to the priest¦78524 Eleazar¦78523 as the contribution¦78525 to Yahweh¦78526.
\v 30 Then¦78528 from the half \add of the plunder\add* \add given\add* to the \add ≈community\add*, take¦78532 one from every fifty¦78539 \add captive\add* people¦78529, and \add ≡the same\add* from the cattle¦78545 and donkeys¦78548, and from the \add ≈sheep¦78551 and goats\add* and other animals. That's to be given to the Levites¦78557 because they're the ones who look after Yahweh's residence.”
\v 31 \add ≈So¦78563\add* Mosheh and¦78565 the priest¦78566 Eleazar¦78565 did what Yahweh¦78569 had told¦78568 them to do.
\p
\v 32 The remaining¦78576 plunder¦78579 \add after the slaughter of the boys and¦78574 the married women\add* from what the warriors had brought back was: 675,00 sheep¦78582,
\v 33 72,000 cattle¦78593,
\v 34 61,000 donkeys¦78598,
\v 35 and¦78603 32,000 girls \add ≈who hadn't been married\add*.
\v 36 The \add ≈warriors who'd fought\add* got: 337,500 sheep¦78627,
\v 37 \add ≈less\add* 675 that were given to Yahweh¦78641 \add as his tribute¦78640\add*.
\v 38 The cattle¦78650 were 36,000 \add ≈less\add* 72 for Yahweh¦78655.
\v 39 There were 30,500 donkeys¦78659 \add ≈less\add* Yahweh's tribute¦78664 of sixty-one.
\v 40 The \add ≈girls and¦78669 young women\add* were 16,000 \add ≈less\add* 32 for Yahweh¦78675.
\v 41 \add ≈So¦78680\add* Mosheh gave¦78680 Yahweh's contribution¦78685 to the priest¦78688 Eleazar¦78687 as Yahweh had \add ≈instructed¦78690\add* Mosheh.
\p
\v 42 The¦78698 half for the \add ≈community\add* that¦78699 Mosheh¦78701 had divided¦78700 off from the \add ≈warriors¦78704\add*
\v 43 was: 337,500 sheep¦78712,
\v 44 36,000 cattle¦78724,
\v 45 30,500 donkeys¦78729,
\v 46 and¦78735 16,000 \add ≈girls who hadn't been married\add*.
\v 47 From that half for the \add ≈community\add*, Mosheh took¦78741 one from every fifty¦78753 people¦78744 and animals, and gave¦78760 it to the Levites¦78762 who serve in Yahweh's tent¦78765, just as Yahweh had \add ≈instructed¦78768\add* Mosheh.
\p
\v 48 Then¦78774 the \add ≈top army\add* officers¦78778 (the commanders over thousands, and¦78784 the commanders over hundreds¦78785), went to Mosheh¦78777
\v 49 and \add ≈informed\add* \add *him\add*, “\add We¦78790,\add* your¦78791 servants¦78791 have \add ≈counted the soldiers who were under us,\add* and \add ≈none of our men¦78796 are\add* missing¦78802,
\v 50 \add ≈so\add* we've brought¦78806 an offering¦78809 to Yahweh: every¦78811 man who found¦78813 \add ≈something\add* gold¦78816 \add like\add* an armlet¦78817 or bracelets¦78818, signet¦78819 ring or earring¦78820, or necklaces¦78821 \add has donated it\add* to \add ≈make us right with\add* Yahweh.”
\v 51 \add ≈So¦78829\add* Mosheh¦78830 and¦78831 the priest¦78832 Eleazar¦78831 took¦78829 those \add ≈crafted\add* gold¦78835 items¦78838 from them,
\v 52 and the total¦78843 contribution¦78846 of gold¦78845 \add ≈offered\add* to Yahweh¦78849 by the commanders of thousands¦78852 and of hundreds \add ≈weighed around 190 kilograms\add*.
\v 53 Each of the \add ≈warriors¦78865\add* had taken¦78867 \add ≈their own\add* plunder¦78867,
\v 54 and Mosheh¦78872 and the priest¦78874 Eleazar¦78873 took¦78871 the gold¦78877 from the commanders¦78879 of thousands¦78880 and of hundreds¦78881, and brought¦78882 it to the \add ≈sacred¦78886\add* tent¦78886 as a memorial¦78888 for the \add ≈Israelis¦78889\add* \add ≈in front¦78892\add* of Yahweh¦78893.
\c 32
\s1 The tribes who stayed east of Yarden
\rem /s1 The Tribes East of the Jordan; Conquest and Division of Transjordan; The Transjordan Tribes
\r (Deu. 3:12-22)
\p
\v 1 The \add people\add* from the Reuven and Gad¦78904 \add ≈tribes\add* \add had amassed\add* \add ≈a lot of\add* livestock, and they¦78907 \add ≈noticed¦78907\add* that the Yazer¦78911 and Gilead¦78915 \add ≈regions¦78910\add* \add ≈were very suitable\add* for livestock.
\v 2 \add ≈So¦78921\add* \add *their leaders\add* went¦78921 to Mosheh¦78930 and the priest¦78934 Eleazar¦78933 and the \add ≈community¦78938 leaders\add* to say,
\v 3 \add The regions of\add* Atarot, Divon¦78942, Yazer¦78943, Nimrah¦78944, Heshbon¦78945, Elealeh¦78946, Sevam, Nevo, and Beon¦78949
\v 4 are \add in\add* the land \add here\add* that¦78952 Yahweh¦78954 has \add ≈handed over to\add* \add ≈us Israelis¦78956\add*. It's¦78957 \add ideal\add* for livestock, and \add we,\add* your¦78961 servants¦78961, \add ≈raise\add* livestock.
\v 5 If we've \add ≈earnt\add* your favour¦78969, let this land be given¦78971 to your servants¦78976 for \add ≈us to own¦78977\add*, \add rather than forcing us\add* to cross¦78980 over the Yarden \add river with¦78970 all the other tribes\add*.”
\p
\v 6 “It wouldn't be right for your \add ≈fellow Israelis\add* to go¦78993 to war \add ≈while\add* you all \add just\add* stay here,” Mosheh¦78986 told them.
\v 7 “\add ≈So¦78999\add* why do you¦79000 discourage¦79000 \add ≈Israeli¦79005 enthusiasm\add* for crossing over into the land that¦79011 Yahweh¦79015 has given¦79013 them?
\v 8 Your parents did that at¦79020 Kadesh-Barnea when I sent¦79020 them \add in¦79020\add* to \add ≈survey\add* the land.\x + \xo 32:8-9: \xt Num 13:17-33.\x*
\v 9 They went¦79029 as far as the Eshkol \add ≈valley\add* and¦79029 they saw¦79034 the land, \add ≈yet\add* they discouraged¦79038 the \add ≈people¦79042 from\add* entering the land that¦79050 Yahweh¦79054 had given¦79052 them.
\v 10 Yahweh¦79059 \add ≈got very angry\add* that day¦79060, and¦79062 \add ≈promised\add*,
\v 11 ‘From the men¦79068 who came¦79069 out of Egypt¦79070, no man who's twenty¦79072 or older will see¦79067 the land which¦79077 I promised to Abraham¦79079, Yitshak \add (Isaac¦79080)\add*, and Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*, because they're not \add ≈fully with\add* me.
\v 12 \add ≈Only\add* Yefunneh's¦79092 son Kalev \add (Caleb¦79089)\add* and¦79094 Nun's¦79097 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add* \add will enter\add* because they¦79099 \add ≈have believed\add* me.’
\v 13 \add ≈So¦79103\add* Yahweh \add ≈got angry with¦79107\add* Yisrael¦79107, and¦79108 made \add ≈us\add* wander¦79108 in¦79107 the wilderness¦79109 for forty¦79110 years until¦79112 that¦79118 generation¦79117 was \add ≈eliminated\add* who had \add ≈been evil¦79119 as per Yahweh's judgement\add*.
\v 14 \add ≈Now look here!\add* You're \add ≈standing in front of me\add* \add just\add* like your parents—a brood¦79127 of \add ≈disobedient\add* people¦79128 who'll make Yahweh¦79136 more angry with you than he was with your parents!
\v 15 If you all turn¦79142 away from following¦79143 him¦79143, he'll \add ≈abandon¦79146\add* you all in¦79147 the wilderness¦79147 again¦79145, and you will have destroyed¦79148 this \add ≈nation\add*.”
\p
\v 16 \add ≈However, they¦79157 stepped\add* closer to him and said¦79157, “\add First\add* we'll build pens for our animals, and build cities¦79163 for our \add ≈families\add* \add here\add*.
\v 17 Then¦79166 we'll equip¦79167 ourselves¦79167 for war, \add ≈to go ahead of the rest\add* of Yisrael¦79171 until¦79172 we've brought¦79176 them into their¦79179 place¦79179. \add ≈Meanwhile\add* our¦79181 \add ≈families\add* will live in those fortified¦79183 cities¦79182 because \add ≈there'll still be threats from\add* those who live in \add ≈this region\add*.
\v 18 We¦79196 won't return¦79189 to our¦79192 \add ≈homes¦79192\add* until¦79193 every¦79197 \add ≈Israeli¦79195\add* is in possession of his inheritance¦79194.
\v 19 We won't¦79201 take any land \add there\add* on the other¦79204 side of the Yarden \add river\add* or beyond¦79206 because this \add ≈will be\add* our¦79209 inheritance¦79202 here on the eastern¦79213 side.”
\p
\v 20 “If you're \add ≈going to do that\add*,” Mosheh¦79218 \add ≈responded¦79216\add*, “then you all must¦79221 equip¦79228 yourselves¦79228 to \add ≈fight battles¦79231 for\add* Yahweh¦79230,
\v 21 and¦79233 all of \add &your\add* \add ≈armed warriors\add* must¦79233 cross¦79233 the Yarden¦79240 \add ≈to serve\add* Yahweh¦79242 until¦79243 he's driven¦79244 his¦79248 enemies¦79247 out \add ahead of him¦79248\add*.
\v 22 \add Once\add* the land is subdued¦79250 \add ≈before\add* Yahweh, then¦79250 you all can return¦79255. You'll be free of obligation from Yahweh and from Yisrael¦79259, and this land \add here\add* will be your possession¦79264 \add ≈from\add* Yahweh.
\v 23 \add ≈However\add*, if you all don't¦79270 \add ≈help the rest of us\add*, you will be disobeying Yahweh¦79275, and¦79276 \add @your disobedience\add* will \add ≈catch up with you\add*.
\v 24 \add So go ahead and\add* build your cities¦79285 for your \add ≈families\add*, and pens¦79287 for your flocks¦79288, and \add ≈do what you've committed to\add*.”
\p
\v 25 “Your servants¦79303 will do what you've said¦79293,” \add ≈confirmed\add* the \add leaders of\add* the Reuven and¦79297 Gad¦79296 tribes.
\v 26 “Our wives¦79310 and children, and our livestock¦79311 and all our animals¦79314 will remain in cities¦79318 here in the Gilead¦79319 \add region\add*,
\v 27 \add ≈but¦79321\add* we'll equip¦79325 ourselves for battle and¦79321 to cross¦79322 \add <the river\add* to battle for Yahweh¦79328 just as my master¦79331 has spoken¦79332.”
\p
\v 28 \add ≈So¦79334\add* Mosheh¦79336 \add ≈gave instructions¦79334\add* about them to the priest¦79339 Eleazar¦79338, Nun's¦79344 son Yehoshua¦79341, and¦79334 the \add ≈Israeli¦79351 tribal leaders\add*,\x + \xo 32:28-32: \xt Josh 1:12-15.\x*
\v 29 telling them, “If the \add ≈men from Gad¦79361 and Reuven tribes\add* cross¦79358 over the Yarden with you \add ≈and equipped¦79372 ready to fight for\add* Yahweh¦79375 and that land \add ≈is conquered\add*, then¦79353 you must¦79358 give¦79379 them the Gilead¦79384 \add ≈region¦79383 for them to own¦79385\add*.
\v 30 \add ≈However,\add* if they don't¦79389 cross¦79390 over with¦79394 \add the rest of\add* you, then¦79387 \add ≈they'll have to accept\add* land \add ≈to own\add* \add there\add* in¦79394 Kanaan \add (Canaan¦79397)\add*.”
\p
\v 31 “What Yahweh¦79409 has told you, \add &his\add* servants¦79412, that's what we'll do,” the \add ≈leaders of the Gad¦79402 and¦79403 Reuven tribes responded\add*.
\v 32 We'll¦79416 \add ≈send armed men across\add* to Kanaan, equipped¦79418 to fight for Yahweh¦79420. \add ≈However,\add* our¦79425 inheritance¦79425 to own¦79424 will be \add here\add* on this side of the Yarden \add river\add*.”
\p
\v 33 \add ≈So¦79429\add* Mosheh¦79432 gave¦79429 \add <that region\add* to the tribes¦79440 of Reuben¦79437 and Gad¦79435, the half-tribe of Yosef's¦79445 son Menashsheh, \add encompassing\add* the kingdoms of the Amorite¦79451 King Sihon¦79449 and the Bashan's¦79457 King Og¦79455, plus¦79436 the surrounding territories¦79460.
\v 34 The Gadites rebuilt¦79465 Divon¦79471, Atarot¦79474, Aroer¦79476,
\v 35 Atrot¦79480-Shofan¦79481, Yazer¦79484, Yogbehah¦79485,
\v 36 Beyt-Nimrah¦79490, and¦79487 Beyt-Haran¦79490—\add all\add* fortified¦79496 cities¦79495 with pens¦79497 for their flocks.
\v 37 The Reuvenites rebuilt Heshbon¦79505, Elealeh¦79508, Kiriatayim,
\v 38 Nevo¦79514, Baal¦79517-Meon¦79518, and¦79512 Sibmah¦79523, \add ≈but¦79512\add* they¦79531 \add ≈renamed\add* \add some\add* of the cities¦79529.
\p
\v 39 The descendants¦79534 of Menashsheh's son Makir¦79535 went¦79533 to Gilead¦79539 and¦79533 captured¦79540 it—driving out the Amorites¦79544 who \add ≈lived there\add*.
\v 40 \add ≈So¦79549\add* Mosheh¦79550 gave¦79549 Gilead¦79553 to Menashsheh's¦79557 son Makir¦79554, and¦79558 \add his clan\add* lived there.
\v 41 Menashsheh's \add other\add* son Yair went¦79565 and captured¦79566 \add @the Amorite\add* villages and named them ‘Yair's¦79573 Towns’ \add (or ‘Havvot-Yair’)\add*.
\v 42 \add A man named\add* Novah went¦79576 and captured¦79577 Kenat¦79580 and its villages¦79583, and renamed it to ‘Novah’ after himself.
\c 33
\s1 The journey legs from Egypt to Sinai
\rem /s1 The Journey from Egypt to Moab; The Stages of Israel's Journey from Egypt; Stages in Israel's Journey; Remembering Israel's Journey
\p
\v 1 \add @The following\add* are \add the details\add* of the \add ≈stages of Yisrael's journeys¦79591\add* \add starting from\add* when they¦79596 exited Egypt¦79598 \add ≈tribe-by-tribe\add* under Mosheh¦79602 and Aharon's leadership¦79600.
\v 2 Mosheh¦79606, \add ≈acting on Yahweh's¦79614 instructions\add*, had written down their \add ≈departure points\add*, so these¦79615 were \add the legs of\add* their journeys¦79610:
\p
\v 3 The day after¦79628 \add they celebrated\add* the ‘pass-over’ \add ≈(around the end of March)\add*, they left¦79619 Rameses¦79620 city, raising \add ≈one fist\add* in¦79621 full view of all Egypt¦79639 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 4 \add ≈Meanwhile\add*, the Egyptians were burying¦79642 all their oldest sons who'd been struck¦79645 down by Yahweh¦79646 \add ≈who had\add* \add also\add* \add ≈totally humiliated\add* their gods¦79651.
\p
\v 5 After leaving Rameses¦79660, the \add ≈Israelis¦79659\add* \add went\add* to Sukkot and¦79661 camped¦79661 \add there\add*.
\v 6 Then¦79664 they left¦79664 Sukkit¦79665 and¦79666 camped¦79666 at Etam¦79667 at the edge of the wilderness¦79670.
\v 7 \add ≈After\add* Etam¦79673, they turned¦79674 back to Pi-Hahirot (opposite Baal-Tsefon) and¦79672 camped¦79685 \add ≈facing\add* Migdal.
\v 8 Then¦79689 they left¦79689 Pi-Hahirot¦79691 and walked through the middle¦79693 of the sea¦79695 into the Etam¦79702 wilderness and camped¦79703 at¦79693 Marah¦79704.
\v 9 From Marah¦79707, they went¦79708 to Eylim which had twelve springs¦79713 with¦79710 seventy¦79715 palm¦79716 trees¦79716 \add around them\add*, and¦79706 they camped¦79717 there¦79719.
\v 10 \add ≈After\add* Eylam, they camped¦79723 beside the Red Sea
\v 11 before leaving the sea¦79731 and camping in the Sin¦79737 wilderness.\f + \fr 33:11 \ft Note that this is located in the southwestern Sinai Peninsula (between Eylim and Mt. Sinai), and different from the Tsin \+add (Zin)\+add* wilderness (which is located in the northern Negev desert, near Kadesh-Barnea).\f*
\v 12 \add ≈Travelling¦79742 from there,\add* they camped¦79743 at¦79744 Dofkah¦79744,
\v 13 and¦79748 then¦79746 from there, at¦79749 Alush¦79749.
\v 14 \add ≈After leaving\add* Alush¦79752, they camped¦79753 at¦79754 Refidim¦79754 \add but¦79751\add* they didn't¦79755 have water¦79759 there¦79758 to drink¦79761.
\v 15 \add ≈When¦79763\add* they left¦79763 Refidim¦79764, they camped¦79765 in¦79766 the Sinai¦79767 wilderness¦79766.
\s1 The journey legs in the wilderness
\p
\v 16 From the Sinai¦79771 wilderness¦79770, they went to Kivot-Hattaavah and¦79772 camped¦79772 \add there\add*.
\v 17 \add ≈When¦79776\add* they left¦79776 Kivot-Hattaavah, they camped¦79779 at¦79780 Hatserot,
\v 18 and¦79784 then¦79782 from there, at¦79785 Ritmah¦79785.
\v 19 From Ritmah¦79788, they \add went to\add* Rimmon¦79790-Perets to camp,
\v 20 and¦79796 after that, on¦79797 to Livnah¦79797.
\v 21 Then¦79799 they left¦79799 Livnah¦79800 and¦79801 camped¦79801 at¦79802 Rissah¦79802,
\v 22 \add ≈before moving on¦79807 from there to\add* camp at¦79807 Kehelatah¦79807.
\v 23 From Kehelatah¦79810, they camped¦79811 at¦79812 Mt¦79812. Shefer¦79814,
\v 24 then¦79816 they left¦79816 \add *the mountain\add* and¦79820 camped¦79820 at¦79821 Haradah¦79821.
\v 25 \add ≈When¦79823\add* they left¦79823 Haradah¦79824, they camped¦79825 at¦79826 Makhelot¦79826,
\v 26 and¦79830 after that, on¦79831 to Tahat¦79831.
\v 27 From Tahat¦79834, they camped¦79835 at¦79836 Terah¦79836,
\v 28 and¦79840 then¦79838 from Terah¦79839, they went to Mitkah¦79841 to camp.
\v 29 \add ≈After\add* Mitkah¦79844, they camped¦79845 at¦79846 Hashmonah¦79846,
\v 30 and¦79850 \add ≈next after that\add*, they camped¦79850 at¦79851 Moserot¦79851.
\v 31 Then¦79853 they left¦79853 Moserot¦79854 and¦79855 camped¦79855 at¦79856 Bene-Yaakan.
\v 32 From Bene-Yaakan, they \add went to\add* Hor-Haggidgad and¦79862 camped¦79862 \add there\add*,
\v 33 then¦79866 they left¦79866 and¦79869 camped¦79869 at¦79870 Yotbatah¦79870.
\v 34 Then¦79872 they left¦79872 Yotbatah and¦79874 camped¦79874 at¦79875 Avronah.
\v 35 From Avronah, they \add went to\add* Etsyon-Gever and¦79879 camped¦79879 \add there\add*,
\v 36 then¦79883 they left¦79883 and¦79886 camped¦79886 in¦79887 the Tsin¦79889 \add (Zin¦79889)\add* wilderness¦79887, i.e., at¦79887 Kadesh¦79891.
\v 37 Then¦79893 they left¦79893 Kadesh¦79894 and¦79893 camped¦79895 at¦79896 Mt¦79897. Hor¦79896 by the border¦79898 with¦79896 Edom¦79900.
\p
\v 38 Aharon \add (Aaron¦79903)\add* the priest¦79904 \add ≈climbed\add* Mt¦79908. Hor¦79907 \add ≈following Yahweh's instructions\add*, and¦79902 then¦79902 died¦79913 there¦79914 on¦79923 the 5th of the first¦79925 month, forty¦79916 years after¦79917 the \add ≈Israelis¦79920\add* had left Egypt¦79922.\x + \xo 33:38: \xt Num 20:22-28; Deu 10:6; 32:50.\x*
\v 39 \add *He\add* was 123 years old when he died¦79935 \add there\add* on¦79935 Mt¦79937. Hor¦79936.
\p
\v 40 \add ≈Meanwhile,\add* the Canaanite¦79941 king¦79942 of Arad¦79943 who lived in the Negev¦79947 in Kanaan, heard that the \add ≈Israelis¦79951\add* were coming¦79950.
\p
\v 41 \add @The Israelis\add* left¦79954 Mt¦79956. Hor¦79955 and¦79957 camped¦79957 at¦79958 Tsalmonah¦79958.
\rem /s1 Instructions before Crossing the Jordan
\v 42 \add ≈When¦79960\add* they left¦79960 Tsalmonah¦79961, they camped¦79962 at¦79963 Punon¦79963,
\v 43 and¦79967 \add ≈after that\add*, on¦79968 to Ovot.
\v 44 \add ≈From\add* Ovot, they \add went on¦79973\add* to Iyey-Haavarim at¦79973 the Moav border¦79975.
\v 45 Then¦79978 they left¦79978 \add *there\add* and¦79980 camped¦79980 at¦79981 Divon¦79981-Gad¦79979,
\v 46 \add ≈before going on¦79988 to\add* camp at¦79988 Almon-Divlatayim.
\v 47 \add ≈From there,\add* they \add went into\add* the Avarim mountains¦79995 and¦79994 camped¦79994 \add ≈facing\add* Nevo.
\v 48 \add ≈After leaving\add* the Avarim mountains¦80001, they \add ≈reached\add* the Moav plains¦80004 by the Yarden \add (Jordan) river\add* \add ≈opposite\add* Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 49 They camped¦80010 \add ≈beside\add* the \add *river\add* from Beyt-Hayshimot to Avel-Shittim \add there\add* on¦80019 the Moav plains¦80019.
\rem /s1 Directions for the Conquest of Canaan
\p
\v 50 Then Yahweh¦80024 spoke¦80023 to Mosheh¦80027 \add there\add* on¦80028 the Moav plains¦80028 beside the Yarden \add ≈opposite\add* Yeriho,
\v 51 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦80039\add* that you're all about¦80045 to cross¦80045 the Yahweh to enter Canaan¦80052.
\v 52 Then¦80054 you all must¦80054 \add ≈drive¦80054 all the land's inhabitants¦80059 out ahead of you\add*, and destroy all their carved¦80066 images and cast metal¦80071 images, and all their \add ≈hilltop shrines\add*.
\v 53 Take the land from there and¦80079 start to live there, because I've¦80088 given¦80088 \add *it\add* to all of you to own¦80079.
\v 54 \add ≈Use lots\add* to divide the land up for your clans¦80100. \add ≈The larger¦80101 groups must¦80095 get more than the smaller¦80106 groups\add*, then¦80095 \add ≈whatever the lot gives, that will be the area to be given within the land for that ancestral¦80121 tribe¦80120\add*.\x + \xo 33:54: \xt Num 26:54-56.\x*
\p
\v 55 If you don't¦80126 \add ≈drive out the current inhabitants¦80130\add*, then¦80124 they'll become like barbs¦80137 in your eyes¦80138 and thorns¦80139 in your sides¦80140, and they'll harass you all \add ≈when you live there\add*.
\v 56 \add ≈If that happens,\add* then¦80151 I'll¦80156 \add ≈give you all the punishment\add* that I intended¦80153 for them.”
\c 34
\s1 The boundaries within Canaan
\rem /s1 Boundaries of Canaan; Boundaries of the Land; The Boundaries of the Land
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦80161 told Mosheh¦80164 \add (Moses¦80164)\add*,
\v 2 “Tell the \add ≈people¦80170\add* that you're all about¦80177 to enter Canaan¦80181—the land that will become your inheritance¦80187. \add ≈The boundaries¦80190 will be\add*:
\p
\v 3 “The \bd southern¦80196\bd* border will extend from the Tsin¦80199 wilderness¦80197 along the Edom¦80203 border across to the Salt \add (Dead)\add* Sea on the east,
\v 4 cross south of the Scorpion Pass, continue to Tsin¦80221, and go south of Kadesh-Barnea. Then¦80214 it will go on to Hatsar-Addar¦80231 and proceed to Atsmon,
\v 5 From Atsmon \add it¦80235 will extend west\add* to the riverbed at the border¦80236 with Egypt¦80239, and¦80240 then¦80235 across to the \add Mediterranean\add* Sea.
\p
\v 6 “The \bd western\bd* border¦80255 will be the \add ≈Mediterranean\add* sea¦80248.
\p
\v 7 “The \bd northern¦80263\bd* border¦80262 will start at the \add ≈Mediterranean\add* sea¦80266 and¦80258 extend west to Mt¦80271. Hor¦80270,
\v 8 and then on to Levo-Hamat¦80277 and onward to Tsedad¦80281.
\v 9 \add From there\add* the border will extend¦80283 to Zifron¦80285, and¦80283 it will end at Hatsar-Eynan, \add ≈completing\add* the northern¦80295 border.
\p
\v 10 “The \bd eastern¦80300\bd* border¦80299 will begin at Hatsar-Eynan and¦80297 extend \add south\add* to Shefam¦80303,
\v 11 then go downhill to Rivlah east of Ayin, then along the \add ≈hills\add* to the east of Lake Galilee \add (Heb. Kinneret¦80319)\add*.
\v 12 Then¦80322 the border will extend \add south\add* along the Yarden \add River\add* and¦80322 \add ≈end¦80326 at\add* the Salt \add (Dead)\add* Sea.
\p “Those will be your \add ≈country's\add* borders.”
\p
\v 13 Then¦80336 Mosheh¦80337 \add ≈continued\add*, “That will be the land that¦80345 \add must¦80346 be distributed\add* by lot. It'll be given by Yahweh¦80351 as an inheritance¦80346 for the nine¦80353 tribes¦80354 and¦80336 the Menashsheh half-tribe\x + \xo 34:13: \xt Num 26:52-56.\x*
\v 14 \add as\add* the Reuven and Gad¦80368 tribes and the Menashsheh half-tribe have already received their inheritance¦80375.
\v 15 \add Yes,\add* the \add other¦80383\add* two¦80377 and¦80379 a half tribes¦80378 have taken¦80381 up their¦80382 inheritance¦80382 on the eastern¦80386 side of the Yarden \add river\add* across from Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\s1 The teachers egpepamaaren of land
\rem /s1 Tribal Leaders; Leaders to Divide the Land; The Leaders Responsible for Dividing the Land
\p
\v 16 Then Yahweh¦80391 told Mosheh¦80394,
\v 17 “These¦80397 are the men¦80399 who will \add ≈distribute\add* the land: the priest¦80408 Eleazar¦80407 and Nun's¦80412 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*,
\v 18 as well as one leader from each tribe¦80418 to allocate the land that will be their inheritance¦80420.
\v 19 Those \add tribe¦80428\add* leaders are:
\li1 From Yehudah¦80429 \add (Judah)\add*, Yefunneh's¦80433 son Kalev \add (Caleb¦80430)\add*,
\li1
\v 20 From Shimeon, Ammihud's¦80441 son Shemuel¦80438,
\li1
\v 21 From Benyamin¦80444, Kislon's son Elidad¦80445,
\li1
\v 22 From Dan¦80453, Yogli's¦80458 son Bukki¦80455,
\li1
\v 23 From Menashsheh, Efod's¦80470 son Hanniyel,
\li1
\v 24 From Efrayim, Shiftan's¦80480 son Kemuel¦80477,
\li1
\v 25 From Zevulun, Parnach's¦80490 son Elizafan¦80487,
\li1
\v 26 From Yissakar, Azzan's¦80500 son Paltiel¦80497,
\li1
\v 27 From Asher¦80505, Shelomi's¦80510 son Ahihud¦80507,
\li1
\v 28 From Naftali¦80515, Ammihud's¦80520 son Pedahel¦80517.”
\p
\v 29 \add ≈The above\add* are \add the men\add* that Yahweh¦80525 \add ≈put in charge of dividing up\add* Kanaan as the inheritance¦80526 for the \add ≈Israelis¦80529\add*.
\c 35
\s1 Cities for the Levites
\rem /s1 Towns for the Levites; The Cities Assigned to the Levites; Cities for the Levites
\p
\v 1 \add ≈While\add* they were there on¦80541 the Moav plains¦80541 beside the Yarden \add river\add*, Yahweh¦80537 told Mosheh¦80540 \add (Moses¦80540)\add*.\x + \xo 35:1-8: \xt Josh 21:1-42.\x*
\v 2 “Tell the \add Israelis¦80552\add* that out of the land that they'll \add ≈own¦80557\add*, they must¦80554 give the Levites¦80555 cities for them to live in, \add ≈as well as\add* some pastureland¦80560 around¦80562 \add &those\add* cities.
\v 3 The cities¦80567 will be for them to live¦80569 in, and that pastureland¦80570 will be for their herds and their flocks, and for their other animals¦80575.
\v 4 The pastureland¦80577 must¦80580 extend out half a kilometre around¦80587 the walls of the Levites¦80581 cities¦80578.
\v 5 Then¦80589 going out a kilometre \add ≈in each compass direction\add*, that will also be their land.\f + \fr 35:5 \ft It's not exactly clear what different activities would occur in these two rings of land, but remember that as much food as possible and animals would have to be brought into the city as soon as the residents received news of an approaching army.\f*
\rem /s1 Cities of Refuge
\v 6 The Levites¦80631 \add ≈must be given forty-two cities to live in, plus¦80642\add* you all must \add ≈designate\add* six refuge cities so that¦80629 if someone accidentally kills another, they can flee to the refuge city.
\v 7 \add ≈That would make a total of\add* forty-eight cities¦80650, plus¦80655 their¦80660 pasturelands¦80660, to be given to the Levites¦80653.
\v 8 The larger¦80670 tribes must¦80664 give more cities than the smaller¦80673 tribes, according¦80676 to the area that¦80663 they inherit¦80677.”
\s1 The refuge cities
\rem /s1 Cities of Refuge; The Cities of Refuge
\r (Deu. 19:1-13; Josh. 20:1-9)
\p
\v 9 Then Yahweh¦80686 told Mosheh¦80689,\x + \xo 35:9-28: \xt Deu 19:2-4; Josh 20:1-9.\x*
\v 10 “Tell the \add ≈Israelis¦80695\add* that when you¦80697 cross¦80701 the Yarden \add river\add* \add ≈to enter\add* Kanaan,
\v 11 you all must¦80708 choose some cities to become ‘refuge¦80712 cities’ \add so that\add* if someone accidentally¦80721 kills another person¦80720, they can flee there¦80716.
\v 12 The cities¦80725 will be places to stay safe from \add ≈being avenged¦80727\add* \add by the relatives\add* until¦80731 the killer¦80730 can \add ≈be formally tried\add*.
\v 13 You all must¦80740 \add ≈allocate\add* six refuge¦80744 cities—
\v 14 three on the eastern side of the Yarden, and there on the western side in Kanann.
\v 15 Both¦80766 \add ≈Israelis¦80765\add* and \add ≈foreigners living in¦80769 the country\add* can flee to \add any of\add* those six¦80771 cities¦80773—anyone¦80780 who kills \add another\add* person¦80782 by accident¦80783.
\rem /s1 Concerning Murder and Blood Revenge
\p
\v 16 “However, if someone strikes¦80790 \add @another person\add* with¦80787 \add ≈a metal object¦80787\add* and they die¦80794, then¦80785 that person is a murderer, and murderers must¦80795 be \add ≈executed\add*.
\v 17 \add ≈Similarly,\add* anyone who strikes¦80805 \add @another person\add* when holding a \add rock¦80799 or\add* stone¦80799, then¦80798 that¦80801 person is a murderer, and¦80798 murderers must¦80803 be \add ≈executed\add*.
\v 18 \add ≈Again,\add* if someone¦80820 strikes¦80822 \add @another person\add* with¦80814 a piece of wood, then that¦80818 person is a murderer, and murderers must¦80820 be \add ≈executed\add*.
\v 19 The \add relative who\add* is avenging¦80830 the \add spilt\add* blood¦80831 must¦80833 \add ≈execute the murderer¦80836 as soon as he finds them\add*.
\p
\v 20 “If someone pushes¦80846 \add @another person\add* in hatred¦80845, or lies in wait and¦80852 then¦80843 throws something at¦80845 them,
\v 21 or angrily strikes¦80856 them with¦80855 their hand¦80857, and then they die¦80859, \add ≈it must be regarded as murder,\add* and when the avenger¦80865 of their blood¦80866 finds the murderer, he must \add ≈execute\add* them.
\p
\v 22 “\add ≈But¦80875\add* if someone pushes¦80881 \add @another person\add* without any hateful \add intent\add*, or throws something at¦80877 them without lying¦80890 in¦80877 wait,
\v 23 or drops a rock¦80895 without \add ≈noticing\add* someone¦80898, and they die¦80898 \add ≈but¦80902\add* they weren't \add @that person's\add* enemy¦80908 and no harm was intended,
\v 24 then¦80914 the community must¦80914 judge¦80914 between the \add ≈one who killed\add* and¦80918 the avenger¦80919 \add ≈of the dead person\add*, in accordance with these¦80923 regulations.
\v 25 \add If the one who killed is declared innocent\add*, then¦80925 the community must rescue them from the avenger¦80931 and return¦80933 them to the refuge¦80939 city¦80938 that they'd fled to, and \add ≈that accidental killer\add* must live¦80944 there¦80943 until¦80946 after the death¦80948 of the high priest¦80949 (who had been anointed¦80953 with¦80945 sacred¦80956 oil¦80955).
\v 26 \add ≈However,\add* if they then¦80958 ever left the refuge¦80967 city¦80966 that they'd fled to,
\v 27 and the avenger found them outside¦80976 the city boundary, then¦80972 \add ≈that relative of the dead person\add* is permitted to kill that person and won't¦80986 be accountable for their blood.
\v 28 \add That's\add* because the \add ≈one who killed¦81004\add* must¦80993 remain¦80993 in¦80991 that city¦80991 until¦80994 the death of the high priest—they can only return¦81003 to \add ≈their family home\add* after¦80999 the high priest's death.
\v 29 You all must¦81010 \add follow\add* these¦81011 regulations¦81013 through¦81015 the generations¦81015 no matter where you live¦81017.
\p
\v 30 “\add If\add* someone¦81026 murders¦81029 \add another\add* person¦81023, they're to be executed if there's evidence¦81024 from witnesses (\add plural,\add* not just one witness).
\v 31 That sentence \add ≈can't¦81038 be changed to a fine and¦81038/or a payment to the deceased's family\add*—\add @the murderer\add* \em must¦81040\em* be executed.
\v 32 \add ≈Similarly for the accidental killer who fled to a refuge¦81062 city¦81061\add*, they can't¦81054 \add ≈elect to pay a fine and¦81054/or pay compensation\add* in order to be able to return¦81063 \add ≈home\add* before the high priest's¦81069 death¦81068.
\v 33 You mustn't profane the land that¦81077 you're all going to \add by tolerating murder\add*, because \add human\add* blood pollutes¦81073 the ground, and¦81071 you all can't¦81071 \add ≈restore the land with¦81079 any sacrifice\add*—only by the blood of the one who shed \add someone else's\add* blood.
\v 34 You mustn't profane the land that¦81107 you'll all be living in because I'll also be living in it¦81114, as I will live among \add you\add* \add ≈Israelis¦81120\add*.”
\c 36
\s1 Women inheriting property
\rem /s1 Women Who Inherit Property; Marriage of Female Heirs; The Inheritance of Married Women; Inheritance of Zelophehad's Daughters
\p
\v 1 \add ≈Now\add* the leaders of the Gilead clans¦81137 (\add ≡Gilead was\add* the son of Makir¦81133, son of Menashsheh, one of Yosef's¦81139 sons) approached Mosheh¦81142 and the \add ≈Israeli¦81148\add* leaders
\v 2 and said, “Yahweh commanded my master to \add ≈distribute\add* the land by lot as an inheritance \add ≈for the people¦81162\add*, and my master was \add also\add* commanded by Yahweh to give our brother¦81172 Tselofehad's inheritance to his daughters¦81173.\x + \xo 36:2: \xt Num 27:7.\x*
\v 3 \add ≈However¦81181, if\add* they \add ended up\add* \add ≈being married by men from other\add* tribes, then¦81175 their inheritance would \add ≈pass from our tribe to their husbands' tribes, so we'd end up with less land as our tribal\add* inheritance.
\v 4 Then¦81198 when Yisrael¦81203 celebrates the Jubilee \add Year\add*, then¦81198 that¦81209 inheritance will be added¦81204 to the inheritance of \add @their husbands'\add* tribes, and¦81198 be deducted from the inheritance of our¦81214 \add ≈ancestral¦81214\add* tribe.”
\p
\v 5 Then¦81218 Mosheh¦81219 \add ≈gave a ruling\add* to the \add ≈Israelis¦81222\add* \add ≈in accordance with what Yahweh¦81227 had told¦81218 him\add*, “These \add ≈Yosefite men\add* are correct.
\v 6 Yahweh's \add ≈command¦81240\add* to Tselofehad's daughters¦81242 is that¦81238 \add ≈each of you may marry whoever you want as long as it's someone from your own\add* tribe¦81251.
\v 7 That¦81273 way, land \add ≈in¦81268 Yisrael¦81261\add* won't¦81256 \add ≈move\add* from tribe to tribe, because \add ≈it¦81258 will always stay as part of\add* the inheritance \add ≈given to that\add* tribe.
\v 8 \add ≈Any woman¦81288 who inherits land can only marry someone from her¦81286 own\add* tribe¦81280, so that the people will \add always\add* \add ≈retain ownership of their tribal\add* inheritance.
\v 9 \add &That\add* inheritance mustn't pass from tribe to tribe, but¦81297 each \add ≈Israeli¦81311\add* tribe must¦81299 keep hold of its¦81307 inheritance.”
\p
\v 10 ⇔So Tselofehad's¦81322 daughters¦81321 obeyed what Yahweh¦81315 had told¦81314 Mosheh¦81318,
\v 11 and the \add five\add* daughters¦81330 (Mahlah¦81325, Tirtsah, Hoglah¦81327, Milkah, and Noah¦81329) married their \add ≈cousins on their father's¦81333 side\add*.
\v 12 \add ≈The men they¦81343 married\add* were from the Menashsheh tribe (Yosef's¦81342 son), so \add ≈their land continued to belong to their father's¦81351 family and\add* tribe.
\p
\v 13 \add ≈All the above\add* were the commands¦81354 and regulations that¦81356 Yahweh¦81358 ordered¦81357 Mosheh¦81361 to tell the \add ≈Israelis¦81364\add*, \add while they were camped\add* on¦81359 the Moav plains¦81366 beside the Yarden \add river\add* \add ≈opposite\add* Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
